a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 F.
a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 In a large mixing bowl, add the flours, sugar, baking power, baking soda, and salt. Stir to combine.
a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 In a separate medium mixing bowl, whisk together the milk and sourdough starter until combined.
a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 Add the butter pieces to the dry ingredients. Mash all of the pieces of butter through the tines of a fork or pastry blender once.
a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 Add the wet ingredients to the dry and stir just until a shaggy dough forms.
a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 Turn the rough dough out onto a floured surface and form it into a 1-inch thick rectangle. Fold the rectangle in thirds like a business letter. Dust the dough lightly with flour and use a rolling pin to roll it out to 1 1/2 inches thick. Repeat the letter fold and roll the dough again, this time to a thickness of about 3/4 of an inch.
a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 Cut the dough into your desired shape. We prefer square biscuits because there is no leftover scrap dough.
a165c9ac-5e77-4f0c-ac57-2a2e2cbef5f8 Place the biscuits on a parchment-lined baking sheet and brush the tops with milk. Bake for about 15 minutes, or until golden and well-risen. Serve immediately.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 Gather the ingredients.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt. Whisk or stir to blend thoroughly.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 In another bowl, whisk together the eggs and milk.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 Add the egg-milk mixture to the flour mixture, stirring just until blended.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 Mix in the melted butter. If the batter seems too thick to spread, add a little more milk.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 Using about 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake, drop onto a hot, greased griddle.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 Cook until you see that the bubbles over the surface are breaking and the edges appear somewhat dry.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 Turn to brown the other side and finish cooking.
b4c0fa8b-f4e6-4668-9e98-ef5fa639eed4 Top with your favorite toppings and enjoy!
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Cut the butter into small pieces and put on a plate in the freezer.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Spread the pecan halves out in a dry skillet and cook over medium heat, stirring, until they are lightly browned and begin to smell toasty. Remove to a plate and let them cool. Alternatively, toast the pecans on a baking sheet in a 400 F oven for about 5 minutes, turning about halfway through the cooking time. Remove the pecans to a plate to cool.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Heat the oven to 350 F or reduce the heat from 400 F to 350 F if you toasted the pecans in the oven.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Put the 1/2 cup of granulated sugar, all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt, if using, in the bowl of the food processor. Add the cooled pecans. Pulse until the mixture is fine.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Add the frozen pieces of butter to the flour and pecan mixture and pulse until the mixture resembles fine meal. Pour the flour mixture into a large bowl.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Stir the mini chocolate chips into the dry ingredients and then make a well in the center. Pour the 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons of heavy cream into the center along with the vanilla extract. Blend the flour mixture into the cream with your hands until moistened.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Turn the dough out onto a floured surface and knead a few times, just enough to make a smooth ball. Do not overwork the dough.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c With floured hands or a floured rolling pin, roll the dough out into a circle about 3/4-inch thick. It will be about 10 to 12 inches in diameter.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c With a round or square biscuit cutter â€” any size will do â€” cut out the scones. Gather the scraps of dough together and lightly press them together â€” again, not overworking â€” and cut out the remaining scones.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Place the cut-out scones on the prepared baking sheet, leaving about 2 inches between them.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Brush the scones lightly with some heavy cream and sprinkle with plain granulated sugar or vanilla sugar.
62e80bfb-b849-4c6b-8756-6029a557822c Bake the scones for about 18 to 22 minutes, or until the scones are browned.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 425 F.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Add the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt to a large bowl and mix.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Using the large side of a box grater, grate in the cold butter and then stir with your fingers to make sure it's coated in the flour mixture. Alternately, you can cut the butter into 1 inch pieces and work it in with your fingers, a fork, or a pastry cutter until the largest pieces are the size of peas.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Pour in the milk and lemon zest and stir to roughly mix. Add the blueberries and mix just until barely incorporated.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Turn the dough out onto well-floured surface and roll it out to about a 1-inch thickness.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Using a 2 1/2-inch cookie or biscuit cutter, cut out the biscuit rounds and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until the biscuits are a light golden brown. Let cool slightly.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 To make the lemon glaze, whisk together the powdered sugar, milk ,and lemon juice until smooth.
5631a3f1-2e51-4442-9b1b-5e6374a63fe4 Pour over the slightly cooled biscuits and serve.
b4aa3b51-ba7d-4e31-8807-9c05dc9fb7ee Butter a 9-by-13-inch baking dish. Heat the oven to 325 F (165 C/Gas 3).
b4aa3b51-ba7d-4e31-8807-9c05dc9fb7ee Cube bread and place evenly in the prepared baking dish. Sprinkle evenly with sausage and cheese.
b4aa3b51-ba7d-4e31-8807-9c05dc9fb7ee In a bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk, salt, and pepper. Pour over the layers in the pan.
b4aa3b51-ba7d-4e31-8807-9c05dc9fb7ee Bake 45 minutes or until set. Cut into squares to serve.
b4aa3b51-ba7d-4e31-8807-9c05dc9fb7ee This casserole may also be prepared the night before. Just cover and refrigerate the unbaked casserole. Take it out of the refrigerator about 15 minutes before baking time; bake as directed.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 Gather the ingredients.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 12 cup muffin tin or spray with baking spray.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 In a large skillet or saute pan over medium heat, melt the butter. Add the chopped onions and mushrooms and cook, stirring, until the onions are softened and mushrooms are tender. Add the spinach, about 1/3 at a time, and cook, stirring, until the greens are all wilted. Set aside to cool slightly.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 In a large bowl, whisk the eggs and egg whites until blended. Stir in the shredded cheese, pepper, salt, and nutmeg. Stir in the cooled spinach mixture.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 Spoon the mixture into muffin cups, filling each about half full.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 Bake for about 25 minutes, until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean. The quiches will puff up but will deflate soon after removing them from the oven.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 Let them cool for a few minutes, then use a spatula to lift them out onto a tray or plate.
a6c11e5d-ea25-4273-ba6b-8ccfd8c3a477 Enjoy!
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f Gather the ingredients.
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, and allspice.
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f Slice the French bread into slices that are at least 1-inch thick. You can use a whole-grain French loaf, but any French or Italian bread should work nicely. Slice at a slight angle to make a longer piece of bread.
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f Soak each slice in the egg custard mixture. Turn the slices until all of the mixture has been absorbed into the bread. Depending on how stale the bread is, this may take from 5 to 10 minutes. The secret to this recipe is to completely saturate the bread. This is why thick slices of stale bread are used since thinner fresh bread would fall apart too easily. Make sure to flip the bread so all sides can soak evenly.
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f Preheat oven to 400 F. In a large non-stick skillet over medium heat, very lightly brown the slices in the butter and oil for about 2 minutes per side. Don't make it too dark as it will also be baking in the oven.
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f From the frying pan or skillet, transfer to a baking sheet or casserole dish. Bake for 10 minutes. After 10 minutes, remove from the oven, turn over, and put back in the oven for another 5 minutes to brown on the other side.
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f Traditionally, pain perdu is served with powdered sugar sprinkled over the top. If you want it to look like it would in the French Quarter, then dust away and dig in. You can also top it with maple syrup or fruit sauces like jellies, jams, or marmalades.
e6012bec-9bb4-4b8b-81d6-05f453b42e6f Serve and enjoy!
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 Gather the ingredients.
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 Grease and flour 12 muffin cups or line with paper liners. Preheat the oven to 375 F (190 C).
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 In a medium bowl, combine the salt, baking powder, flour, sugar, and cinnamon.
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 Toss the cherries in 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, and stir gently to combine.
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 In a separate bowl, whisk the egg, vanilla extract, milk, and melted butter until well-blended.
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 Stir the egg and milk mixture into the dry mixture until moistened.
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 Fill the muffin cups about two-thirds full.
8f07d0f2-7b61-4d01-817d-f3e803998b69 Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean. Let the muffins cool for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Heat the oven to 375 F / 190 C / Gas 5. Line a 12-cup muffin tin with muffin/cupcake papers.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the butter with the granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Beat the egg and 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla into the creamed mixture.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b In another bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt; mix well to blend.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Add about one-third of the flour to the first mixture along with half of the milk; blend well.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Add another one-third of the flour mixture and the remaining milk; mix until blended.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Add the remaining flour and mix until well blended.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Stir in the shredded carrots and chopped walnuts.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Fill the prepared muffin cups almost full.
92bdf67f-4e10-49d0-8936-a259f059347b Bake the muffins for about 25 minutes, or until browned and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Gather the ingredients.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 In a mixing bowl, mix together flour and salt.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Cut in cold butter with a pastry blender until coarse crumbs form.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Add water, a little at a time, until dough holds together and forms a ball.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Shape into a disk, wrap in plastic wrap, and refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 On a lightly floured surface with a floured rolling pin, roll out dough into a circle about 12 inches in diameter.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Fit dough into a 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan. Trim edges, leaving a little overhang, about 1/4-inch all around the edge. Prick dough with a fork.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Line with foil and fill with dried beans or pie weights.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Bake quiche crust for 10 minutes at 375 F.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, thyme, and pepper.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Pour into the baked crust and crumble bacon over the top with the shredded Cheddar cheese.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Bake at 375 F for about 30 minutes, or until quiche filling is set and the top is lightly browned.
1de7c809-ff35-483e-a296-dac9287a8792 Serve the quiche with fresh tomato wedges or a tossed salad.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Gather the ingredients.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Bring the water and salt to a boil in a large heavy saucepan.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Add the grits and continue to simmer, stirring constantly, over medium heat until the grits are cooked and thick like mush, about 15 to 20 minutes. If necessary, add a little more boiling water.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Pour the hot grits onto a large plate or medium baking sheet to make a layer about 3/4-inch deep. Cover and let stand to cool, then refrigerate to chill thoroughly.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 When the grits are cold and firm, cut them into rectangular pieces or use biscuit cutters and cut rounds.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Dredge the grits pieces with flour, shaking off any excess flour.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Heat about 1/2-inch of vegetable oil in a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat. Fry the grits cakes until golden brown on both sides, about four to five minutes total.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.
9cf51cbe-a3e8-4d95-92f8-e20b7ac69e46 Serve hot.
2841051c-13a0-47c2-9418-13993c91ffa9 Preheat the oven to 350° F. Grease and flour a standard 12-cup muffin pan, or spray with baking spray which contains flour.
2841051c-13a0-47c2-9418-13993c91ffa9 In a large bowl, whisk the milk, eggs, flour, salt, and pepper until well blended. Stir in the cheddar cheese, chopped broccoli, and bell pepper.
2841051c-13a0-47c2-9418-13993c91ffa9 Spoon the mixture into the prepared pan, filling each cup nearly to the rim.
2841051c-13a0-47c2-9418-13993c91ffa9 Bake for 26 to 32 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center of a quiche comes out clean.
d5d28661-5c5f-48fd-be0e-160080232a21 Gather the ingredients.
d5d28661-5c5f-48fd-be0e-160080232a21 Heat the oven to 375 F. Grease 12 muffin cups or spray with baking spray.
d5d28661-5c5f-48fd-be0e-160080232a21 In a large bowl, combine the all-purpose flour, 3/4 cup of granulated sugar, the baking powder and soda, and salt. Use a whisk to blend the dry ingredients thoroughly.
d5d28661-5c5f-48fd-be0e-160080232a21 In another bowl, combine sour cream with the egg, melted butter, lemon zest, and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice. Whisk the mixture until smooth and well blended.
d5d28661-5c5f-48fd-be0e-160080232a21 Blend the sour cream mixture into the dry ingredients just until blended and all ingredients are moistened.
d5d28661-5c5f-48fd-be0e-160080232a21 Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full. Bake for 18 minutes or until browned and a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the center of a muffin. Cool in the pan on a rack for 5 minutes. Remove the muffins to a rack. Place foil or a pan under the rack to catch drips. Poke each muffin several times with a toothpick.
d5d28661-5c5f-48fd-be0e-160080232a21 Meanwhile, bring the 1/3 cup of lemon juice and 1/4 cup of sugar to a boil in a small saucepan. Cook, stirring until sugar is completely dissolved. Using a spoon, drizzle a little of the juice mixture over each muffin.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b Grease the inside of the crock pot with 1 tablespoon of the butter.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b Measure the remaining ingredients and add them to slow cooker with remaining butter.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b Stir well.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b Cover and cook on low for 6 to 9 hours (3 to 4 hours on high), stirring occasionally.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b If desired, transfer the polenta or grits mixture to a greased loaf pan.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b Chill thoroughly then cut into 1/4-inch slices.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b Fry the slices in butter or bacon drippings until browned.
4c1fe20a-1239-434b-b4d1-88187ebfda3b Fried polenta or grits cakes make a tasty base for chicken à la king, creamy shrimp or seafood dishes, or a meaty stew or chili.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 Gather the ingredients.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 In a shallow bowl, whisk egg and egg white until foamy.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 Whisk in the milk, vanilla, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 Heat a warming drawer or heat the oven to 200 F.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 Heat butter in a heavy skillet over medium-low heat. Dip 4 slices of bread in the egg mixture, turning to coat thoroughly. Let excess drip back into a bowl.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 Place coated bread slices in a hot skillet. Cook, turning with a spatula until both sides are nicely browned, about 2 minutes each side.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 Transfer to a warm plate and keep warm in the oven (or warming drawer). Repeat with remaining slices of bread and egg mixture.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 To serve, sprinkle with cinnamon sugar if desired.
2f847658-d170-4781-9744-9ad144c63017 Serve with maple syrup, golden cane syrup, sorghum, or your favorite pancake syrup. Enjoy!
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d Gather the ingredients.
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d Heat the oven to 400 F.
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d Grease muffin cups or line with cupcake papers (about 18).
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d Toss the cranberries with 1/4 cup of sugar in a bowl; set aside.
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, and remaining 1 cup sugar. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d In another bowl combine eggs with milk; stir into flour mixture until just moistened.
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d Gently fold in nuts and orange peel and cranberries.
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d Fill the prepared muffin cups about two-thirds full.
98a1c5d5-3669-4f2c-b047-49a4f70c1b3d Bake in the preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
997a065a-ece2-4811-8313-c1608b2d04a6 In a small mixing bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff; set aside.
997a065a-ece2-4811-8313-c1608b2d04a6 In another bowl beat the egg yolks; add milk and melted butter.
997a065a-ece2-4811-8313-c1608b2d04a6 Sift dry ingredients together; add to the egg yolk mixture and mix until smooth. Fold in blueberries. Gently fold in beaten egg whites.
997a065a-ece2-4811-8313-c1608b2d04a6 Bake in a hot waffle iron.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b Gather the ingredients.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b Preheat the oven to 475 F.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b In a small bowl, combine the egg, milk, extract, and lemon zest, if using. Whisk to blend thoroughly. Whisk in the flour until smooth.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b Use a shallow container with sides no more than 3 inches high, such as a small saucepan with an ovenproof handle, or an oven-safe ramekin. A 5-inch cast iron skillet is perfect for one pancake.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b Put the pan in the hot oven and melt 2 teaspoons butter.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b With a potholder or oven mitt, swirl the pan to coat the entire bottom and sides with the melted butter. Pour the batter into the pan and place in the hot oven. Bake the pancake for about 10 minutes, until puffed and golden brown.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b Remove the Dutch baby from oven; squeeze a little fresh lemon juice over it if desired. Serve it sprinkled with powdered sugar or top with syrup, preserves, fresh fruit, spiced warm fruit, sausage, bacon, ham, or a meat substitute.
89db51f2-0f35-43a6-a609-36c2f9d2983b Enjoy!
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add Gather the ingredients.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add Preheat oven to 325 F/165 C. Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan or tube cake pan.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the softened butter with the sugar.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat until light and fluffy. Add and mix in the vanilla.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add Sift 2 cups flour, salt, and baking powder together.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add Add the sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add In a medium bowl, dredge berries in remaining 1/2 cup flour.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add Gently fold floured berries into the batter. Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan.
54eae221-a402-41a3-97cc-6381b1135add Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Gather the ingredients.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Preheat oven to 400 F.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Grease and flour a 12-cup muffin pan.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Rinse and drain raspberries. Put them on paper towels to dry a bit.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 In another smaller bowl, whisk the egg with the milk. Add the egg and milk mixture to the dry mixture along with the melted butter. Mix lightly to combine, just until ingredients are moistened. The batter will be somewhat lumpy.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Sprinkle raspberries and pecans or walnuts over the batter and gently fold into the batter. Spoon into the prepared muffin pans.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Sprinkle cinnamon sugar over each muffin, if desired.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Bake in the preheated oven for 18 to 21 minutes, or until a cake tester or toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the center of a muffin.
9175d154-9d9e-4a3d-8431-ec4275944927 Enjoy!
0c9f17be-0cf4-4c0c-adfd-7c4f8bf8382d Gather the ingredients.
0c9f17be-0cf4-4c0c-adfd-7c4f8bf8382d In a wide, shallow bowl, combine the egg, milk, sugar, and cinnamon, if using, vanilla, and salt. Whisk until the mixture is smooth and well blended.
0c9f17be-0cf4-4c0c-adfd-7c4f8bf8382d In a large skillet over medium-low heat, melt the butter.
0c9f17be-0cf4-4c0c-adfd-7c4f8bf8382d Dip a slice of pound cake in the egg batter mixture, turning carefully to coat both sides. Don't let the cake soak for long or it could break down. Using a spatula, move the coated slice of pound cake to the skillet. Repeat with the remaining slice of cake.
0c9f17be-0cf4-4c0c-adfd-7c4f8bf8382d Let the pound cake slices cook for about 3 minutes, or until the bottoms are browned. Carefully turn each slice to brown the other side.
0c9f17be-0cf4-4c0c-adfd-7c4f8bf8382d Serve pound cake French toast with warm preserves, syrup, fruit or berries, or a dessert sauce. Or simply sprinkle the slices with powdered sugar.
84d54734-6300-4997-8f14-c55afcf57784 In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and vanilla.
84d54734-6300-4997-8f14-c55afcf57784 Cut each slice of bread into four strips.
84d54734-6300-4997-8f14-c55afcf57784 Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
84d54734-6300-4997-8f14-c55afcf57784 Dip the bread strips in the bowl to soak briefly.
84d54734-6300-4997-8f14-c55afcf57784 When the butter is hot, add a batch of soaked bread strips to the skillet and cook until golden brown, turning to brown both sides.
84d54734-6300-4997-8f14-c55afcf57784 Sprinkle with a little confectioners' sugar or a sugar and cinnamon blend and serve with butter and maple syrup. Or top with maple butter or powdered sugar.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Gather the ingredients.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Place the bread in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish; set aside.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb In a bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk, dry mustard, and dried minced onion.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Pour the mixture over the bread.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Sprinkle bacon over casserole.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Cover the casserole and refrigerate it until ready to bake.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Remove the casserole from the refrigerator and let it stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Pre heat oven to 350 F.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Cover the casserole with foil and bake in the oven for 25 minutes.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Uncover, sprinkle with shredded cheddar cheese and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes, or until the eggs are set. To test whether it is done, insert an instant-read thermometer in the center of the casserole. Eggs should be cooked to a minimum of 160 F for food safety.
46e171dd-4097-4a8b-a0c1-738b0de236eb Let the breakfast casserole stand for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting and serving.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Gather the ingredients.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Beat egg yolks in a medium mixing bowl.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Add milk and melted butter.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Stir egg mixture into dry ingredients; mix until batter is smooth and stir in blueberries.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Fold in beaten egg whites.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Cook the pancakes on a hot greased griddle on one side until the edge looks dry and bubbly and the bottom is browned.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Flip the pancake and cook the other side until nicely browned.
4b87d098-a1d2-4270-9fad-917a80b4c28c Serve them with maple syrup or a fresh blueberry sauce and enjoy!
752d5cea-4b95-4826-a0d1-68052497789f Heat the oven to 375 F (190 C/Gas 5). Line muffin cups with paper liners. (The recipe makes 12 to 16 muffins, depending on the size of the muffin cups.)
752d5cea-4b95-4826-a0d1-68052497789f In a large bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. Stir to blend thoroughly.
752d5cea-4b95-4826-a0d1-68052497789f Inâ€‹ a separate bowl, combine the pumpkin, melted butter, milk or half-and-half, the beaten eggs, brown and granulated sugars, and vanilla; mix until blended.
752d5cea-4b95-4826-a0d1-68052497789f Stir pumpkin mixture into the dry ingredients and stir just until moistened. Fold in pecans or raisins, but don't over-mix.
752d5cea-4b95-4826-a0d1-68052497789f Line a muffin tin with paper liners or grease well and dust with flour. Or use a baking spray with flour.
752d5cea-4b95-4826-a0d1-68052497789f Fill each muffin cup about 3/4-full with the pumpkin muffins batter, sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar if desired, and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
752d5cea-4b95-4826-a0d1-68052497789f Serve warm or at room temperature.
13106911-7227-442d-b4e1-a79a713de091 Heat oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4. Butter a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
13106911-7227-442d-b4e1-a79a713de091 In a large skillet, cook sliced sausage with the onion and bell pepper until vegetables are translucent. Whisk eggs with milk in a bowl with the Creole seasoning, pepper, and parsley, if using; set aside.
13106911-7227-442d-b4e1-a79a713de091 Arrange the torn bread pieces over the bottom of the buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with the sausage mixture and the diced tomatoes. Top with Cheddar cheese, then pour the egg mixture evenly over the top. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
13106911-7227-442d-b4e1-a79a713de091 Bake the casserole for 35 to 40 minutes, or until it is puffy and lightly browned.
bff71574-da4a-471e-ac09-c9f9ad996617 Heat the oven to 350 F.
bff71574-da4a-471e-ac09-c9f9ad996617 Line the pie shell with a sheet of foil and fill at least 3/4 full with pie weights or dry beans. Bake the pie shell in the preheated oven for 7 minutes. Remove it to a rack and cool.
bff71574-da4a-471e-ac09-c9f9ad996617 In a skillet over medium heat, brown the sausage, breaking up and turning until the meat is no longer pink. Drain well.
bff71574-da4a-471e-ac09-c9f9ad996617 Arrange the sliced hard-cooked eggs in the bottom of the cooled crust; top with the drained browned sausage and shredded cheeses.
bff71574-da4a-471e-ac09-c9f9ad996617 In a bowl, whisk together the 3 eggs, milk, salt, and pepper. Pour egg mixture over sausage and cheese mixture.
bff71574-da4a-471e-ac09-c9f9ad996617 Bake the quiche in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Remove to a rack and let stand for 8 to 10 minutes before slicing and serving.
a6f72dc5-eea8-4904-97b3-56b0c6dafd78 If you plan to keep batches warm until they are all made, heat the oven to 200 F.
a6f72dc5-eea8-4904-97b3-56b0c6dafd78 In a bowl, whisk the orange juice with the orange zest, buttermilk, and eggs until smooth.
a6f72dc5-eea8-4904-97b3-56b0c6dafd78 In another bowl combine the flour, salt, baking powder, soda, and sugar. Stir into the first mixture, blending well. Add the melted butter and stir until smooth.
a6f72dc5-eea8-4904-97b3-56b0c6dafd78 Heat a skillet or griddle over medium heat. Add the oil to the hot skillet. When the oil is hot, pour about 1/4 cup of batter into the pan for each pancake.
a6f72dc5-eea8-4904-97b3-56b0c6dafd78 When bubbles begin to appear over the top of the pancakes and the edges begin to look dry, flip them and brown the other side lightly.
a6f72dc5-eea8-4904-97b3-56b0c6dafd78 Adjust the heat under the pan, as necessary.
a6f72dc5-eea8-4904-97b3-56b0c6dafd78 Remove the pancakes to a plate and keep warm in the preheated 200 F oven or a warming drawer.
818fdb10-bcab-4acf-bc71-f870cd8d2f44 Gather the ingredients.
818fdb10-bcab-4acf-bc71-f870cd8d2f44 Mix milk, salt, pepper, and hot sauce in a medium-size pot. Bring the liquid to a slight boil over medium-high heat.
818fdb10-bcab-4acf-bc71-f870cd8d2f44 When the milk is bubbling, whisk in the grits. Reduce the heat, letting grits cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.
818fdb10-bcab-4acf-bc71-f870cd8d2f44 Add the butter, cream cheese, and cheddar cheese to the grits, stirring until they are melted into the grits. Taste, adjust seasonings, if necessary, and serve. â€‹
818fdb10-bcab-4acf-bc71-f870cd8d2f44 Enjoy!
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 Gather the ingredients.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 Heat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4. Butter an 8-inch square baking dish.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 In a large skillet, cook sausage and onion, breaking up sausage with a spatula. When sausage is cooked through, drain off excess fat.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 In the prepared baking dish, layer the hash brown potatoes, half of the shredded cheese, browned sausage and onion mixture, then the remaining shredded cheese.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and pepper; pour the egg mixture over cheese.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 45 to 55 minutes, or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 Transfer the casserole to a wire rack and let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 Cut into squares. Serve with salsa, if desired.
dcf246da-a153-4986-80fa-727025526a57 Enjoy!
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Melt the butter in a skillet or saucepan over medium heat. Add the sliced mushrooms and cook until the mushrooms are tender and have released their liquid. Drain them and set aside.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Preheat oven to 375 F / 190 C / Gas 5.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Line the pie crust with foil and fill with weights or dry beans. Bake pie crust for about 10 minutes or until it looks dry and lightly browned. Remove the foil and weights and let the crust cool.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea In a bowl, combine the milk, eggs, butter, flour, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup of the cheddar cheese; whisk until well blended. Set aside.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Sprinkle the remaining 1/4 cup of cheddar cheese over the crust. Layer the drained broccoli, ham, and mushrooms on the cheese layer.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Pour the milk and egg mixture over all, taking care not to overfill. Depending on the size of your pie dish, you might have to discard a little of the egg mixture. Or bake the extra mixture in a buttered ramekin.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Arrange the tomato slices over the top of the quiche filling.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Place the quiche a foil-lined baking sheet or large square of foil under the pie dish to catch any drips.
4612089e-c8c7-4855-a288-571d953a53ea Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.
039e933e-e631-4aa5-9f83-6e3e28cac860 In a small saucepan, combine the bulgur, 1 cup milk, salt, and 1 tablespoon of brown sugar, if desired.
039e933e-e631-4aa5-9f83-6e3e28cac860 Bring to a boil.
039e933e-e631-4aa5-9f83-6e3e28cac860 Reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer, stirring frequently, until thickened and tender, about 12 to 16 minutes.
039e933e-e631-4aa5-9f83-6e3e28cac860 Add a little more milk or water if needed as it nears the end of cooking time.
039e933e-e631-4aa5-9f83-6e3e28cac860 Serve with a little maple syrup and/or brown sugar, or top with berries, raisins, or dried cranberries, as desired.
1f68f7bd-3f28-4014-b0e3-8eea45943a89 Gather the ingredients.
1f68f7bd-3f28-4014-b0e3-8eea45943a89 Peel the peaches, remove the pits, and dice into small cubes. You should have about 3 cups of diced peaches.
1f68f7bd-3f28-4014-b0e3-8eea45943a89 Combine the water, sugar, and cornstarch in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat. Add the diced peaches and simmer for 2 minutes.
1f68f7bd-3f28-4014-b0e3-8eea45943a89 Remove the pan from heat and stir in the vanilla extract and cinnamon, if using.
1f68f7bd-3f28-4014-b0e3-8eea45943a89 Let cool slightly before serving.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Gather the ingredients.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Preheat the oven to 400 F. Grease and flour 12 muffin cups, or line with paper muffin liners.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Cream butter and sugar with an electric hand-held mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add bananas and vanilla, and beat until smooth.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Mix together the flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Stir flour mixture into butter mixture, alternating with the sour milk or buttermilk. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened; gently stir in the chopped pecans or walnuts.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin cups or liners, filling about two-thirds full. Bake for about 15 to 18 minutes, or until tops are lightly browned.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Cool the muffins in the pan on a rack for a few minutes; turn them out onto rack to cool longer.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Serve warm or at room temperature.
e8a62f02-81b6-4e55-8fbe-51514de16a14 Enjoy!
6de855e5-60b7-46f5-931a-35eb56de5653 Heat oven to 400 F. Generously butter a large baking sheet.
6de855e5-60b7-46f5-931a-35eb56de5653 If desired, remove the crusts from bread slices and discard them or reserve them for another use. Set the bread aside.
6de855e5-60b7-46f5-931a-35eb56de5653 In a small bowl, beat the eggs with salt, sugar, milk, and vanilla. Pour into a flat-bottomed dish large enough to accommodate a few slices of the bread. Put bread slices into the dish to soak up some of the egg mixture, a few at a time. Turn with a spatula and let them soak on the other side, but not too long, or they will be too saturated and difficult to turn. Gently remove the soaked bread slices to the buttered baking sheet and continue with the remaining bread slices. Spoon any remaining egg mixture over the slices.
6de855e5-60b7-46f5-931a-35eb56de5653 Place the baking sheet in the preheated oven; bake the pain perdu for 15 to 20 minutes, turning after the first 10 minutes to brown on both sides.
6de855e5-60b7-46f5-931a-35eb56de5653 Serve immediately with melted butter and your favorite honey or syrup.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Gather the ingredients.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 In a shallow bowl, whisk egg and egg white until foamy. Whisk in milk, vanilla, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Have warming drawer heated or heat oven to 200°.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Heat butter in heavy skillet over medium-low heat.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Dip 4 slices of bread in the egg mixture, turning to coat thoroughly. Let excess drip back into the bowl.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Place the coated bread slices on a hot griddle or skillet. Cook, turning until both sides are nicely browned, about 2 minutes each side.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Transfer to a warm plate and keep warm in oven or warming drawer.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Repeat with remaining bread and egg mixture.
1b9897e6-c726-4d3f-9df5-524bdd6e88c0 Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar, if desired. Serve with maple syrup.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Gather the ingredients.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Lightly butter each slice of bread and then cut the slices in half. Arrange the bread slices in a 9 x13 x 2-inch baking pan.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 In a large skillet or saute pan, brown the sausage. Use a spatula or spoon to break it up. Drain and pat with paper towels. Sprinkle the sausage over the bread. Top the sausage with the shredded cheese.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 In a mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, salt, dry mustard, and the half and half or milk until well blended. Pour egg mixture over bread, sausage, and cheese.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Cover the pan with foil and refrigerate overnight.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Remove the casserole from the refrigerator and let it stand at room temperature for about 20 minutes.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Remove the foil from pan and bake the casserole for 45 minutes, or until it is bubbly around the edges and lightly browned on top. It might take a bit longer if it's still quite cold. A butter knife inserted into the center of the should come out clean when it's done.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Remove the breakfast casserole to a rack and let it stand for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
498ab7ef-6373-4970-960f-204aad86d9e9 Serve and enjoy!
bbf8610e-d8f9-4b56-bdc3-155e2c664f76 Gather the ingredients.
bbf8610e-d8f9-4b56-bdc3-155e2c664f76 In a large, heavy skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove the bacon to paper towels to drain. In the bacon drippings, cook the onion and potatoes until browned, about 5 minutes. Pour the beaten eggs into the skillet.
bbf8610e-d8f9-4b56-bdc3-155e2c664f76 Cook, stirring gently until the eggs are set and cooked through. Be sure to reduce the heat and keep stirring so the egg mixture doesn't stick or burn on the bottom of the pan. Season with salt and pepper.
bbf8610e-d8f9-4b56-bdc3-155e2c664f76 Crumble the bacon and sprinkle it and the shredded cheese onto the cooked eggs. Let it stand a minute or two, just until the cheese melts.
bbf8610e-d8f9-4b56-bdc3-155e2c664f76 Serve warm and enjoy. Refrigerate any leftovers.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Adjust oven rack to middle position and preheat oven to 350 F.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Line the cups of a muffin tin with 12 paper liners. Set aside.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, and salt in a mixing bowl. Whisk or stir to blend well.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Using metal blade in food processor, process cream cheese, lemon juice, and vanilla until smooth.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Add eggs and process 15 seconds. Scrape down the sides of the food processor bowl with a spatula.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 With processor running, pour hot melted butter down the food chute gradually, but within 10 seconds. Process 10 seconds longer
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Add milk and process for 5 seconds.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Add dry ingredients to container and mix with 4 to 6 quick pulses.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Fold the blueberries into the batter with a spatula.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Spoon an equal amount of batter into each muffin cup, filling each about 2/3 to 3/4 full.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
ba4421bb-d776-466f-86c1-9c4deb010663 Cool on rack 15 minutes.
61d42f6e-a798-436c-bcac-615343949c0d Gather the ingredients.
61d42f6e-a798-436c-bcac-615343949c0d Preheat oven to 400 F.
61d42f6e-a798-436c-bcac-615343949c0d Mix milk and egg together in a mixing bowl; add extract.
61d42f6e-a798-436c-bcac-615343949c0d Sift together the dry ingredients, including sugar. Add to milk and egg mixture. Mix until well moistened.
61d42f6e-a798-436c-bcac-615343949c0d Fold in walnuts and dates, then the melted butter, mixing just enough to blend.
61d42f6e-a798-436c-bcac-615343949c0d Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 18 minutes, or until date muffins are nicely browned.
61d42f6e-a798-436c-bcac-615343949c0d Serve and enjoy!
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 Gather the ingredients.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 Peel the potatoes and shred using the large shredding holes on a box grater or the shredding disk of a food processor.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 Place the potatoes in a strainer and rinse with abundant cold water to release some starch. Shake to remove excess water and transfer the potatoes to a clean kitchen towel. Squeeze well, many times, to remove excess moisture.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 In a medium-size bowl, combine the potatoes with the finely chopped onion, salt, and pepper.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 In a large non-stick pan, heat the butter and oil using medium heat.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 When the butter and oil are hot, add the potato and onion mixture. Using a spatula, press them down firmly, but do not stir the potatoes. You want to create a crunchy layer at the bottom.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 When the bottom is golden brown, turn the potatoes carefully and brown the other side: Using silicon gloves or oven mittens, place a round plate on top of the pan, turn the pan upside down so the potatoes are on the plate, and then slide the potatoes back into the pan. Alternatively, you can cut the potatoes in four quarters and turn them upside-down in sections.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 Sprinkle extra salt and pepper to taste. Once the potatoes are crunchy and gold on both sides, transfer to a plate to serve or keep warm in a 200 F oven until it's time to use.
c24f0741-d2b9-4f9f-aa5d-de5a499158a1 Serve with the breakfast foods of your liking and enjoy!
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Gather the ingredients.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Thaw potatoes between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Heat the oven to 425 F/220 C/Gas 7.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Press potatoes into bottom and up sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate; drizzle the melted butter over potatoes.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Bake for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned; cool on a rack for 10 minutes.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Reduce the oven temperature to 350 F/177 C/Gas 4.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Combine ham, cheese, and bell pepper; spoon into potato shell.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, and pepper, blending well; pour egg mixture over ham mixture.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set; let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
fdee963f-7bf3-48b4-967f-2f81e7a296dd Enjoy!
6143fadb-d365-462e-b2b9-ebbf4b92db95 Combine all of the fruits together in your slow cooker along with the water, sugar, vanilla, lemon zest, and â€‹lemon juice. Stir to blend.
6143fadb-d365-462e-b2b9-ebbf4b92db95 Cover and cook on low until the fruit is tender, about 6 to 8 hours.
6143fadb-d365-462e-b2b9-ebbf4b92db95 Serve warm or at room temperature.
586b99df-1477-45c6-829b-73147542cf9e Gather the ingredients.
586b99df-1477-45c6-829b-73147542cf9e Grease a 2-quart baking dish or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
586b99df-1477-45c6-829b-73147542cf9e Whisk together the eggs, milk, and seasoning in a 9- by13-inch baking dish.
586b99df-1477-45c6-829b-73147542cf9e Arrange bread pieces in the baking dish; top with the sliced sausage then cheese.
586b99df-1477-45c6-829b-73147542cf9e Cover and refrigerate overnight or let stand for 15 minutes and bake. If you refrigerate overnight, give the casserole about 20 to 30 minutes to come to room temperature before baking.
586b99df-1477-45c6-829b-73147542cf9e Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until firm and lightly browned around the edges.
10d26533-f700-4efd-a7e5-9546eeb8ca4a Gather the ingredients.
10d26533-f700-4efd-a7e5-9546eeb8ca4a Beat eggs until fluffy.
10d26533-f700-4efd-a7e5-9546eeb8ca4a Whisk in 1/3 cup milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce, and pepper.
10d26533-f700-4efd-a7e5-9546eeb8ca4a Heat butter in a heavy 10-inch skillet over low heat; pour in egg mixture.
10d26533-f700-4efd-a7e5-9546eeb8ca4a Cook slowly, lifting at the edge to allow uncooked egg to run underneath. When the omelet is almost cooked but still shiny, cover and continue cooking until the surface dries, about 2 minutes.â€‹
10d26533-f700-4efd-a7e5-9546eeb8ca4a Top with cheese and chopped green onion; fold in half.
334080b7-7f23-4f60-ab60-0cc3c7f1a531 In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt, and pepper together until well blended.
334080b7-7f23-4f60-ab60-0cc3c7f1a531 Melt butter in a skillet over medium-low heat until butter is foamy; pour in egg mixture. As mixture begins to set on bottom and sides of skillet, lift and fold over with a spatula.
334080b7-7f23-4f60-ab60-0cc3c7f1a531 Cook until eggs are almost set; fold in tomato and green onion.
334080b7-7f23-4f60-ab60-0cc3c7f1a531 Heat through; serve immediately.
308a865e-792f-41ad-88c0-133088800cac Butter the inside of the crockery insert of the slow cooker.
308a865e-792f-41ad-88c0-133088800cac Add the cracked wheat, oats, coconut, pearl barley, brown rice, and salt to the crock pot.
308a865e-792f-41ad-88c0-133088800cac Add the water and stir to blend.
308a865e-792f-41ad-88c0-133088800cac Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Gather the ingredients.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Heat the oven to 350 F / 180 C / Gas 4.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Put 1 teaspoon of melted butter in each of four individual baking dishes or ramekins. Brush the butter over the bottoms and sides of the dishes.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Break 2 eggs into each dish.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Add 2 tablespoons of heavy cream to each dish and then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Bake in the preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of shredded cheese over each egg just a minute or two beforeâ€‹ the dish is done.
b77e7ee1-656b-42cc-853d-506ece2b8f40 Serve and enjoy!
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Gather the ingredients.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Combine chili sauce, grape jelly, and mustard in the crockpot and stir well. Cook covered on HIGH while preparing the meatballs.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil. Grease or spray with cooking oil.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 In a large bowl, combine the ground beef with the beaten egg, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, and salt. Mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon or your hands, if needed.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Shape into about 2 or 3 dozen (half-ounce) meatballs or 16 to 18 (one ounce) meatballs. Arrange the meatballs in the prepared baking pan and bake for 12 to 18 minutes, or until cooked through. Alternatively, place a cooling rack in the pan and bake the meatballs on the rack.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Once cooked, discard any liquid from the baking pan and transfer the meatballs to the crockpot. Stir to coat, cover, and cook on LOW for 3 to 4 hours.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Stir well before serving.
bae1a6ec-ab6c-4aa6-bedb-57fbd1e7b3e4 Enjoy!
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Gather the ingredients.
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Cook bacon gently until partially cooked but not crisp and still flexible.
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Rinse scallops under running cold water, pat dry with paper towels. If you notice any tag-like pieces on the side of the scallops, this is a tough muscle and should be removed. Just pinch it with your fingers to remove.
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Cut each bacon slice crosswise in half; wrap each half around a scallop and secure with a toothpick.
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Sprinkle scallops lightly with seasoned pepper. Preheat broiler.
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Place scallops on a rack in broiling pan.
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes, or until scallops turn opaque throughout, using tongs to turn scallops frequently so the bacon browns evenly on all sides.
977704f6-4f60-454e-ab05-43fab39637a3 Serve as an appetizer or an entrée.
94988107-2a09-4724-b075-6068175d6ce9 Cut tips off of chicken wings with kitchen shears. Cut the wings at the joint and put them in a bowl. Cover with cold water, 1 tablespoon of white vinegar, and 2 tablespoons of salt. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
94988107-2a09-4724-b075-6068175d6ce9 Heat oven to 425 F.
94988107-2a09-4724-b075-6068175d6ce9 Line a large baking pan or roasting pan with foil. Place a cooling rack in the pan. Discard the brine and arrange the wings on the rack. Bake for 20 minutes. Turn wings over and bake for 20 minutes longer.
94988107-2a09-4724-b075-6068175d6ce9 Meanwhile, heat the butter, hot sauce, Tabasco, 2 tablespoons white vinegar, and garlic powder in a small saucepan until butter is melted and the mixture is hot.
94988107-2a09-4724-b075-6068175d6ce9 In a bowl, toss the hot baked wings with the butter and hot sauce mixture. Arrange on a platter with dip and celery sticks, if desired.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Gather the ingredients.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 In a small saucepan over low heat, melt the butter. Set aside 1/4 cup of the melted butter for brushing the rolls.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Add the mustard, poppy seeds, onion (if using), and Worcestershire sauce to the remaining butter in the saucepan. If using onions, cook over low heat until the onions are translucent and tender.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Without separating the pull-apart rolls, halve the block of rolls horizontally. Spread both cut-sides evenly with the butter mixture.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Arrange the ham evenly over the bottom half of the rolls and then evenly lay or sprinkle the cheese over the ham. Cover the sandwiches with the top half of the rolls.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Brush the top of the bread rolls with the reserved melted butter and sprinkle with additional poppy seeds.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Lightly spray a piece of foil, large enough to wrap the rolls, with nonstick cooking spray. Tightly wrap the rolls in the foil and refrigerate until 30 minutes before serving time.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Heat the oven to 375 F.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Place the foil-wrapped rolls on a baking sheet.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Transfer to the oven and bake until the rolls are thoroughly heated and the cheese has melted, about 15 minutes.
bd5f6e2b-8607-4f8a-ba9b-689e8ee3e6e2 Serve and enjoy!
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Gather the ingredients.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas Mark 4). Lightly grease a 12-cup muffin pan or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion to the pan and sauté until lightly browned and tender.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Add the finely minced garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 minute longer.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 In a bowl, combine the ground beef with the breadcrumbs, 1/2 cup of the ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, beaten egg, thyme, oregano, ground black pepper, and salt.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Add the sautéed vegetables, mixing until well blended.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Pack the meat mixture into the prepared muffin cups.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Bake the meatloaf muffins for 20 minutes.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Top each meatloaf muffin with a few teaspoons of the remaining ketchup. Return to the oven and bake for about 5 to 10 minutes longer.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 The meatloaf muffins should register at least 160 F on an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of one.
d8e0b8a4-a44c-4ce6-a96f-bfdaf6459a91 Serve and enjoy.
e0d66d0c-b9d5-46fa-9856-f1b80d5136d3 Gather the ingredients.
e0d66d0c-b9d5-46fa-9856-f1b80d5136d3 Line a large baking sheet or shallow baking pan with foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray or baking spray. Preheat the oven to 425 F.
e0d66d0c-b9d5-46fa-9856-f1b80d5136d3 Combine the Sriracha sauce, honey, soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic, and ginger in a bowl.
e0d66d0c-b9d5-46fa-9856-f1b80d5136d3 Pour the panko crumbs in a wide, shallow bowl.
e0d66d0c-b9d5-46fa-9856-f1b80d5136d3 Dip the chicken strips or tenders in the sriracha sauce mixture to coat thoroughly, then roll in the panko crumbs. Arrange the chicken fingers in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet.
e0d66d0c-b9d5-46fa-9856-f1b80d5136d3 Bake for 20 minutes, or until cooked through and lightly browned. The internal temperature (check the center of the thickest piece) should be at least 165 F. on a food thermometer.
e0d66d0c-b9d5-46fa-9856-f1b80d5136d3 Serve and enjoy!
a703fc6b-52e9-4d47-9ce8-fe2835128ca7 Gather the ingredients.
a703fc6b-52e9-4d47-9ce8-fe2835128ca7 Put the chopped onion and garlic in a strainer. Pour boiling water over them, discarding the water. Allow the chopped onion and garlic to fully cool and drain.
a703fc6b-52e9-4d47-9ce8-fe2835128ca7 Combine drained onions and garlic with chopped tomatoes, peppers, cilantro, and lime juice. Add salt and black pepper.
a703fc6b-52e9-4d47-9ce8-fe2835128ca7 Refrigerate for at least 2 hours to blend the flavors.
a703fc6b-52e9-4d47-9ce8-fe2835128ca7 The pico de gallo will keep for up to three days in the fridge. Serve as a dip or a condiment with Mexican-style dishes and enjoy.
16aaf588-96a7-497b-b0df-23a5678b0f05 Gather the ingredients.
16aaf588-96a7-497b-b0df-23a5678b0f05 Preheat oven to 425 F. Line a baking sheet with nonstick foil or parchment paper.
16aaf588-96a7-497b-b0df-23a5678b0f05 Brush cut sides of French bread with melted butter. Sprinkle lightly with onion powder and garlic powder. Top with blue cheese or Gorgonzola cheese, tomatoes, chives or green onions, mozzarella, and parsley.
16aaf588-96a7-497b-b0df-23a5678b0f05 Bake about 10 to 15 minutes, until bread is crusty on the outside and the top is melted and just beginning to turn golden.
16aaf588-96a7-497b-b0df-23a5678b0f05 Serve as is for an appetizer or serve it as an accompaniment for a classic spaghetti dinner or any other pasta dish like linguine with clam sauce.
16aaf588-96a7-497b-b0df-23a5678b0f05 Enjoy!
0bca539e-e545-4477-8b13-590b623b58dc Gather the ingredients.
0bca539e-e545-4477-8b13-590b623b58dc In a bowl, combine the mayonnaise, Creole mustard, Creole seasoning, pepper, parsley, green onion, and bell pepper; set aside. If the Creole seasoning does not contain salt, add a dash of salt, or to taste.
0bca539e-e545-4477-8b13-590b623b58dc Drain the crabmeat and gently squeeze it to get as much of the liquid out as possible.
0bca539e-e545-4477-8b13-590b623b58dc Put the crabmeat in a medium bowl. With a spatula or wooden spoon, fold in mayonnaise mixture and 1 cup of the bread crumbs, just until blended. Shape into 8 crab cakes, about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
0bca539e-e545-4477-8b13-590b623b58dc I use a biscuit or cookie cutter with an open top to shape the cakes and press the ingredients down to make them hold together. Press gently into reserved crumbs. Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
0bca539e-e545-4477-8b13-590b623b58dc Heat the butter and oil over medium heat. When the butter stops foaming, fry crab cakes for about 5 minutes on each side, carefully turning only once. Serve with lemon wedges and Remoulade or other sauce.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Heat the oven to 350 F.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Wash and trim the end of stems from mushrooms. Pop remaining stem out. Chop stems finely and set them aside.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 In a medium saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter. Once melted, brush the melted butter over mushroom caps.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Spray a shallow baking dish (about 8-inch square, or one which will fit mushrooms in one layer) with nonstick cooking spray, line with parchment paper, or grease the pan with butter.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Melt the remaining butter in the saucepan over medium heat. When the butter is hot add the reserved chopped stems, minced green onions, and red bell pepper. Cook for 3 to 5 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Combine the onion and butter mixture with the bread crumbs, crabmeat, Cajun seasoning, and pepper. Taste and add salt, as needed.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Fill the mushrooms, mounding the stuffing in each cap.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Sprinkle each filled mushroom cap with a little Parmesan cheese, if desired.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until the crab stuffing is hot and mushroom caps are tender.
f039247f-964c-459a-8f15-0bdbf16009c0 Serve them hot. If you need to keep them warm for a lengthy serving, use a warming tray, chafing dish, or slow cooker.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 Gather the ingredients.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 Cook the spinach following the package directions. Drain it in a colander, pressing with the help of a bowl or big cooking spoon to squeeze out as much of the liquid as possible.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 In a large bowl, combine the warm spinach with the softened butter. Add the stuffing crumbs, Parmesan cheese, and minced onions. Mix well and add salt and pepper to taste, plus the nutmeg. Be mindful that stuffing crumbs already have salt in them so go light at first and check the seasoning again right before baking.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 In a small bowl, whisk the eggs lightly and add them to the spinach mixture. Combine thoroughly and chill the mixture for about 30 minutes, covered.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 While the mixture chills, line a large rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper or spray it with nonstick cooking or baking spray.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 If using, put the fine dry breadcrumbs in a plate or bowl.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 Once the mixture is cool, use a rounded teaspoon or small cookie scoop and shape the spinach mixture into small balls. If the mixture is sticking to your hands, dampen them with cold water as you work.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 Roll each ball in the bread crumbs until it's lightly coated and place it on the baking sheet, leaving about 1/2-inch of space in between.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until they feel firm to the touch.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 If you're serving them as an appetizer, keep them warm on a warming tray, or in a buffet server, chafing dish, or slow cooker.
8fa96f4d-d24a-47ff-8b0b-fc06b513edc1 Enjoy!
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Gather the ingredients.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Combine the turkey, mashed potatoes, parsley, and black pepper.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Add green onions and cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Add the flour and stir until well blended.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Stir in chicken broth and milk. Continue cooking, stirring, for 2 minutes. Add salt, to taste.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Combine with the turkey mixture, blending well. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, about 1 to 2 hours.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Put the 1/2 cup of flour on a plate. Beat eggs in a bowl with 1 tablespoon of water. Put the finely ground bread crumbs in another bowl.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Shape croquette mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls (a little smaller if you're making appetizers).
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Roll gently in the flour to coat, then in the egg until coated. Coat with the breadcrumbs. Place on a waxed paper or foil-lined cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining turkey mixture and crumbs.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Let the croquettes stand for about 30 to 45 minutes to dry a bit.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Heat oil to about 360 F. Fry the croquettes in small batches for about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, depending on size, or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
c736f5a1-30fa-4224-8df2-0fab2e3d9c35 Serve with hot turkey gravy and cranberry sauce as part of a post-holiday meal or as appetizers for guests.
a2bd6c4b-c3f1-4bad-937d-c752d021f212 In a medium bowl, combine the cream cheese, sour cream, chilies, onion, red bell pepper, and cheddar cheese. Mix thoroughly.
a2bd6c4b-c3f1-4bad-937d-c752d021f212 Spread onto tortillas and roll up. Cover tightly and chill for 2 hours or overnight. When ready to serve, cut each roll into 1/2-inch slices. Serve with a mild or medium salsa or a Picante sauce.
d6b138bb-1aa0-4bbf-9025-6d5c39279bd1 Gather the ingredients.
d6b138bb-1aa0-4bbf-9025-6d5c39279bd1 Scoop out the seeds. Discard the big chunks of stringy pulp and put the seeds in a colander.
d6b138bb-1aa0-4bbf-9025-6d5c39279bd1 Rinse the pumpkin seeds under cold running water. Swish them around to remove any pieces of pulp clinging to the seeds. Drain.
d6b138bb-1aa0-4bbf-9025-6d5c39279bd1 Spread the seeds out onto a kitchen towel to dry. Don't use paper towels to dry the seeds; they will stick.
d6b138bb-1aa0-4bbf-9025-6d5c39279bd1 Preheat the oven to 300 F. Line a baking sheet with foil.
d6b138bb-1aa0-4bbf-9025-6d5c39279bd1 Spread the seeds out on the foil-lined baking sheet. Sprinkle the pumpkin seeds with the salt and drizzle with vegetable oil. Toss to coat the seeds thoroughly. Bake the pumpkin seeds in the preheated oven for about 35 to 45 minutes, stirring and turning once or twice. They should be lightly browned and crisp.
d6b138bb-1aa0-4bbf-9025-6d5c39279bd1 Serve the pumpkin seeds in snack dishes and enjoy!
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Gather the ingredients.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Preheat the oven to 325 F. Butter a shallow baking dish large enough to hold the mushroom caps in a single layer.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Carefully clean the mushrooms with a wet paper towel, remove the stems, leaving the caps whole.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Finely chop the mushroom stems.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Sauté the mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons of melted butter until tender. Transfer to a plate and set aside.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Sauté the chopped stems, green pepper, and chopped onion in the remaining 5 tablespoons of butter until the onions are translucent.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Add the breadcrumbs, salt, pepper, and cayenne pepper to the onion and pepper mixture. Stir to blend the ingredients thoroughly and remove from heat.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Fill each mushroom cap with the breadcrumb mixture and then sprinkle each with a small amount of Parmesan cheese.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Arrange the stuffed mushroom caps in the prepared baking dish.
63d359e1-48ba-461c-a2c4-87286670580a Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in the preheated oven, or until the filling has browned and the cheese is melted and crunchy.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Gather the ingredients.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Heat oven to 350 F.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Arrange the tortilla chips in one layer on parchment-lined baking sheets.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Gently spread some bean dip on each large chip.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Place a jalapeno ring or two on the bean dip. Drizzle a little salsa or chili sauce over the top and place a quarter-slice of cheese on each.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Bake in the heated oven until cheese melts, about 10 to 15 minutes.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Top each appetizer with a small dollop of guacamole or sour cream and add another jalapeno ring for garnish, if desired.
fc848215-8813-4cfc-beed-3b37dd1f9cdf Serve immediately and enjoy! Note that these do not store well as they will become soggy. You might consider baking these in batches so you can serve your family and guests hot, tasty appetizers, instead of cold, soggy ones.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Gather the ingredients.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Preheat the oven to 400 F. Scrub the potatoes and prick several times with a skewer or fork tines.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Bake the potatoes for about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until the potatoes are fork-tender.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 When the potatoes are cool enough to handle, cut them in half lengthwise. Scoop out much of the potato from each half, leaving about 1/4 to 1/2 inch of potato in the shell. Save the potato for another use, such as baked potato soup or mashed potatoes.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Cut the halves in half again lengthwise. Brush all over with olive oil or vegetable oil, then sprinkle the tops with salt and pepper.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Arrange on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes, until slightly crisp around the edges.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Remove the potato skins from the oven and mound about 1 tablespoon of shredded cheese on each piece; sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Return the potato skins to the oven and bake for another 7 to 10 minutes, or until the cheese has melted.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Top with thinly sliced green onion.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 If desired, serve with small bowls of salsa, guacamole, and sour cream.
cf37b400-a767-4010-b6f4-fa5dfc5396d6 Serve and enjoy!
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Heat oil up to about 350 F in the deep fryer, or use a deep heavy skillet or Dutch oven with enough oil to cover several wings lying flat.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Whisk together eggs and water. Set aside.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Mix together the barbecue sauce and honey. Make the sauce as sweet as you like.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Put the flour into a food storage bag, then shake the wings in it to lightly coat.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Roll the wings in the egg wash, then toss them back into the bag. You want a fairly heavy coating of flour so the barbeque sauce has something to hang onto. You may want to dip and shake 2 to 3 times, using more flour and eggs as needed.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Fry the wings in batches until they're golden brown and crispy. You'll be baking them later, so don't worry about the wings being thoroughly cooked. Drain chicken wings on paper towels.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Preheat oven to 325 F.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Once the chicken pieces are browned and drained, dip each piece into the barbeque sauce and honey mixture and place onto cookie sheets. Make sure the pieces don't touch each other.
f8b3709b-3231-453e-ba54-a834cc3e1dfa Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until they no longer look shiny and the chicken tests done (juices run clear when poked with a knife). Baking dries the coating out a bit and sets the coating so it doesn't fall off.
1dad4c79-a188-4f46-8e26-a8d9e238cc84 In large mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs with minced onion, salt, pepper, and 1/2 cup water. Add ground beef and egg. Shape beef mixture into 16 meatballs.
1dad4c79-a188-4f46-8e26-a8d9e238cc84 Brown the meatballs slowly in a large skillet over medium-low heat.
1dad4c79-a188-4f46-8e26-a8d9e238cc84 When the meatballs are browned and cooked through, remove from the skillet and set aside. Cook celery and pepper strips in skillet for about 5 minutes. Add remaining water, vinegar, brown sugar, and soy sauce. Mix cornstarch with a little cold water then add to skillet; stir well and cook for about 4 minutes. Add meatballs and pineapple. Cook until heated through.
1dad4c79-a188-4f46-8e26-a8d9e238cc84 Serve with hot cooked rice or noodles, along with steamed broccoli or green beans.
95c486ff-689e-492b-ac54-0a6a09f66802 Wash and trim the end of stems from mushrooms. Pop the remaining stem out. Chop stems and set aside. Melt 2 tablespoons butter; brush over mushrooms. Spray a shallow baking dish (about 8-inch square, or one which will fit mushrooms in one layer) with butter-flavored spray or grease with butter.
95c486ff-689e-492b-ac54-0a6a09f66802 Heat remaining 2 tablespoons of butter in a skillet. Chop green onions; combine with reserved chopped mushroom stems, ham, and garlic. Add to skillet along with the spinach; sauté until tender. Add bread crumbs, salt, and pepper to vegetable mixture; stir well. Add a little cream to moisten more if necessary.
95c486ff-689e-492b-ac54-0a6a09f66802 Fill each mushroom cap with a little of the stuffing, mounding the filling. Top each filled mushroom cap with some of the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
95c486ff-689e-492b-ac54-0a6a09f66802 Bake at 350 F for about 20 minutes, until â€‹the cheese is melted and mushroom caps are tender.
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 Gather the ingredients.
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, cornflake crumbs, parsley, eggs, ketchup, onion, soy sauce, garlic powder, and pepper. Mix until just combined, to avoid making the meatballs tough.
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 Form into small balls, from 1/2 to 3/4-inch in diameter.
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 Place the meatballs in a casserole dish or baking pan. Pre heat oven to 325 F.
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar, and lemon juice. Cook over medium heat while stirring until smooth.
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 Pour the hot sauce over meatballs in casserole. If desired, add one 8-ounce can of pineapple chunks (drained).
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in the pre heated oven, depending on the size of the meatballs.
c7b2a7dd-5e1c-4247-9768-1edf9c75a760 Transfer to the slow cooker and keep on low for serving.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Gather the ingredients.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Heat the oven to 450 F.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems and set aside.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Put the sausage in a skillet over medium heat. Cook the sausage, stirring and breaking up until it is fully cooked. Remove the sausage to a bowl, leaving 1 or 2 tablespoons of drippings in the skillet.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Cook the mushroom stems in the drippings for 5 to 10 minutes, until tender and browned. Remove the pan from the heat.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Stir the cooked mushroom pieces into the bowl with the sausage.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Add the bread crumbs and cheese; blend thoroughly.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Fill mushroom caps with the sausage mixture.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Bake in the preheated oven for about 15 minutes.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 If desired, top the stuffed mushrooms with more mozzarella cheese and return to the oven just until the cheese has melted.
8dcffff5-cece-42e0-b590-1d844c9966a4 Serve and enjoy!
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Heat the oven to 350 F.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Lay a large sheet of heavy duty foil in a roasting pan. Place the pork roast on foil. Rub pork all over with garlic and seasonings. Arrange the medium onion slices over the top. Wrap the foil around the pork roast.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Bake the pork in the preheated oven for about 4 to 5 hours, or until the pork is very tender and falling apart. When the meat is cool enough to handle, remove the bones and begin to shred the meat with forks or chop, discarding as much of the excess fat as possible.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Sauté the chopped onions in oil until tender. Put the shredded pork in a slow cooker. Blend in the 1 cup barbecue sauce and vinegar, along with the sautéed onion. Heat the pork on LOW setting for about 2 hours, or until hot and flavorful. Or, simmer, covered, over low heat for about 30 minutes to 1 hour.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 While the pork is in the slow cooker, make the buns.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 In a bowl or large cup, whisk together the milk and yeast. Let the mixture stand at room temperature until the yeast has dissolved. Place the milk and yeast mixture, melted butter and beaten egg, flour, sugar, and 1 teaspoon of salt in the bread machine in the order suggested by your bread machine manufacturer. Run on dough cycle. Remove finished dough to a lightly floured surface. Roll half of the dough to about 1/4-inch thickness or slightly more. Cut out with a 1 1/2-inch cutter. Or make your sandwiches slider-size using a 2-inch cutter.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Place the dough rounds on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Cover with a kitchen towel and let them rise for about 30 minutes.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Heat the oven to 350 F.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Bake for 15 to 18 minutes, or until browned. Brush tops with a little butter while they're hot. Let the buns cool completely on a rack.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Split the cooled buns.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Fill each small split bun with a little of the shredded pork, then add a small spoonful of slaw. Or serve slaw on the side with a small spoon. Replace the top of the bun and secure with a toothpick, if desired.
9e324b7a-814d-4fc7-be79-4d174bbb2380 Pass the mini pulled pork sandwiches on a tray with a small bowl of barbecue sauce and more slaw, if desired.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Gather the ingredients.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Rinse the scallops, remove the tough abductor muscle (see the tips) if not already removed, and dry thoroughly with paper towels.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Cut large scallops in half horizontally, if desired. Set aside.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Put the 1 tablespoon of butter and the olive oil in a skillet.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Heat over medium heat until hot and butter is foamy or about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Add the scallops and sear for about 2 to 4 minutes on each side or until browned on both sides and somewhat firm but with a little give when lightly pressed with a finger.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Cook the scallops in batches, if necessary to keep them in a single layer.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Put the scallops on a warm plate and keep warm.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Add 1 tablespoon of butter to the pan, along with the finely chopped shallots or onion.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Cook, stirring until the onion is translucent and softened.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Add the wine and simmer for about 1 to 2 minutes or until reduced by about one-half.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Add the lemon zest along with the chopped fresh chives and parsley.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Reduce heat to low.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Add the remaining 3 tablespoons of butter and whisk until melted.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Return the scallops to the skillet and cook, gently turning, until warmed through.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Sprinkle the scallops with salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Serve drizzled with the sauce mixture, along with lemon wedges.
4ad18412-dc54-4b04-99f8-d6c83582afe7 Enjoy!
c7b17a8a-a601-497b-ad3c-4542d43f2589 Gather the ingredients.
c7b17a8a-a601-497b-ad3c-4542d43f2589 Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4. Butter a 1-quart casserole dish.
c7b17a8a-a601-497b-ad3c-4542d43f2589 In a medium bowl, lightly whisk the egg. Add the crabmeat, mayonnaise, mustard, Old Bay, and capers, if using. Stir to blend thoroughly.
c7b17a8a-a601-497b-ad3c-4542d43f2589 Spoon the crabmeat mixture into the prepared casserole dish and then top it with the Ritz cracker crumbs.
c7b17a8a-a601-497b-ad3c-4542d43f2589 Bake in the preheated oven for about 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and lightly browned.
c7b17a8a-a601-497b-ad3c-4542d43f2589 Serve and enjoy!
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Gather the ingredients.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Trim larger pieces of beef from bones and cut into 1-inch pieces.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Heat the oven to 400 F.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Put the bones (i.e. neck bones, shanks, ribs, etc.) and beef pieces in a large roasting pan with the onions, carrots, and celery. Toss with the olive oil.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Roast for 45 minutes, turning a few times so the beef browns evenly.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Remove the beef and vegetables to a stockpot and set aside.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Pour off any excess grease and place the roasting pan over medium heat. Add the 1 tablespoon of tomato paste and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Add 2 cups of water and bring to a simmer.
