24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Add the tomato paste mixture to the stockpot, along with the remaining 3 quarts of water. If the water doesn't quite cover the bones, add a little more water.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Add the bay leaf, parsley sprigs, peppercorns, and thyme.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Put the stockpot over medium-high heat and bring to a boil. Skim off any foamy scum from the top.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Then reduce heat to the lowest setting and simmer for 3 to 4 hours. The stock should be flavorful and reduced slightly. If you want a richer, more concentrated flavor, cook longer to reduce more.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Strain through a cheesecloth-lined strainer into a large bowl. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Remove the solid fat from the surface.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Ladle into 1-, 2-, or 4-cup freezer containers or jars, leaving about an inch of headspace.
24402de8-0103-4e19-a730-e82a618dd5e6 Refrigerate and use within 4 days or freeze for up to 3 months.
cfdfbc75-88c1-412b-86e2-551b4bbe0abf Heat the oil in a deep, heavy saucepan to about 360 F, or until a cube of bread browns in about 30 seconds.
cfdfbc75-88c1-412b-86e2-551b4bbe0abf Shape the cold macaroni and cheese into small balls.
cfdfbc75-88c1-412b-86e2-551b4bbe0abf In a shallow bowl, beat the eggs lightly with 2 tablespoons of milk.
cfdfbc75-88c1-412b-86e2-551b4bbe0abf Dip the mac and cheese balls in bread crumbs, then into the beaten eggs, then in crumbs again.
cfdfbc75-88c1-412b-86e2-551b4bbe0abf Drop carefully into hot fat and cook, turning, until golden brown, about 1 to 2 minutes.
cfdfbc75-88c1-412b-86e2-551b4bbe0abf Remove to paper towels to drain; keep warm while making subsequent batches.
fba4e348-2107-4837-8e4c-5484cdbe452d Wrap a piece of bacon around each piece of hot dog and secure it with a toothpick.
fba4e348-2107-4837-8e4c-5484cdbe452d Put one layer of bacon-wrapped hot dogs in the bottom of your slow cooker insert and add a generous sprinkling of brown sugar. Repeat with the remaining hot dogs and brown sugar.
fba4e348-2107-4837-8e4c-5484cdbe452d Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.
71a1b926-acb2-4a62-826b-64900c60f2b6 Gather ingredients.
71a1b926-acb2-4a62-826b-64900c60f2b6 Place the cream cheese and sour cream in a bowl mix with an electric mixer on low until well blended. Add the green onions, chiles, and cheddar cheese. Beat just until blended. Taste and add salt and ground black pepper, as needed.
71a1b926-acb2-4a62-826b-64900c60f2b6 Spread mixture thinly and evenly over tortillas to within about 1/4-inch of the edges.
71a1b926-acb2-4a62-826b-64900c60f2b6 Roll each filled tortilla up jelly-roll fashion, wrap each tortilla in plastic wrap, and refrigerate.
71a1b926-acb2-4a62-826b-64900c60f2b6 Slice, serve, and enjoy!
71a1b926-acb2-4a62-826b-64900c60f2b6 Serve with your favorite salsa or a few different dips. Ranch dressing, guacamole, and sour cream are all good choices.
9447782d-60d9-4343-b3a9-597318c804e9 Combine sauce ingredients in slow cooker; cover and cook on high while preparing meatballs.
9447782d-60d9-4343-b3a9-597318c804e9 Combine meatball ingredients and mix until well blended.
9447782d-60d9-4343-b3a9-597318c804e9 Shape into 1 to 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
9447782d-60d9-4343-b3a9-597318c804e9 Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add meatballs; brown on all sides. You might have to do this in batches.
9447782d-60d9-4343-b3a9-597318c804e9 Place browned meatballs in a 325 F oven and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until cooked through (if the skillet isn't ovenproof, transfer to a baking dish). Ground beef should be cooked to at least 160 F.
9447782d-60d9-4343-b3a9-597318c804e9 Transfer meatballs to slow cooker with a slotted spoon. Cover and reduce to low for 2 to 4 hours.
9447782d-60d9-4343-b3a9-597318c804e9 Serve hot as an appetizer or over rice for a main dish.
79e6dbbf-93ca-46b1-8103-e361318d057a Cut 6 of the hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
79e6dbbf-93ca-46b1-8103-e361318d057a Scoop the cooked yolks out of egg halves. Press yolks and remaining whole hard-cooked egg through a sieve into a small bowl. Stir in 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise and the mustard; season to taste with salt and pepper. Add more mayonnaise, as needed.
79e6dbbf-93ca-46b1-8103-e361318d057a Mound the yolk filling in the egg white halves.
79e6dbbf-93ca-46b1-8103-e361318d057a Sprinkle the tops with a little sweet paprika, if desired.
79e6dbbf-93ca-46b1-8103-e361318d057a Garnish with sliced olives, sliced grape or cherry tomatoes, finely chopped the red onion, or snipped fresh chives.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Rinse and pick over crab meat, discarding any pieces of shell or cartilage. Try to leave lumps as large as possible.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over low heat; slowly saute finely diced onion, celery, red pepper, and garlic until tender.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Whisk egg in a bowl; add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, and Creole seasoning.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Combine with sauteed vegetables and soft bread crumbs, mixing well.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Add the crab meat and form into loose patties; place on a waxed paper-lined plate.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Refrigerate for about 1 hour, or until firm.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Heat remaining 4 tablespoons butter in large skillet over medium-low heat.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Gently place crab cakes in skillet and cook for about 5 minutes. Turn and cook for 4 to 5 minutes longer, until cooked through.
2d7a6010-e293-4211-8881-9a862b5cd898 Serve with a remoulade sauce or tartar sauce.
88512cf0-77e2-407d-8892-e480134bb18f Put the butter and cheese in the container of a food processor. Add the flour, salt, cayenne, and Worcestershire. Cover and pulse until thoroughly blended.
88512cf0-77e2-407d-8892-e480134bb18f If a food processor is not used, put the flour, salt, and cayenne in a bowl. Add the butter, cheese, and Worcestershire, and using two knives or a pastry blender, blend thoroughly.
88512cf0-77e2-407d-8892-e480134bb18f Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap and chill for at least 1 hour.
88512cf0-77e2-407d-8892-e480134bb18f Preheat oven to 300 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or leave it ungreased.
88512cf0-77e2-407d-8892-e480134bb18f Roll small amounts of dough into a long tube about the width of a straw and cut into desired lengths. Alternatively, roll dough out on a floured surface to about 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch thickness, cut into strips, and gently twist. If you roll them into straw shapes, use a flat block or flat wide dish bottom to roll them uniformly. Arrange the strips on the baking sheet.
88512cf0-77e2-407d-8892-e480134bb18f Bake in the preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until the straws are crisp and lightly browned. Remove and let cool.
d1b1bf28-1827-4c92-bde6-8f9c3f9b4f7e Cut peppers in half lengthwise. Discard pulp and seeds and rinse carefully.
d1b1bf28-1827-4c92-bde6-8f9c3f9b4f7e In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining crab filling ingredients.
d1b1bf28-1827-4c92-bde6-8f9c3f9b4f7e Stuff pepper halves with crab mixture and press stuffing around the pepper. Set peppers aside.
d1b1bf28-1827-4c92-bde6-8f9c3f9b4f7e Prepare breading mixture. Place the 2 cups cracker meal in a wide, shallow dish or pie plate. In another bowl mix together milk, eggs and salt and pepper.
d1b1bf28-1827-4c92-bde6-8f9c3f9b4f7e Dip peppers in egg mixture, then roll in the cracker meal to coat thoroughly. Repeat procedure with all peppers.
d1b1bf28-1827-4c92-bde6-8f9c3f9b4f7e Deep fry at 365 F, until golden brown.
d1b1bf28-1827-4c92-bde6-8f9c3f9b4f7e Drain on paper towels or brown paper.
b14ace25-48c8-431d-9558-0411b1e39ebd Gather the ingredients.
b14ace25-48c8-431d-9558-0411b1e39ebd Spread lettuce in an even layer in a deep-dish pie plate, gratin dish or serving bowl.
b14ace25-48c8-431d-9558-0411b1e39ebd Spread refried beans over lettuce. (Hint: To make the beans easier to spread, transfer them to a microwave-safe container, and heat on high for 20 seconds.)
b14ace25-48c8-431d-9558-0411b1e39ebd Top with salsa, then guacamole.
b14ace25-48c8-431d-9558-0411b1e39ebd Stir together sour cream and chili powder. Spread over the guacamole layer.
b14ace25-48c8-431d-9558-0411b1e39ebd Sprinkle cheddar cheese over the sour cream layer. Dot with sliced black olives.
b14ace25-48c8-431d-9558-0411b1e39ebd Serve with tortilla chips.
240da6ba-215f-40a4-b0fb-288dedc04095 Heat the oven to 250° F (130° C/Gas 1/2). Grease a baking pan or line with foil and grease the foil.
240da6ba-215f-40a4-b0fb-288dedc04095 In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar, flour, and salt.
240da6ba-215f-40a4-b0fb-288dedc04095 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the egg white until foamy.
240da6ba-215f-40a4-b0fb-288dedc04095 Slowly beat the brown sugar and flour mixture into the egg white. Add the vanilla extract and then fold in the pecan halves.
240da6ba-215f-40a4-b0fb-288dedc04095 Arrange the pecans in a single layer in the prepared baking pan and bake for about 45 to 55 minutes, stirring about every 15 to 20 minutes.
71374e8b-7dab-4a23-96f7-39d40a7cd137 Gather the ingredients.
71374e8b-7dab-4a23-96f7-39d40a7cd137 Toast the pecans: Preheat oven to 350 F. Spread chopped pecans out on a large baking sheet. Bake for about 5 minutes, or until the chopped pecans are lightly browned and aromatic.
71374e8b-7dab-4a23-96f7-39d40a7cd137 In a medium saucepan, combine the brown sugar, granulated sugar, cream, milk, butter, and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 230 F.
71374e8b-7dab-4a23-96f7-39d40a7cd137 Lower heat slightly if the mixture threatens to boil over. Add the toasted pecans and continue cooking, stirring constantly, to 236 F.
71374e8b-7dab-4a23-96f7-39d40a7cd137 The mixture should form a soft ball when a little is dropped in cold water. Remove from the heat and add vanilla; let stand for about 5 minutes. Stir with a wooden spoon until the mixture is thickened and slightly creamy, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
71374e8b-7dab-4a23-96f7-39d40a7cd137 Using a tablespoon or small cookie scoop, spoon the pralines onto a sheet of parchment paper or waxed paper. If the mixture becomes grainy, heat and stir over medium heat for a few seconds, or until it can be easily scooped and dropped.
71374e8b-7dab-4a23-96f7-39d40a7cd137 Serve and enjoy!
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Gather the ingredients.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Oil a shallow baking dishâ€”large enough to fit the mushroom caps in one layerâ€” with 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Wash the mushrooms well.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Remove the stems from the mushrooms and chop them finely.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Arrange the mushroom caps in the prepared baking pan.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 If you are using individual Italian sausages, remove the outer casings.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat; cook the sausage with the chopped mushroom stems until the sausage is no longer pink. Add the garlic and continue cooking for 1 minute
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Add parsley and the Parmesan cheese to the sausage mixture. If the mixture is too dry, add a teaspoon or two of olive oil.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Fill the mushroom caps with the sausage mixture and pour 1/4 cup of hot water into the pan.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Bake in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes.
353a7751-c26d-4d1b-b744-d08c2f2f8158 Serve and enjoy!
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Gather the ingredients.
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Heat the oven to 375 F (190 C/Gas 5).
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Line a rimmed baking pan with foil. Butter the foil lightly.
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Wash mushrooms well; dry and remove stems with a sharp knife.
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Combine the crabmeat , chopped parsley, and pimiento.
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Stir together mayonnaise and dry mustard until well blended; gently stir it into crabmeat mixture.
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Fill each mushroom cap with about 2 tablespoons of crab mixture. Arrange in the prepared baking pan.
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 If desired, top the mushrooms with a little shredded or grated Parmesan cheese.
789305ab-2bb2-4409-bc8f-4a4ac85dc290 Bake in the preheated oven for about 10 minutes, or until hot.
fd9df57f-690f-488c-b082-591683412de8 Gather the ingredients.
fd9df57f-690f-488c-b082-591683412de8 Place a large disposable baking pan on a large foil-lined baking sheet. If you don't have a disposable pan, line a large baking pan bottom and sides with heavy duty foil.
fd9df57f-690f-488c-b082-591683412de8 With kitchen shears, cut tips off of chicken wings; discard tips. Cut each trimmed wing into two pieces at the joint.
fd9df57f-690f-488c-b082-591683412de8 In a large cup or small bowl, combine the maple syrup, brown sugar, garlic, green onions, soy sauce, teriyaki, and peppers.
fd9df57f-690f-488c-b082-591683412de8 Arrange the chicken wing pieces in the prepared baking pan and pour the sauce over them.
fd9df57f-690f-488c-b082-591683412de8 Bake the wings for 1 hour at 350 F, turning 3 to 4 times. Increase the oven temperature to 400 F and bake for about 20 to 30 minutes longer, turning the wings every 10 minutes to brown evenly.
fd9df57f-690f-488c-b082-591683412de8 Remove the wings to a serving dish and garnish with chopped cilantro, sesame seeds, or chopped green onion.
0daca371-b063-4d6b-9df0-b4893f16d63a In the slow cooker, combine the ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, barbecue sauce, and bourbon. Stir to blend thoroughly.
0daca371-b063-4d6b-9df0-b4893f16d63a Add the cocktail franks or mini smoked sausages to the sauce and stir to coat.
0daca371-b063-4d6b-9df0-b4893f16d63a Cover the pot and cook on high for 1 hour; remove the lid and cook on low for 1 hour longer.
0daca371-b063-4d6b-9df0-b4893f16d63a Keep the setting on low or switch it to warm and serve the cocktail franks hot from the slow cooker.
cfff2403-000f-42c0-9f14-367c358d12cc In a bowl with a hand-held stick blender or in a food processor, combine the cream cheese, mayonnaise, wing sauce, and celery. Blend or process until smooth.
cfff2403-000f-42c0-9f14-367c358d12cc Serve the dip with chicken wings, chicken strips, vegetable dippers, or crackers.
cfff2403-000f-42c0-9f14-367c358d12cc Cover the bowl and refrigerate until serving time.
cfff2403-000f-42c0-9f14-367c358d12cc The recipe makes about 2 cups of dip.
6f6d76fd-ffdd-44f6-bc8d-3144f4ecbdd9 If using regular hot dogs, cut into bite-size pieces. Place franks in a crock pot.
6f6d76fd-ffdd-44f6-bc8d-3144f4ecbdd9 Combine remaining ingredients in a measuring cup or bowl and pour over hot dogs.
6f6d76fd-ffdd-44f6-bc8d-3144f4ecbdd9 Cook on LOW for 3 to 4 hours, or on high for 1 to 2 hours.
6f6d76fd-ffdd-44f6-bc8d-3144f4ecbdd9 Serve from the crock pot, with the temperature set on low.
dad7313d-8c55-4531-8c15-1c094d19ae2c In a medium bowl with an electric mixer, combine the cream cheese, mayonnaise, and garlic; beat until smooth. Fold in the drained minced clams along with the remaining seasonings. Transfer the dip mixture to a serving bowl or container.
dad7313d-8c55-4531-8c15-1c094d19ae2c Cover the container and refrigerate the clam dip for about 2 hours, or until it is thoroughly chilled.
dad7313d-8c55-4531-8c15-1c094d19ae2c Serve the chilled dip with chips, crackers, or fresh sliced vegetables.
f2f314ee-2841-42f9-932c-ac35bd1b7244 Gather the ingredients.
f2f314ee-2841-42f9-932c-ac35bd1b7244 In a medium mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, cheddar cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, and garlic. Beat with an electric mixer until well blended. Scrape the sides with a spatula and cover with plastic wrap.
f2f314ee-2841-42f9-932c-ac35bd1b7244 Refrigerate the cheese mixture until firm and then shape it into a ball. Wet your hands to help with the process without the cheese sticking to your palms.
f2f314ee-2841-42f9-932c-ac35bd1b7244 Roll the cheese ball in the chopped pecans or peanuts until well coated.
f2f314ee-2841-42f9-932c-ac35bd1b7244 Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least 24 hours for best flavor.
f2f314ee-2841-42f9-932c-ac35bd1b7244 Remove from the refrigerator 2 hours before serving. Remove the plastic wrap and place it in the center of a plate or tray and arrange assorted crackers around it just before serving. Wrap and refrigerate any leftover cheese ball for up to one week.
f2f314ee-2841-42f9-932c-ac35bd1b7244 Enjoy!
49d22b50-c0c1-47a1-a73d-bc600e89b68f In a small bowl, combine wine and melted butter. In a food processor, combine Cheddar cheese, sour cream, salt, and cayenne pepper. Process until mixture is smooth. With motor still running, gradually add the butter and wine mixture, processing until smooth.
49d22b50-c0c1-47a1-a73d-bc600e89b68f Store in airtight container and refrigerate for 24 hours for best flavor.
49d22b50-c0c1-47a1-a73d-bc600e89b68f Serve with assorted crackers.
48a010cd-a244-4d5a-bf2f-18845ac4acad Gather the ingredients.
48a010cd-a244-4d5a-bf2f-18845ac4acad In a medium bowl, mix cornmeal, salt, self-rising flour, water, bacon drippings, milk, and egg to form a batter thick enough to drop out with a tablespoon.
48a010cd-a244-4d5a-bf2f-18845ac4acad Heat a cast-iron skillet until it's hot but not smoking. Add oil and let it heat up.
48a010cd-a244-4d5a-bf2f-18845ac4acad Drop batter by the tablespoon into the skillet. Let it cook until the edges are bubbling and the center is set.
48a010cd-a244-4d5a-bf2f-18845ac4acad Using a spatula, flip the fritters to cook on the other side.
48a010cd-a244-4d5a-bf2f-18845ac4acad Remove the fritters to a plate lined with a paper towel to drain excess oil.
48a010cd-a244-4d5a-bf2f-18845ac4acad Serve immediately with honey and butter, if desired.
50bb5414-f24b-43c7-a1b8-209eac2fa220 Gather the ingredients.
50bb5414-f24b-43c7-a1b8-209eac2fa220 Spray the inside of the crock pot stoneware with nonstick cooking spray.
50bb5414-f24b-43c7-a1b8-209eac2fa220 Place all ingredients except hot sauce in the crock pot. Cook on high 1 to 2 hours.
50bb5414-f24b-43c7-a1b8-209eac2fa220 Stir. Taste, and add hot sauce if desired. Turn heat down to warm and serve the chili con queso right from the crockpot, or place in a serving dish and serve with tortilla chips.
50bb5414-f24b-43c7-a1b8-209eac2fa220 Enjoy!
ce008785-d5be-4dc0-8b35-0e060bae31f7 Gather the ingredients.
ce008785-d5be-4dc0-8b35-0e060bae31f7 Peel the eggs carefully and cut them in half lengthwise. Set the halves on a platter or egg tray. If you cut a very thin slice from the bottom of the eggs, they will not wobble.
ce008785-d5be-4dc0-8b35-0e060bae31f7 Remove and mash the yolks; combine mayonnaise, mustard, and relish. Taste and add salt and pepper, as needed. Add more mayonnaise, if desired.
ce008785-d5be-4dc0-8b35-0e060bae31f7 Refill the centers of the egg halves with the yolk mixture. Garnish with a sprinkling of ground paprika.
ce008785-d5be-4dc0-8b35-0e060bae31f7 Serve and enjoy!
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b Gather the ingredients.
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b Heat the oven to 350 F. Line a large rimmed baking sheet (half-sheet pan) with parchment paper.
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b In a large, heavy saucepan or deep skillet over medium heat, melt the butter. Add the corn syrup and brown sugar and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture boils.
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b Add the pecans to the syrup mixture and cook for about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b Spread the syrup-coated pecans out on the prepared baking sheet.
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b Bake in the preheated oven for about 7 minutes, or until the pecans are browned.
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b Cool completely and transfer to a covered container.
992105e4-a95e-4d84-bf3c-5f1f4c86859b Store at room temperature for up to 2 weeks.
85b5062f-9417-4485-a746-2d7caf6e4d03 In a bowl or food storage bag, toss scallops gently with the Cajun seasoning, 2 teaspoons olive oil, salt, and pepper. Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
85b5062f-9417-4485-a746-2d7caf6e4d03 Heat the 1 tablespoon olive oil and 2 teaspoons of butter in a large skillet over high heat. With tongs, arrange the scallops in the hot fat and cook for about 2 to 3 minutes on each side, or until nicely browned.
85b5062f-9417-4485-a746-2d7caf6e4d03 Serve as a first-course salad with Mimosa Dressing or serve with rice and steamed veggies for a delicious meal.
790dff4d-a22a-4e9a-8e70-00e861c0261c In a large food storage bag, combine buttermilk, 1 teaspoons salt, and 2 teaspoons Creole seasoning. Add chicken; seal and refrigerate for about 2 hours.
790dff4d-a22a-4e9a-8e70-00e861c0261c Combine flour and remaining 1 teaspoon Creole seasoning in a food storage bag. Add the chicken and toss to coat thoroughly.
790dff4d-a22a-4e9a-8e70-00e861c0261c Heat about 1/4 to 1/2-inch oil in a deep heavy skillet to about 350°.
790dff4d-a22a-4e9a-8e70-00e861c0261c Fry several chicken pieces at a time. Fry, turning several times with tongs, until deep golden brown, about 6 to 8 minutes for each batch. Serve with Come Back Sauce, Jezebel Sauce, or Sweet and Sour Sauce.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 Gather the ingredients.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 In a small bowl, combine the paprika, garlic powder, oregano, onion powder, kosher salt, thyme, and the black and cayenne peppers. Stir to combine. Transfer the mixture to a jar with a lid.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 In another small bowl, combine the mayonnaise with the finely chopped green onion, Dijon mustard, hot sauce, and dill relish. Add 3/4 teaspoon of the Cajun seasoning (or to taste). Cover and refrigerate the remoulade until serving time.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, minced onion, pressed garlic, and 1 1/2 teaspoons of the Cajun seasoning mixture. Mix to blend thoroughly.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 With your hands of a burger press, shape the meat mixture into four burgers. Each burger will weigh approximately 6 ounces. With your thumb, make an indentation in the center of each burger. Refrigerate the burgers until it is time to cook. Store the remaining Cajun seasoning in a cool, dark place.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 Heat the grill to medium-high heat. When the grill is hot, brush the grate with olive oil or canola oil. Place the burgers on the grill, indentation side up and grill for about 5 minutes. Carefully flip the burgers and continue grilling for about 4 to 5 minutes longer, or until the burgers register 160 F, the minimum safe temperature recommended by the USDA.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 Transfer the burgers to a plate or rack and tent with foil. Let them rest for 5 minutes.
34c93dff-ee30-42c6-8a5b-8183396c27c4 Assemble the burgers on buns with your choice of toppings, along with a generous amount of remoulade sauce.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Gather the ingredients.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar, salt, paprika, chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, black pepper, and cayenne pepper.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Pat the chicken with paper towels to dry. Rub the chicken pieces all over with the seasoning mixture.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Place the trivet in the instant pot and add 1 cup of water. Place the seasoned chicken pieces on the trivet.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Pour about 1/4 cup of barbecue sauce into a small bowl and brush it over the chicken pieces.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Secure the Instant Pot lid and turn the steam release valve to the sealing position. Choose the pressure cook function (or manual on early models), high pressure, and set the time for 18 minutes. When the time is up, let the steam release naturally for 10 minutes. Carefully turn the steam release valve to the venting position to release any remaining steam.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Preheat the oven broiler. Arrange the chicken on a foil-lined baking pan and brush the pieces with more barbecue sauce. Broil the chicken for about 2 to 4 minutes, or until slightly charred. Broiling gives the chicken extra color, but feel free to skip this step.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Serve the chicken with potatoes or rice and offer extra barbecue sauce at the table.
55d4268f-d92a-4a37-83bc-ddfaffd30cd6 Enjoy your meal!
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Gather the ingredients.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Put the bacon in a large skillet and place the skillet over medium heat. Cook until the bacon has rendered its fat. With a slotted spoon, remove the bacon pieces to paper towels to drain. You should have about 1/4 to 1/3 cup of drippings left in the pan. Refrigerate the crumbled bacon to use as a garnish or save it for another use.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Remove 2 tablespoons of oil from the 3/4 cup and set it aside. Add the remaining oilâ€”about 2/3 cupâ€”to the bacon drippings. Add the flour to the bacon drippings and oil mixture and cook over medium heat, constantly stirring, for about 25 to 30 minutes, or until the roux is the color of milk chocolate. Remove the roux from the heat and set it aside.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat. Add the smoked sausage and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Add the onions, celery, green and red bell pepper, and the white and light green parts of the green onions to the sausage; continue to cook for about 4 minutes, or until the vegetables are soft. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute longer.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 To the vegetables and sausage, add the reserved roux; stir to combine.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Gradually add 2 cups the chicken stock to the pot a little at a time, stirring constantly. Add the chopped turkey, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaves, salt, Cajun seasoning, thyme, and black pepper. Bring to a boil and then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. If too thick, add more stock in small amounts.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Stir the parsley and chopped green onions (dark green parts) into the gumbo and serve it over hot steamed rice.
139bb867-ca19-4180-aed5-86c795d0b0d7 Garnish the turkey gumbo with extra green onions, parsley, and the crumbled cooked bacon, if desired.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Gather the ingredients.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Preheat the oven to 200 F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil and place a rack in the pan.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Arrange the catfish in a wide, shallow bowl or pie plate; pour the buttermilk over the fish.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Pour about 1 inch of oil in a deep, heavy skillet or heavy Dutch oven and place the pan over medium-high heat. (If you will be frying hushpuppies in the same pan, use a Dutch oven and 1 1/2 inches of oil.)
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Meanwhile, combine the cornmeal, flour, salt, paprika, pepper, cayenne, and garlic powder on a pie plate.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Take the fish out of the buttermilk and dredge the fish fillets in the flour mixture to coat thoroughly. Shake off excess flour mixture.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 You are ready to fry when the oil reaches about 350 F; you can use a candy thermometer or drop a pinch of the flour mixture into the oilâ€”if it bubbles and floats the oil is ready. Just be mindful of maintaining the oil temperature while cooking the fish in batches.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Carefully arrange 2 to 3 fillets in the pan.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Cook for about 5 to 6 minutes, or until golden brown. If the oil isn't deep enough to cover the fish, turn the fillets carefully after about 3 minutes.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 Remove the fish to the rack in the baking pan and place in the oven while you cook another batch. Repeat until all of the fish are cooked.
117587db-a50a-4f5e-b626-c56cb85a00b1 If making hush puppies, bring the oil up to 370 F and fry them in the same pan.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Gather the ingredients.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Start by making the rub. Place all the rub ingredients in a food processor and blitz to create a dark, lump-free powder. Pour into a small bowl.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Dry the chicken breasts with kitchen paper. Place in a large dish, pour enough spice rub over the breasts to coat both sides of the chicken breasts. Cover the dish with a kitchen towel and set aside for 30 minutes.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Preheat the oven to 425 F.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Heat the olive oil in a non-stick ovenproof pan to hot, but not smoking. Carefully remove the chicken breasts one at a time from the dish. Shake gently to remove any loose rub, then place in the pan to sear. Cook for 3 minutes on each side, then place the pan in the center of the oven.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Bake the chicken for 15 minutes or until cooked by checking using a meat thermometer reading 165 F or press the breast firmly and it should feel solid to the touch.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Once cooked, remove from the oven, cover with a tea cloth and leave to rest for 10 minutes, which will soften the chicken and make it more tender. Slice the chicken into even slices and serve over hot white rice (or pasta if you prefer) sprinkled with chili flakes and a little lime zest.
dedec8ad-f65d-40b5-8e17-7d963b630fe6 Serve and enjoy!
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b First, prepare the pulled pork filling. Place half a sliced onion in the bottom of your slow cooker.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b Stud the pork roast with cloves and season with salt and pepper.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b Place roast in slow cooker on top of the sliced onion. Add the remaining sliced onion and add enough water to cover.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b Cover and cook on low 8 to 12 hours, or until the pork is very tender and falling apart.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b Remove roast. Remove and discard cloves, bone and fat, as well as any water, onions and grease remaining in pot.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b When pork roast is cool enough to handle, use a fork or your fingers to pull it apart until the entire roast is shredded.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b Return the pulled pork to the slow cooker. Add the chopped onion and BBQ sauce and cover. Heat on high for 1 to 3 hours or until the onions are soft and the mixture is very tender
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b When the pulled pork is almost ready, prepare the cornbread taco shells. In a bowl, combine cornmeal, all-purpose flour and salt. Then add milk and the egg, and stir until mixture is nicely incorporated. Donâ€™t overwork the batterâ€”some lumps are okay. You want a pretty thick consistency, but still a little runny. If the mixture seems too dry, add a little more milk; if it seems too wet, add a touch more cornmeal.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b Grease a small skillet with oil and place over medium heat. When the pan is very hot, spoon a small amount of batter into the skillet. Cook the cornbread taco shell 2 to 3 minutes on the first side, then flip, and cook 1 to 2 minutes more on the second side. The taco shells should be soft and flexible. Repeat with remaining batter. Depending on the size of your tacos, recipe should yield 4 to 8 taco shells.
2948c149-57b2-478d-bf73-a26ad1b3e65b To assemble tacos, fill taco shells with the pulled pork, coleslaw, jalapeños and drizzle with lime juice. Serve immediately.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Gather the ingredients.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Dry the chicken pieces with a paper towel and arrange them in pan or baking dish. Rub the chicken with 1 tablespoon of kosher salt and 1 teaspoon of black pepper. Cover the pan with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours or up to 24 hours.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 In a deep, heavy skillet or saucepan, heat about 2 inches of oil to 325 F. Place a cooling rack in a rimmed baking pan. Preheat the oven to 200 F.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 In a bowl, combine the milk, eggs, and hot sauce.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Pour the milk and egg mixture into a wide, shallow bowl. Put the flour in a separate wide, shallow bowl.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Dip a chicken piece in the flour and turn until it is thoroughly coated.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Dip the flour-coated chicken in the milk and egg mixture and turn to coat.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Dip the chicken piece in the flour once again, turning to coat.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Repeat with the remaining chicken pieces.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Fry the chicken in small batches in the hot oil for 16 to 19 minutes, or until the pieces reach about 165 F at their centers on an instant-read thermometer. Chicken breast pieces will take 15 to 17 minutes. Remove the chicken pieces to the prepared pan with the cooling rack and place the pan in the oven. Repeat with the remaining chicken pieces. Set the cooking oil aside to cool slightly.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 In a heatproof bowl, combine the cayenne pepper, brown sugar, paprika, 1 teaspoon of kosher salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and the garlic powder. Add about 1/2 cup of the hot cooking oil to the spices and stir to blend.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Brush the hot oil over the chicken pieces. Stir the oil frequently as you brush.
99fe9d1d-8066-4cc1-8c95-9242143da961 Serve with white bread and pickles. Enjoy.
44b22c88-7665-4b75-8588-6358b662bf35 Heat oil to 375 F.
44b22c88-7665-4b75-8588-6358b662bf35 Beat egg in a bowl with milk. In another bowl, mix flour, cornstarch, salt, pepper and cayenne in a bowl.
44b22c88-7665-4b75-8588-6358b662bf35 Dunk chicken in liquid mixture, then flour mixture, then add to the hot oil and fry until golden brown and chicken cooked through. Set aside.
44b22c88-7665-4b75-8588-6358b662bf35 Slice donuts in half, spread butter on insides and place cut side down on griddle until toasty.
44b22c88-7665-4b75-8588-6358b662bf35 To assemble the sandwich, first put donut halves, grilled sides on the outside. On one piece, top with 2 pieces of fried chicken, a few dashes of hot sauce, add several slices of cheese, then top with the other donut half to close the sandwich.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 Gather the ingredients.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 Dry the pork with paper towels. In a large bowl, combine the brown sugar, smoked paprika, kosher salt, garlic powder, chili powder, black pepper, onion powder, cumin, dry mustard, and cayenne. Add the pork chunks to the bowl and toss to coat them thoroughly with the spice mixture.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 Place the trivet in the Instant Pot and add the water (or other liquid) and vinegar. Place the seasoned pork on the trivet.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 Secure the lid on the Instant Pot and turn the steam release valve to the sealing position. Select the pressure cook or manual button (high pressure) and set the timer to 45 minutes.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 When the time is up, allow a natural release for 15 to 20 minutes. Carefully turn the steam release valve to the venting position to release the remaining pressure.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 Drain and discard the liquids. Remove the pork to a bowl and shred it. Add 1 1/2 cups of barbecue sauce to the pork and stir to blend. Return the pork to the Instant Pot and select the lowest sauté setting. Cook the pork until it is thoroughly heated.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 Serve the pulled pork in split buns or as an entrée with mac and cheese, buttermilk biscuits, and coleslaw.
f6438893-977e-4713-84dd-b5b923d187f7 Enjoy!
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Gather the ingredients.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Cut the tops off of the bell peppers and rinse them under cold water; remove seeds and cut away the white ribs, which might be bitter. Chop the edible part of tops and set aside. Place the peppers in a large pot and cover with salted water.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Heat the olive oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat until oil is hot and the butter is foamy. Sauté the chopped bell pepper (from the tops), chopped onion, and chopped celery for about 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Add the (undrained) canned diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, crushed garlic, oregano, basil, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook for about 10 minutes.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 In a large mixing bowl, combine the egg with the remaining 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and Worcestershire sauce. Gently stir to blend; add ground beef, cooked rice, and 1 cup of the tomato sauce mixture. Mix well.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Heat the oven to 350 F.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Stuff the peppers loosely with the ground beef mixture and place them in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Pour the remaining tomato mixture over the stuffed peppers.
64a361da-be27-433d-ae4b-b8b2fb5d4887 Bake the peppers for about 45 minutes, or until the meat mixture is thoroughly cooked.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 Gather the ingredients.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 In a skillet over medium heat, brown the sliced sausage in 2 to 3 teaspoons of vegetable oil; remove the sausage to a plate and set aside.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 In a large stockpot or Dutch oven, combine the chicken broth and tomatoes. Place the pot over medium heat to bring to a simmer.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 Meanwhile, in a large skillet over medium-high heat, combine the 1/2 cup of oil and the flour. Cook, whisking constantly until the roux is medium to deep brown. Don't let the mixture burn, or you will have to start over with fresh oil and flour.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 To the skillet with the roux, add the chopped onion, celery, and bell pepper; cook, stirring constantly with a spoon until vegetables are softened. Stir the vegetable and roux mixture into the simmering tomato and broth mixture.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 Put the skillet back on the heat and add 2 more teaspoons of oil; reduce to medium heat. Add the okra and cook, stirring, until lightly browned and not stringy or sticky.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 Transfer the cooked okra to the simmering pot along with the Creole or Cajun seasoning, the bay leaf, and cooked sausage. Cover and cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 Add the prepared shrimp and cook for about 10 minutes longer, until the shrimp is cooked through.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 Taste and add salt and pepper, as needed.
1839e874-3fb0-4e97-ad46-a58c3df77585 Serve the gumbo over a mound of hot boiled long-grain white rice. Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley or green onions.
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f Gather the ingredients.
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f If you will be cooking in batches, line a large baking sheet with foil and top with a wire rack (such as a cooling rack).
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f Sprinkle the chicken breasts with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f In a food storage bag or wide, shallow bowl, combine the flour, 1/2 teaspoon each salt and pepper, and the baking powder. Shake or stir to blend. Put the chicken pieces in the flour mixture and shake or mix gently until well coated.
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f Place the chicken on a rimmed baking dish or large platter. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f Pour about 1 1/2 inches of vegetable oil in a deep skillet or Dutch oven and place it over medium heat. Heat the oil to 350 F.
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f Add the chicken pieces to the hot oil. When the chicken is hot and browning well, reduce the heat to medium-low. Continue cooking for 8 to 12 minutes on each side, or until well browned and juices run clear when pierced with a fork. (Boneless chicken breasts will take about half the time.)
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f If cooking in batches, remove the chicken pieces to the rack on the prepared pan and tent loosely with foil; fry the remaining chicken.
c4fbc91f-5e0c-4194-9cd2-377f9e2d537f Serve with your favorite sides and enjoy.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Gather the ingredients.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Peel about 12 to 15 large leaves off of the cabbage head.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Drop the cabbage leaves into a large pot of well salted boiling water; cover and cook for 3 minutes. Drain well.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Position a rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4).
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc For the filling, combine the ground beef, rice, onion, egg, milk, salt, and pepper in a medium bowl. Mix well and divide into 12 portions.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Place a portion of the beef mixture (about 2-1/4 oz.) onto the center of each cabbage leaf.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Roll the leaf around the filling, burrito-style, folding in the edges to seal it in.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Fasten the rolls with toothpicks. Place the rolls in a single layer in a large baking dish or an oven-safe Dutch oven.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc For the sauce, combine the diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, and 1/2 cup of water.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Pour over the cabbage rolls. Cover with a lid or aluminum foil (carefully avoiding the toothpicks) and bake in the preheated oven for about 1 hour until the cabbage is tender and the sauce is bubbling.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Remove the rolls with a slotted spoon and discard the toothpicks.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Carefully pour the juices into a medium saucepan and place over medium heat. Stir the cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water until dissolved. Add to the sauce and bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly until thickened.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Serve the cabbage rolls topped with the sauce.
a183170f-28e0-4cb6-986d-f16fd5466ebc Enjoy!
68b5d3a2-0e33-4d44-8b6d-fe8a6679ef22 Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4). Butter a 2 1/2- to 3-quart baking dish.
68b5d3a2-0e33-4d44-8b6d-fe8a6679ef22 Bring a large pot of about 4 quarts of water to a boil over high heat. Add about 1 tablespoon of salt to the water. Add the macaroni, reduce the heat to medium, and continue boiling until al dente** following package directions. Drain the macaroni well.
68b5d3a2-0e33-4d44-8b6d-fe8a6679ef22 In a bowl combine the mayonnaise, cream cheese, shredded cheese, drained pimientos, and grated onion. Mix the ingredients together until thoroughly blended. Taste and add salt and freshly ground black pepper, as needed. Add the hot drained macaroni and mix until well blended.
68b5d3a2-0e33-4d44-8b6d-fe8a6679ef22 Spoon the macaroni and pimiento cheese mixture into the prepared baking dish.
68b5d3a2-0e33-4d44-8b6d-fe8a6679ef22 Sprinkle the French fried onions over the casserole.
68b5d3a2-0e33-4d44-8b6d-fe8a6679ef22 Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes, or until the macaroni and cheese mixture is hot and bubbling around the edges and the topping is lightly browned and crispy.
68b5d3a2-0e33-4d44-8b6d-fe8a6679ef22 Serve with a simple tossed green salad or fresh sliced tomatoes, or serve it along with a holiday meal or Sunday dinner.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Gather the ingredients.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Cut beef into narrow 2-inch long strips about 1/2 inch thick. Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper and set aside.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a medium saucepan.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Blend in flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Gradually stir in beef broth, stirring and cooking until thickened and smooth.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Heat the olive oil and remaining 1 tablespoon of butter in a skillet or sauté pan over medium heat; add the onions and cook, stirring, until the onions are just tender.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Add the meat strips and quickly brown on all sides.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Add the beef and onions to the thickened beef sauce. Cover and cook on low for 10 minutes; stir in sour cream and heat through, but do not boil.
b6cfe601-4806-4248-83d5-8a61aa60300e Arrange the beef stroganoff on a platter over buttered noodles or hot cooked rice, and garnish with the fresh chopped parsley.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Gather the ingredients.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Place tilapia fillets in a shallow dish and sprinkle with garlic powder.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Combine melted butter, lemon juice, and soy sauce in a small bowl.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Pour over the tilapia, then turn to coat. Let stand for 10 minutes.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Heat the broiler to 500 F. Oil the rack of the broiler pan and place it in the oven about 4 inches from the heat source. Heat until the pan is hot.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Place fish on broiler pan and then broil for about 5 minutes on each side, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Sprinkle with paprika.
ce45f4d4-dfdd-4be1-8b9e-d8af7227c7d5 Serve with your choice of sides and enjoy.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Gather the ingredients.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Thoroughly wash the navy beans and pick them over. Discard any damaged or malformed beans and look for small stones.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Pour the beans into a very large pot and add 2 quarts of water. Place the pot over high heat and bring to a full boil; let boil for 3 minutes.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Remove from the heat and let beans soak for 2 to 4 hours.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Once the beans have soaked, add the ham hocks or ham bone to the pot with the beans and their cooking water and bring to a simmer.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Continue to cook over low heat until the beans are tender, or about 90 minutes.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Remove the bones and chop the ham, discarding the bones and fat. Reserve the ham on the side.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Return the chopped ham to the pot. Add the onions, bay leaf, celery, and optional carrots to the pot, as well as the extra leftover chopped ham, if using.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Add enough water or unsalted vegetable stock to make about 16 cups of liquid. Taste the broth and add salt and pepper, as needed.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Cook the soup for about 30 minutes to one hour, or until the vegetables are tender and the liquid has thickened a little.
a24a26dc-2365-49f0-bf70-4819300a67ee Serve hot and enjoy!
077cdfc7-deed-4aeb-8c04-d9740baaf73b Gather the ingredients.
077cdfc7-deed-4aeb-8c04-d9740baaf73b In a saucepan, combine the butter, minced garlic, pepper, salt, dill weed, and paprika. Heat over low heat until butter is melted and begins to simmer.
077cdfc7-deed-4aeb-8c04-d9740baaf73b Remove from the heat and set aside.
077cdfc7-deed-4aeb-8c04-d9740baaf73b Brush a little of the butter mixture in the bottom of a shallow baking dish (line baking dish with foil, if desired) then place tilapia fillets on the buttered area.
077cdfc7-deed-4aeb-8c04-d9740baaf73b Brush top of each tilapia fillet with the seasoned butter mixture.
077cdfc7-deed-4aeb-8c04-d9740baaf73b Bake at 350 F for 12 to 15 minutes, until it flakes and separates easily with a fork.
077cdfc7-deed-4aeb-8c04-d9740baaf73b Enjoy!
de632548-1ae8-4ff6-8e5f-33f36b66f4e1 Gather the ingredients.
de632548-1ae8-4ff6-8e5f-33f36b66f4e1 In a bowl, combine the ground beef, finely chopped onion, cooked rice, and seasonings until well blended.
de632548-1ae8-4ff6-8e5f-33f36b66f4e1 Cut the tops off of the peppers and remove the seeds and fibers.
de632548-1ae8-4ff6-8e5f-33f36b66f4e1 Stuff the peppers with equal portions of the ground beef and rice mixture.
de632548-1ae8-4ff6-8e5f-33f36b66f4e1 Place the stuffed peppers in a crock pot; cover with the spaghetti sauce.
de632548-1ae8-4ff6-8e5f-33f36b66f4e1 Cover and cook on LOW for 6 to 7 hours or on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours. Or until the ground beef is thoroughly cooked and the peppers are tender.
de632548-1ae8-4ff6-8e5f-33f36b66f4e1 To check for doneness, insert an instant-read food thermometer into the center of the filling. It should read at least 160 F / 71 C or 165 F / 74 C for ground turkey.
0ee59ba1-0bd3-49b5-9888-7e9b3cd0f1e1 Gather the ingredients.
0ee59ba1-0bd3-49b5-9888-7e9b3cd0f1e1 Turn the salmon and liquid into a medium-size bowl. Flake the salmon with a fork, removing any skin and bones. Smaller bones are edible and may be mashed. Add the grated onion, parsley, and pepper; blend thoroughly.
0ee59ba1-0bd3-49b5-9888-7e9b3cd0f1e1 Add the beaten eggs and blend well. Add enough breadcrumbs, about 1/2 to 3/4 cup, to make the mixture thick enough to shape into about 12 small patties.
0ee59ba1-0bd3-49b5-9888-7e9b3cd0f1e1 Roll the patties in the remaining breadcrumbs to coat thoroughly.
0ee59ba1-0bd3-49b5-9888-7e9b3cd0f1e1 In a large heavy skillet or sauté pan over low heat, melt 2 tablespoons of butter. When the butter is hot, add the salmon patties. Fry patties slowly on one side until browned. Add the remaining butter, turn the patties, and fry them until browned on the other side.
0ee59ba1-0bd3-49b5-9888-7e9b3cd0f1e1 Serve and enjoy!
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Gather the ingredients.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 In a bowl, combine the ingredients for the rub.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Rub the tri-tip roast all over with the spice mixture.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Put the roast in a food storage bag. Leave it to marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour or up to overnight.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Cover the bottom of a 6- to 7-quart slow cooker insert with the potatoes, onion, and carrots. Drizzle the vegetables with the olive oil and add the parsley, rosemary, oregano or basil, dill, salt, and pepper. Toss to thoroughly coat.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Position the tri-tip roast in the center on top of the vegetables. Add the beef stock.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Cover and cook on low for 6 to 7 hours, or on high for about 3 hours.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Move the meat to a cutting board and slice it thinly against the grain. Serve the meat with the vegetables and any of the braising liquids that accumulated in the slow cooker.
6495972c-8b76-4637-bcd8-b74beeff4221 Enjoy!
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Gather the ingredients.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Peel the shrimp.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Run the tip of a small, sharp knife down the back of a shrimp, remove the dark veinâ€”the shrimp's digestive tractâ€”and then rinse with cold water.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Repeat with the remaining shrimp. Pat them dry with paper towels.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Slice the green onions, keeping the white and light green parts separate from the dark green. Set the dark green sliced green onions aside for garnish.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Heat the butter in large skillet over medium heat. Cook the garlic for 1 or 2 minutes or until softened, but not browned.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Add the shrimp to the garlic, along with the green onions (white and light green parts), wine, and lemon juice. Cook, stirring, until shrimp are pink and firm, about 1 to 2 minutes on each side. (Don't overcook!)
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Add the chopped parsley and salt and pepper before serving.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Garnish with lemon wedges and the sliced dark green onion tops.
c4b64b83-fb2c-43b2-8fab-6962bace9fd9 Serve and enjoy!
a7116a1f-9c91-4573-a873-f996b8f0e5f7 Gather the ingredients.
a7116a1f-9c91-4573-a873-f996b8f0e5f7 Heat the oven to 425 F.
a7116a1f-9c91-4573-a873-f996b8f0e5f7 In a pie plate or a wide, shallow bow,l combine the flour, paprika, salt, and pepper.
a7116a1f-9c91-4573-a873-f996b8f0e5f7 Place the chicken in the flour mixture, turning to coat thoroughly. Or combine the flour and seasonings in a paper bag or plastic food storage bag. Add chicken pieces a few at a time and shake gently to coat.
a7116a1f-9c91-4573-a873-f996b8f0e5f7 Put 1/3 cup butter in a shallow baking pan; place it in the hot oven. When the butter has melted, arrange the chicken in the pan in a single layer, skin-side down.
a7116a1f-9c91-4573-a873-f996b8f0e5f7 Bake for 30 minutes; turn and bake 15 minutes longer, or until chicken is tender and done (at least 165 F on a food thermometer).
5d2d46a6-dffb-45b2-9952-74dec7f61bb4 Gather the ingredients.
5d2d46a6-dffb-45b2-9952-74dec7f61bb4 Put the pork shoulder in the slow cooker, cutting the roast to fit if necessary.
5d2d46a6-dffb-45b2-9952-74dec7f61bb4 Add the water or other liquid and sprinkle the pork lightly with kosher salt, freshly ground black pepper, and cayenne pepper, if using.
5d2d46a6-dffb-45b2-9952-74dec7f61bb4 Cover and cook on LOW for 7 to 9 hours.
5d2d46a6-dffb-45b2-9952-74dec7f61bb4 Drain off the excess liquids, shred the meat with two forks, and discard any excess fat and bone.
5d2d46a6-dffb-45b2-9952-74dec7f61bb4 Return the meat to the crockpot and pour about 1 cup of barbecue sauce over. Cover and cook another 1 to 2 hours.
5d2d46a6-dffb-45b2-9952-74dec7f61bb4 Serve the shredded barbecued pork with extra barbecue sauce on the side.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 Gather the ingredients.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 Preheat the oven to 325 F. Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 Crumble one sleeve of Ritz crackers into the bottom of the prepared casserole dish. Drizzle half of the melted butter over the crackers.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 In a bowl, combine the soup, sour cream, chicken broth, and diced, cooked chicken.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 Spoon the mixture over the Ritz cracker layer.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 Crush the remaining sleeve of crackers and toss them in a bowl with the remaining melted butter. Sprinkle the buttered cracker crumbs over the chicken mixture.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 Bake the casserole in the preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
60e853ac-294c-495e-b04c-c5d3df0c18e8 Serve and enjoy.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Gather the ingredients.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Melt the butter in a Dutch oven or large saucepan over medium-low heat; add the chopped green onion and celery. Sauté, stirring, until tender.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Blend the flour into the butter and vegetables until well incorporated. Continue cooking, stirring, for about 2 minutes.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Warm the milk in another saucepan over medium heat.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Slowly stir the warmed milk into the butter and vegetables. Continue cooking, stirring until thickened.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Add the freshly ground black pepper, tomato paste, and heavy cream.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c If desired, puree the soup in a blender or food processor (see the tips) at this point and then return it to the saucepan.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Stir in the shrimp, crab, and the sherry. Bring it to a simmer.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Serve hot, garnished with parsley, cilantro, and/or chopped green onion tops.
1593ed56-a2fc-4a28-bb8a-94629b3e7c7c Enjoy!
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Gather the ingredients.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Heat oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Cook the pasta in boiling salted water following package directions. Drain and rinse; set aside.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 In a medium saucepan over medium-low heat, melt 4 tablespoons of butter. Add the flour and cook for about 2 minutes, stirring constantly. â€‹
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Gradually add the milk, or half-and-half, and Boursin cheese. Cook, stirring, until hot and thickened.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Add the cheese and peppers. Continue cooking until the cheese has melted, stirring constantly. Add salt and pepper, to taste. If necessary, thin slightly with extra milk.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Combine the sauce with the pasta and stir to blend. Spoon into prepared baking dish.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Toss melted butter and bread crumbs together until the crumbs are thoroughly coated; sprinkle over the casserole.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Bake in the preheated oven for about 25 minutes, or until bubbly and lightly browned.
26f6138f-57c2-4c4b-8111-2cff4b77eef7 Scoop the mac and cheese onto serving plates or bowls and enjoy!
7cfaf187-027c-4161-a327-6711be5bacb0 Gather the ingredients.
7cfaf187-027c-4161-a327-6711be5bacb0 Lightly grease the crockery insert of a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker.
7cfaf187-027c-4161-a327-6711be5bacb0 Trim and discard any excess fat and pat dry with paper towels.
7cfaf187-027c-4161-a327-6711be5bacb0 Scatter the sliced onions in the bottom of the slow cooker, then place ribs on top.
7cfaf187-027c-4161-a327-6711be5bacb0 Sprinkle the pork with salt and pepper, brown sugar, and minced garlic; turn the pork ribs to coat all pieces. Pour apple juice evenly over the pork. Cover and cook on LOW for 7 to 9 hours.
7cfaf187-027c-4161-a327-6711be5bacb0 Drain liquids from the pork and discard. Pour barbecue sauce over the pork and stir slightly to distribute the sauce. Cover and cook on LOW for 1 hour longer. Serve and Enjoy!
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Gather the ingredients.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Line a roasting pan with foil and place a rack on it.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Preheat the oven to 325 F.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Place the ham, fat side up, on a rack in the prepared roasting pan. Score the fat all over in a diamond pattern, cutting to a depth of about 3/4 of an inch. If desired, stud with whole cloves, inserting one clove into each intersection of the diamond pattern.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Bake the ham in the preheated oven for about 18 to 20 minutes per pound. For a 6-pound ham, the cooking time is around 1 hour and 40 minutes and up to 2 hours.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff In a medium saucepan, combine the maple syrup, brown sugar, apple juice, mustard, and ground spice (if using). Place the saucepan over medium-high heat and bring the mixture to a boil. Boil the mixture for about 2 minutes, but be careful not to let it boil over.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff About 20 minutes before the ham is done, spoon about half of the glaze over the ham, and return it to the oven.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff After 10 minutes, brush the remaining glaze mixture over the ham.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Remove the ham from the oven when a thermometer or instant-read thermometer registers at least 140 F in the thickest of the meat away from fat or bone (140 F is the optimal temperature for a fully cooked ham).
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Cover the ham loosely with foil and let it stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
d6c88f06-9e83-496f-9da6-08625501d0ff Carve, serve, and enjoy!
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Gather ingredients.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 If scallops are quite large, cut them so the sizes are fairly uniform.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Rinse the scallops under cold water and pat them dry with paper towels. Remove the tough white side muscle if not already removed.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Heat about 2 to 3 inches of vegetable oil in a deep, heavy cast iron skillet, saucepan, or deep fryer to 350 F.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Line a baking pan or baking sheet with two or three thicknesses of paper towels and set aside.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 In a bowl, combine flour, salt, paprika, and black pepper.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 In another bowl, whisk eggs with the milk.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Put the fine breadcrumbs in a third bowl.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Dip a few of the scallops in the seasoned flour mixture, then in the egg mixture, and then roll them in the breadcrumbs to coat. Repeat with the remaining scallops.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Once the oil has reached the temperature (350 F), add several scallopsâ€•about 6 to 10 depending on the pan sizeâ€•to the hot oil and fry until golden brown, about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Take care not to overcook. They should be warm in the middle, but still moist.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Remove them from the oil with a metal slotted spoon and transfer them to the paper-towel-lined pan. Shake the pan gently for a few seconds so the scallops roll around and excess oil is absorbed.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Repeat with subsequent batches.
0c864b80-f472-4bbb-a746-fb6aa1d157e9 Serve immediately with your choice of cocktail sauce, remoulade sauce, or tartar sauce. Enjoy!
62d2c463-a5d0-45bb-be92-50190456f89f In a slow cooker, layer the ingredients in the order given; add the water or stock. Do not stir the ingredients.
62d2c463-a5d0-45bb-be92-50190456f89f Cover and cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 8 to 10 hours until peas are very soft and the ham falls off the bone.
62d2c463-a5d0-45bb-be92-50190456f89f Remove the meat from the bones and chop. Save some of the chopped ham for a garnish, if desired. Remove the bay leaf.
62d2c463-a5d0-45bb-be92-50190456f89f Before serving, mash the peas slightly to thicken the soup or blend the soup in batches for a smoother texture (safety tips below).
62d2c463-a5d0-45bb-be92-50190456f89f Refrigerate or freeze any leftovers.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Gather the ingredients.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar and mustard. Stir to blend thoroughly.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Moisten the mixture with just enough cola to make a smooth paste. Reserve the remaining cola and set the mustard-sugar paste aside.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 With the help of a sharp knife, score the ham with shallow slashes in a diamond pattern.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Rub the ham with the mustard-sugar paste mixture. If desired, insert a whole clove in each intersection of the diamond pattern.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Place ham in the slow cooker and add the remaining cola.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Cover the pot and cook on HIGH for 1 hour. Turn the slow cooker to LOW and continue cooking the ham for about 7 to 9 hours. Use an instant-read food thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the ham, not touching bone or fat, to ensure the ham has reached the safe temperature â€“ 140 F for fully cooked, and 145 F if not pre-cooked.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Baste the ham with the juices it has yielded about one hour before it's done.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Remove from crockpot and leave to rest for 15 minutes before carving.
086abea5-c490-4f54-8824-ac322e3b5f45 Enjoy!
50285a69-7109-4fd5-9fca-4ce18cd45100 Gather the ingredients.
50285a69-7109-4fd5-9fca-4ce18cd45100 Preheat the oven to 425 F. Lightly oil a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking dish or line it with foil.
50285a69-7109-4fd5-9fca-4ce18cd45100 Combine the garlic, oregano, chili powder, salt, cumin, and black pepper in a small bowl. Add the olive oil and mix well. Use a mortar and pestle to form a paste, or mash it with a fork.
50285a69-7109-4fd5-9fca-4ce18cd45100 Snip off any excess skin and fat deposits from the chicken. Arrange the leg quarters in the prepared baking pan and rub the garlic-spice mixture over each piece.
50285a69-7109-4fd5-9fca-4ce18cd45100 Pour 1/2 cup of chicken broth into the bottom of the baking dish. If desired, use 1/4 cup of dry white wine with 1/4 cup of chicken broth instead.
50285a69-7109-4fd5-9fca-4ce18cd45100 Bake the chicken in the preheated oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until the chicken registers at least 165 F on a meat thermometer.
50285a69-7109-4fd5-9fca-4ce18cd45100 Enjoy!
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Gather the ingredients.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Bring the water and beans to a boil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven; boil for 2 minutes.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Remove the beans from heat, cover, and let stand for 1 hour.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Add the ham and ham bone or ham hock to the beans, along with onion, carrot, celery, bay leaf, and pepper. Bring to a boil.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Skim any foam from top.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Reduce heat, cover, and simmer until beans are tender - about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. If soup is too thick, add a little more water.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 If you used a ham bone or ham hocks, take them out of the soup and remove the meat.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Dice or shred the meat and return it to the soup.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Add the tomato sauce and salt, to taste, and simmer for about 15 minutes longer.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Remove the bay leaf.
8a8dceea-2bf6-4f66-9bba-cc4c6b738af2 Serve in bowls and enjoy!
91943ba5-69d7-415b-bae6-4b21394a4f58 Gather the ingredients.
91943ba5-69d7-415b-bae6-4b21394a4f58 Heat the oven to 450 F/230 C. Line two 9x13x2-inch baking pans with heavy-duty foil.
91943ba5-69d7-415b-bae6-4b21394a4f58 In a food storage bag, combine the flour, salt, pepper, paprika, curry powder, and poultry seasoning.
91943ba5-69d7-415b-bae6-4b21394a4f58 Cut the butter into pieces and place half (1/4 cup) in each foil-lined pan. Put the pans in the oven to melt butter. (Keep an eye on it to make sure it doesn't burn.)
91943ba5-69d7-415b-bae6-4b21394a4f58 Coat the chicken with the seasoned flour mixture, shaking about three legs at a time in the bag.
91943ba5-69d7-415b-bae6-4b21394a4f58 Place the chicken in the melted butter in the prepared pans.
91943ba5-69d7-415b-bae6-4b21394a4f58 Bake the drumsticks for 30 minutes. Turn the chicken over and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, or until tender and nicely browned.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Line a baking dish with foil. Brush the foil with olive oil. Use a garlic or lemon infused oil if you have it.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Heat the oven to 425 F (220 C/Gas 7).
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Cut the fish into serving size pieces. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Put the flour in a wide bowl, pan, or plate.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Whisk egg and milk together in a wide bowl until the mixture is smooth.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Spread the breadcrumbs in a wide bowl, pan, or plate.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Arrange the bowl and plates in this order: flour, milk, and egg, then breadcrumbs.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Dip the fish fillets in the flour, coating thoroughly, then dip in the milk and egg mixture. Coat with breadcrumbs. Arrange on the baking pan and repeat with the remaining fillets and breading.
d330700a-fb67-45c3-a382-da67ab6001ef Bake in the preheated oven for about 10 minutes. Turn and continue baking for another 8 to 10 minutes, or until cooked through. The fish will flake easily with a fork. Allow a little more time for thicker pieces.
57eb21c7-d7bc-4a0e-9de7-b5a9e3b96211 Gather the ingredients.
57eb21c7-d7bc-4a0e-9de7-b5a9e3b96211 Place the pork shoulder in the slow cooker. Add the water and sprinkle with salt and pepper. If desired, add chopped onions.
57eb21c7-d7bc-4a0e-9de7-b5a9e3b96211 Cover and cook on HIGH for 1 hour. Turn to LOW and cook 7 to 9 hours longer, until very tender.
57eb21c7-d7bc-4a0e-9de7-b5a9e3b96211 Remove roast and discard the fat and juices. Chop or shred the pork and then return the meat to the slow cooker.
57eb21c7-d7bc-4a0e-9de7-b5a9e3b96211 Mix some barbecue sauce into the meat for flavorâ€”about 1/2 to 1 cup of sauce. Cover and cook on LOW for about 30 minutes to 1 hour longer, until hot.
57eb21c7-d7bc-4a0e-9de7-b5a9e3b96211 Serve as-is or on warm split sandwich buns with coleslaw and extra barbecue sauce on the side.
57eb21c7-d7bc-4a0e-9de7-b5a9e3b96211 Enjoy!
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Gather the ingredients.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Cook the ziti in boiling salted water following the package directions. Drain well and set aside.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4). Lightly butter a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc While the ziti is cooking, drizzle the olive oil in a large skillet or sauté pan and place it over medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the ground beef, onion, and green bell pepper. Cook, stirring until the onion is tender and the beef is no longer pink.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Drain off the excess fat and then add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, oregano, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Bring to a simmer.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Add the cooked pasta and half of the mozzarella cheese.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Top the casserole with the remaining mozzarella cheese.
1b447323-04fa-47db-a2fd-c8c5db40d5bc Bake the ziti casserole for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Gather the ingredients.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat; brown the oxtails on all sides.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Reduce the heat to medium; add the onions and cook for 5 minutes longer.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute longer.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Sprinkle the flour over the meat and vegetables and stir to blend. Cook for 2 minutes longer.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Put potatoes in bottom of the crock pot along with carrots.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Add the oxtail mixture.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Deglaze the pan with the red wine and pour over the oxtails in the slow cooker.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Add the beef broth to the slow cooker along with the tomato sauce, peppercorns, oregano, chile pepper, cloves, bell pepper, and parsley. Add salt and pepper, to taste.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Cover and cook on low for 9 to 11 hours, or until the oxtails are very tender.
29475168-a78d-4800-af19-5a59a9a1d3c0 Serve and enjoy!
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Put the diced carrots and potatoes in a small saucepan and cover with water. Place the pan over medium heat and bring to a boil. Cover and cook for about 10 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender. Drain and set aside.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 In a deep skillet or saute pan over medium heat, melt the 5 tablespoons of butter. Add the onions and celery and saute for about 2 minutes. Add the chicken pieces and continue cooking, stirring, until the chicken pieces are opaque.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Add the 5 tablespoons of flour to the chicken mixture and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Add the chicken stock and thawed frozen peas. Cook, stirring, until thickened. Add the potatoes and carrots, thyme, salt, to taste, pepper, and heavy cream. Cook, stirring, for about 3 minutes longer. Pour the mixture into a 2-quart baking dish.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Heat the oven to 350 F.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 In a food processor, combine the 2 cups of flour, baking powder, salt, and baking soda. Pulse to mix well. Add the pieces of chilled butter and pulse several times, or until the mixture resembles â€‹coarse meal.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Pour the flour mixture into a large bowl and add the cheese, green onions, and cayenne, if using. Mix well.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Add the buttermilk to the flour mixture and mix with your hands or a spoon just until the dough begins to hold together.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead a few times, just to combine. For the softest biscuits, take care not to overwork the dough. Pat the dough into a rectangle and cut out as desired using a knife, pizza cutter, or biscuit cutters.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Place the biscuits on the chicken pie filling.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Combine the egg yolk with 2 teaspoons of water; brush lightly over each biscuit.
a36d5781-88ab-4e4e-8f90-c114ac58a3b8 Bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the biscuits are golden brown and the filling is bubbling.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 F with a rack in center.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Generously grease the sides and bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with butter or cooking spray.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Heat oil in a medium skillet over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and corn. Cook until fragrant and corn is cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside to cool for 5 minutes.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 In a medium bowl, add the cornbread mix and salt; whisk until well blended.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Add the eggs, butter, and milk to the bowl with the cornmeal mixture. Using a fork, stir together until the wet and dry ingredients are completely combined, with no visible traces of flour or cornmeal.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Stir in the corn, scallions, and half of the cheese.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Spoon into the prepared casserole dish.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Bake until pudding is set and top is golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.
b8d3393d-850d-458b-9acf-e9699564ef82 Garnish with the green scallions.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Lightly brush a rimmed baking sheet with extra-virgin olive oil.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Trim the stem ends of the Brussels sprouts. Remove loose outer leaves and any leaves. Cut the trimmed sprouts in half lengthwise.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Core the pear and cut it into 1-inch pieces or wedges. There's no need to peel the pear.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Slice the small onion or shallot, if using.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 In a large bowl, combine the sliced sprouts, pear and sliced onion or shallot. Drizzle with the 3 tablespoons of olive oil and toss to coat thoroughly.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Spread the sprouts and pear mixture out on the prepared baking sheet and sprinkle lightly with kosher salt and a few grinds of pepper.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Bake for about 30 to 40 minutes, or until the vegetables and pears are browned, turning about every 10 minutes.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Meanwhile, toast the walnuts and cook the bacon.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Place a dry skillet over medium heat. Add the chopped walnuts and cook until lightly browned and aromatic, stirring and turning frequently.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Dice the bacon and cook in a skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove the bacon to paper towels to drain. Set aside.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Remove the Brussels sprouts to a serving bowl. Add the diced bacon and toasted walnuts and toss.
3c9c160b-d4f9-44cc-9d40-bd2416152799 Drizzle 1 teaspoon of balsamic vinegar over the sprouts and toss. Taste and add more balsamic vinegar, as desired. Serve hot.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Gather the ingredients.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Heat the oven to 350 F. Butter a 1-quart casserole or baking dish.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Slice the summer squash and place it in a medium saucepan. Cover the squash with water and add 1 teaspoon of salt. Place the pan over high heat and bring the squash to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cover the pan; continue to cook until tender, or for about 10 to 15 minutes.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Meanwhile, peel the onion and cut it into halves; chop it finely.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Drain the squash thoroughly; return it to the saucepan and mash it. Taste the squash and add salt and pepper, as desired.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab In a bowl, whisk the egg and sugar lightly. Add the mayonnaise, chopped onion, 2 tablespoons of the melted butter, and 1/2 cup of the cheddar cheese. Stir to blend thoroughly.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Blend the mashed squash into the egg and mayonnaise mixture.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Spoon the mixture into the prepared casserole.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Top the casserole with the remaining 1/4 cup of shredded cheese.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Toss the breadcrumbs with the remaining 2 tablespoons of melted butter and then sprinkle them over the casserole.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Bake for 30 minutes, or until bubbly and lightly browned.
00eb7f58-51b4-4419-8bfd-7c580d24baab Serve squash casserole hot.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Gather the ingredients.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Preheat the oven to 375 F. Butter a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking pan or shallow 3-quart casserole.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Peel the sweet potatoes and cut them into 3/4-inch cubes. You should have about 10 to 12 cups when finished. Arrange the sweet potato cubes in the prepared baking pan.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd In a 1 1/4-quart saucepan, combine the brown sugar, butter, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, and ginger and place it over medium heat. Bring the mixture to a boil; stir until the butter is melted and sugar is dissolved, about 7 to 8 minutes.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Stir the vanilla extract into the sauce mixture.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Pour the sugar and butter mixture evenly over the sweet potatoes.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Cover the baking pan tightly with foil and bake for 45 minutes.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd After 45 minutes, uncover the sweet potatoes and gently stir them to coat with the liquid.
