ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Continue baking, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender and the liquid is syrupy.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Remove the baking pan to a rack and increase the oven temperature to 450 F. When the oven has reached 450 F, cover the sweet potatoes with the miniature marshmallows.
ff91d6d9-974e-4882-ab26-54f2adbe1fcd Return the pan to the oven and bake for about 3 to 5 minutes, or until the marshmallows are partially melted and golden brown.
59410a90-cd95-420b-9a0a-2bcfd4592e69 Gather the ingredients.
59410a90-cd95-420b-9a0a-2bcfd4592e69 Spray a large skillet with cooking spray and heat it over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes. Sauté the sliced summer squash, stirring constantly, for about 2 minutes. Add the vegetable broth to the skillet and continue cooking and stirring for a couple more minutes, until the squash feels almost tender.
59410a90-cd95-420b-9a0a-2bcfd4592e69 Add the garlic and green onions and continue cooking and stirring until the squash turns tender but still feels a bit firm, approximately another 2 to 3 minutes.
59410a90-cd95-420b-9a0a-2bcfd4592e69 Use a slotted spoon to scoop the squash from any remaining liquid into a serving bowl. Scatter the basil and add salt and pepper to taste.
59410a90-cd95-420b-9a0a-2bcfd4592e69 Serve and enjoy!
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Gather the ingredients.
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Heat about 2 to 3 inches of vegetable oil in a heavy saucepan to 360 F. Or use an electric deep fryer.
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Combine eggs, milk, and salt in a bowl and whisk to blend.
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Put the flour in a wide, shallow bowl or plate.
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Dip squash in the egg batter and then dredge the slices in flour until well coated.
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Fry in batches in deep hot fat, about 360 F, until golden brown.
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Drain on paper towels.
b311e881-3333-4742-a559-deb789c20692 Season the fried squash slices with salt and pepper or a Creole or seasoned salt blend.
8f924c47-2d00-4f3d-9aae-255fed714e69 Gather the ingredients.
8f924c47-2d00-4f3d-9aae-255fed714e69 Heat the oil in an electric pressure cooker on the sauté setting. Add the onion and bacon and cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are softened and just beginning to brown and bacon has rendered some of its fat about 5 to 6 minutes.
8f924c47-2d00-4f3d-9aae-255fed714e69 Add the collard greens to the pot and season with salt and pepper. Cook, tossing frequently, until the collards are shiny and wilted, 3 to 4 minutes. If all of the greens donâ€™t fit into the pot at the same time, cook and wilt them in batches.
8f924c47-2d00-4f3d-9aae-255fed714e69 Stir in the apple cider vinegar, brown sugar, and hot sauce. Lock lid and turn to the manual setting. Cook on high pressure for 10 minutes.
8f924c47-2d00-4f3d-9aae-255fed714e69 Release the pressure manually, then open lid and taste collard greens. Adjust the seasoning as needed. If thereâ€™s a lot of excess liquid in the pot, return to the sauté setting and simmer until the liquid is reduced enough to just lightly coat the greens.
8f924c47-2d00-4f3d-9aae-255fed714e69 Transfer the cooked collard greens to a platter. Season with additional hot sauce as desired.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Gather the ingredients.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Peel the potatoes and slice them into 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch rounds.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Butter a 7-by-2-inch baking pan (or one that will fit in the Instant Pot with the trivet).
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Arrange a layer of potatoes in the bottom of the pan. Follow the potato layer with about 1 tablespoon of finely chopped onion, a few tablespoons of cheddar cheese, and a sprinkling of the salt, pepper, and nutmeg.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Repeat the layers two times and then finish with another layer of potatoes, a sprinkling of salt and pepper, and a few tablespoons of cheddar cheese. Don't fill the pan completely; there should be at least 1/2-inch of headspace.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b In a bowl, whisk the cream and milk with the flour. Pour the cream and milk over the potatoes. The mixture should come almostâ€”but not quiteâ€”to the top of the potatoes.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Add 1 1/2 cups of water to the Instant Pot.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Place the uncovered baking pan on the trivet. Holding the trivet handles, lower it into the Instant Pot.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Lock the Instant Pot lid in place and set the vent to sealing.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Using the manual setting, choose high pressure for 30 minutes.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b When the time is up, release the pressure quickly.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Grasp the trivet handles and carefully lift the pan of scalloped potatoes out of the cooker.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Sprinkle the remaining cheddar cheese over the potatoes and place the pan on a baking sheet.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Position an oven rack about 6 to 8 inches below the broiler. Preheat the broiler for about 5 to 10 minutes.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Broil the scalloped potatoes for about 3 to 5 minutes, or until golden brown. If necessary, rotate the pan for even browning.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Garnish with chives or parsley, as desired, and serve hot.
09c52518-ef43-4bb8-a403-9d6d2696578b Enjoy!
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Gather the ingredients.
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Heat oven to 350 F. Butter a 2- to 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Wash the squash and then trim and discard the ends. Quarter the squash lengthwise and then cut them into 1/2-inch pieces.
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Transfer the squash pieces to the prepared baking dish. Sprinkle the squash with the 3/4 teaspoon of kosher salt and 1/4 teaspoon of freshly ground black pepper.
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Combine the chicken broth with the minced garlic and pour over the squash.
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Cut the butter into small pieces. Dot the casserole with the butter and then sprinkle with the breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese.
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Cover the baking dish tightly with foil and bake for 35 minutes.
12fa07c7-4e2e-4f69-8796-1ab5c53e7a63 Uncover and bake for about 15 to 20 minutes longer, until the topping has browned and the squash is fork-tender.
2904b06a-c02d-4464-8789-02222cc47ef0 Toss prepared vegetables together in a glass or ceramic bowl (non-reactive container).
2904b06a-c02d-4464-8789-02222cc47ef0 In a small bowl with the lemon juice, drizzle olive oil while whisking, to emulsify the liquids. Add to vegetables; cover and refrigerate for an hour.
2904b06a-c02d-4464-8789-02222cc47ef0 Add cooked, cooled rice; add salt and pepper to taste.
2904b06a-c02d-4464-8789-02222cc47ef0 To toast almonds, put them in a dry skillet over medium heat. Cook, stirring and turning constantly, just until lightly browned and aromatic.
2904b06a-c02d-4464-8789-02222cc47ef0 Top with toasted almonds.
2904b06a-c02d-4464-8789-02222cc47ef0 Refrigerate until serving time.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Heat the oven to 350 F. Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish or spray it with nonstick cooking spray.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Trim the green beans; place them in a strainer or colander and rinse with cold water.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Set the Instant Pot to sauté (normal level). Add the shallots and garlic and cook for about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Add the green beans to the pot along with the chicken stock, salt, and pepper.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Place the lid on the pot; lock it in place and set the vent to "sealing." Choose the manual setting, high pressure, and set the time for 4 minutes. When the time is up, do a quick release.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Strain the liquids into a bowl and return the solids to the pot. Add the cream of mushroom soup to the green beans and stir gently to combine. Reserve about 3 to 4 tablespoons of cheese for the topping and add the remaining cheese to the green beans. Stir the mixture, adding some of the reserved liquids to thin the sauce, if desired. Alternatively, for a richer sauce, add some light or heavy cream or a few tablespoons of sour cream. Taste and adjust the seasonings. Transfer the green bean mixture to the prepared baking dish.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Combine the French fried onions in a bowl with the panko breadcrumbs; toss with the 2 tablespoons of melted butter. Sprinkle the reserved shredded cheese over the green bean casserole filling and then sprinkle the buttered breadcrumbs and fried onions evenly over the cheese.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Bake the casserole in the preheated oven for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until the topping is golden brown and the casserole is hot. Transfer the casserole to a serving dish or serve it straight from the baking dish.
02cd7a54-f7b9-4e31-96af-0e116f62219f Enjoy this green bean casserole with an everyday family meal or holiday feast.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 Gather the ingredients.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 Cook the sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling salt water for 5 to 10 minutes. Drain well.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 In a large bowl, combine the soup and sour cream. Stir in the shredded carrot and mix thoroughly.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 Fold in the well-drained squash and onion.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 In a microwave-safe bowl, melt the butter, remove from microwave, and toss with the stuffing mix.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 Spread half of the stuffing in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish (about 1 1/2- to 2-quart size). Spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 Bake at 350 F until heated through, about 25 to 30 minutes.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 Remove it from the oven and serve the casserole hot.
d42a9397-7f60-4084-9004-8faa2f55d283 Enjoy!
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 Gather the ingredients.
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 Remove the stems from the mushrooms and discard them. Wipe the mushroom caps with damp paper towels and give them a quick rinse under cold running water. Pat dry.
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 Heat a covered grill to medium heat, or about 350 F.
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 Combine the butter, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, and freshly ground black pepper in a small saucepan. Place the saucepan over medium-low heatâ€”on the stovetop or on the grillâ€”and cook until the mixture is simmering and the garlic is aromatic. Remove the sauce from the heat and set aside.
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 If some of the mushrooms are very large, cut them in half or slice them into thick strips. Place the mushrooms on a plate or tray and brush them generously with the melted butter and garlic mixture.
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 On a covered grill over medium coals, grill the portobello mushrooms stem-side down for about 5 to 7 minutes, or until they are browned.
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 Turn the mushrooms and grill the tops for about 5 to 7 minutes longer, or until they are tender and nicely browned with some grill marks.
e07a8d0f-ad75-4a38-8431-2dcef4306021 Serve and enjoy!
a53a28fc-62d9-4a2b-afec-1aee4185235d Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 325 F.
a53a28fc-62d9-4a2b-afec-1aee4185235d Add the almond flour, coconut flour, salt, baking soda, eggs, and heavy cream to a mixing bowl. Whisk together until combined. Add in the melted butter and continue to mix together until all the ingredients are incorporated.
a53a28fc-62d9-4a2b-afec-1aee4185235d Generously grease a 9 or 10-inch cast iron skillet with butter.
a53a28fc-62d9-4a2b-afec-1aee4185235d Pour the batter into the greased skillet. Place it in the preheated oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and firm.
a53a28fc-62d9-4a2b-afec-1aee4185235d Allow the cornbread to cool for about five minutes and then slice. Serve with butter.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Gather the ingredients.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Heat the oven to 350 F. Generously butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Place the cubed squash, chopped onion, salt, and freshly ground black pepper in a large saucepan.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Add a small amount of water (about 1 inch). Cover and cook the squash until tender, stirring occasionally and adding more water if necessary.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Drain the squash and onions thoroughly.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Return to the pan and stir in the butter. Taste and adjust seasonings, adding more salt and pepper to your taste.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Stir the crumbled crackers into the squash mixture.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Turn the squash and cracker mixture into the prepared baking dish.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Pour the milk over the squash and then sprinkle with the cheese and chopped pecans or bread crumbs.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Bake uncovered in the preheated oven for 20 minutes, until the milk is absorbed and the squash casserole is bubbly.
1775484b-a8a0-4a00-b4ff-e1dd118a5f2f Serve hot and enjoy!
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Gather the ingredients.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Heat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas Mark 4. Grease and flour two 8 1/2-by-4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Wash, dry, and, shred the zucchini by hand using a box or Microplane grater or use the shredding disk of a food processor.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Put the zucchini in a mesh strainer or colander and press or squeeze it with your hands to get some of the excess liquid out. You should have approximately 2 cups of shredded zucchini.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the eggs, granulated sugar, and vegetable oil together.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Stir in the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, vanilla, and walnuts, mixing just until all ingredients are combined.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Add the drained zucchini. Mix well.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pans.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Bake the zucchini bread for 55 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center of a loaf comes out with little or no crumbs clinging to it.
fc530460-5b01-44b9-ab23-8b8a6c2a069f Cool, slice, and serve!
bef75712-1e5b-4907-9d34-a53e74b2e055 Place zucchini or summer squash and onions in a large non-reactive pot; add the salt and enough water to cover. Let stand for 2 hours. Pour the mixture into a colander; rinse well with cold water and drain thoroughly.
bef75712-1e5b-4907-9d34-a53e74b2e055 In a 2-quart saucepan, bring the vinegar to a boil; pour over the squash and onions. Let stand for 2 hours. Bring to a boil.
bef75712-1e5b-4907-9d34-a53e74b2e055 Meanwhile, prepare the jars and lids. Wash the jars and lids in hot, soapy water. Fill a large canner with water. Place a rack in the pan and add the jars. Bring to a gentle boil. Turn the heat down to low to keep the jars hot.
bef75712-1e5b-4907-9d34-a53e74b2e055 Put the lids in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a simmer; do not boil. Keep them hot in the barely simmering water until it's time to seal the jars.
bef75712-1e5b-4907-9d34-a53e74b2e055 Boil the squash for 5 minutes; pack the squash pickles into the hot sterilized jars leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Wipe the edges of the jar with a clean, damp paper towel and seal with the lid and screw-on bands. Do not overtighten. Process pint or quart jars in the boiling water bath for 10 minutes from 1 to 1,000 feet, 15 minutes from 1,001 to 6,000 feet, or 20 minutes above 6,000 feet in altitude. The water should be at least 1 inch above the tops of the jars. Add extra boiling water, if necessary.
341fd362-04b1-463f-9e1a-16a9bb63c5cd Gather the ingredients.
341fd362-04b1-463f-9e1a-16a9bb63c5cd Heat the oven to 350 F.
341fd362-04b1-463f-9e1a-16a9bb63c5cd Butter a 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
341fd362-04b1-463f-9e1a-16a9bb63c5cd In a large bowl, combine the mashed sweet potatoes with 1 cup of the brown sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, milk, and 1/2 cup of melted butter. Blend thoroughly and spoon the mixture into the prepared baking dish.
341fd362-04b1-463f-9e1a-16a9bb63c5cd In another bowl, combine the remaining 1/2 cup of brown sugar, the flour, the remaining 1/4 cup of melted butter, and the chopped pecans.
341fd362-04b1-463f-9e1a-16a9bb63c5cd Sprinkle the pecan topping mixture over the top of the sweet potato casserole.
341fd362-04b1-463f-9e1a-16a9bb63c5cd Bake the casserole for 35 to 40 minutes, until the filling is hot and the topping has browned. Serve and enjoy!
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 Gather the ingredients.
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 Lightly butter a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking pan. Heat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4).
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 In a large skillet over medium heat, cook the sausage, breaking it up and stirring frequently, until it is fully cooked and no longer pink. Remove the sausage to paper towels to drain.
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 Wipe out the skillet with a paper towel and place it over medium-low heat. Add the butter and heat until it has melted. Add the chopped onion and celery and cook, stirring, until the vegetables have softened, about 5 to 7 minutes.
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 In a large mixing bowl, toss the bread cubes with the herbs and seasonings.
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 Add the vegetables with the butter and the drained sausage; then add the chicken broth and stir until well moistened, but not mushy.
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 Pack gently into the prepared baking dish and cover it tightly with foil.
060a0d04-444c-43db-9873-9f505cf9d3e4 Bake for 25 minutes. Remove the foil and broil for about 3 to 4 minutes, or just until browned on top.
34cc6af1-8ccf-40a1-91fb-371bf3c8757c Gather the ingredients.
34cc6af1-8ccf-40a1-91fb-371bf3c8757c In a small saucepan, combine the vinegar, mustard, sugar, oil, celery seeds, and black pepper; stir to combine.
34cc6af1-8ccf-40a1-91fb-371bf3c8757c Place the saucepan over high heat and bring the mixture to a boil; remove from heat. Set aside to cool slightly.
34cc6af1-8ccf-40a1-91fb-371bf3c8757c Combine the chopped vegetables in a large bowl; toss with the warm dressing mixture.
34cc6af1-8ccf-40a1-91fb-371bf3c8757c Chill the salad thoroughly before serving and then toss again.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec Gather the ingredients and preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec Grease a 2 1/2- to 3-quart casserole dish.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec Cook the spaghetti in boiling salted water following the package directions. Drain well.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec In a large bowl, combine the cooked and drained spaghetti with 1 cup of cheddar cheese and 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec Add the diced turkey and pimientos.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec In a skillet or saute pan, melt butter and saute the mushrooms and onions until they are tender and most of the liquid has evaporated; add to the turkey mixture along with remaining ingredients. Taste and add salt and pepper, as needed. Gently stir to combine ingredients.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec Transfer the mixture to the prepared casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheddar and Parmesan cheeses.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec Cover the baking dish with a lid or foil and bake for about 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec If desired, place the casserole under the broiler (high heat) for about 4 to 6 minutes, or until the top is lightly browned.
8db3f40f-b1a3-43d7-97bc-62d3dd704dec Serve and enjoy!
959bcca5-ce17-4e9d-b372-086d923489ea In a Dutch oven or large saucepan over medium heat, brown the ground beef in the olive oil. Cook, stirring until the beef is no longer pink.
959bcca5-ce17-4e9d-b372-086d923489ea Add the chopped onion, pinto beans, corn, canned tomatoes, taco seasoning, ranch dressing, and water or beef stock to the ground beef.
959bcca5-ce17-4e9d-b372-086d923489ea Reduce the heat to low and simmer for about 1 hour.
959bcca5-ce17-4e9d-b372-086d923489ea When the soup is ready, top it with tortilla strips, and serve it in big soup bowls.
959bcca5-ce17-4e9d-b372-086d923489ea Serve with a simple tossed salad and hot baked cornbread wedges, if desired.
50906a82-7da8-4665-9999-0a9cba3621f3 Place whole unpeeled potatoes in a large saucepan or Dutch oven. Cover with salted water. Cover the pan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes can be pierced easily with a fork. Drain and let cool until easy to handle.
50906a82-7da8-4665-9999-0a9cba3621f3 Cut the cooled unpeeled potatoes into halves or quarters, depending onâ€‹ the size of potatoes. Chunks should be no larger than 1 inch.
50906a82-7da8-4665-9999-0a9cba3621f3 In a large bowl, combine potatoes with celery and remaining ingredients. Toss to blend. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
a766d5b8-e344-4d7f-acab-52d43e5ff4a9 Gather the ingredients.
a766d5b8-e344-4d7f-acab-52d43e5ff4a9 In a large jar or medium bowl, combine the mayonnaise, 3 to 4 tablespoons of the sugar, the vinegar, celery seed, Creole seasoning, and black pepper. Whisk to blend or cover the jar and shake it until well blended.
a766d5b8-e344-4d7f-acab-52d43e5ff4a9 Toss with shredded or chopped cabbage and refrigerate for an hour or two before serving for best flavor.
a766d5b8-e344-4d7f-acab-52d43e5ff4a9 This dressing makes enough for about one medium head of cabbage. We like to add some grated carrot and onion or onion powder to the mixture, or you could use green cabbage with some shredded red cabbage (see the note about red cabbage and red onion in the Tips and Variations, below).
a766d5b8-e344-4d7f-acab-52d43e5ff4a9 Serve coleslaw with any summer meal, barbecued ribs, grilled chicken, burgers, or pulled pork, or use it to top shredded beef or chicken sandwiches. It is, of course, an essential side to serve with fried catfish or fish and chips!
5f9b18ad-c884-4455-ab6f-035151dd6b53 Gather the ingredients
5f9b18ad-c884-4455-ab6f-035151dd6b53 Heat the vegetable oil in a large, heavy, nonstick skillet or electric skillet over medium heat. Add the sliced onion and sauté until the onion is tender and translucent. Add the red bell pepper and garlic (if using), and cook for 1 minute longer.
5f9b18ad-c884-4455-ab6f-035151dd6b53 Add the diced potatoes, paprika, about 1/2 teaspoon salt, along with the freshly ground black pepper. Cover the pan and cook for about 10 to 15 minutes, or until potatoes are just tender. Uncover and increase the heat to medium-high. Continue cooking for about 8 to 10 minutes, occasionally turning, until the potatoes are golden brown.
5f9b18ad-c884-4455-ab6f-035151dd6b53 Taste and adjust the seasonings, adding more salt, if needed.
5f9b18ad-c884-4455-ab6f-035151dd6b53 Serve and enjoy.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Gather the ingredients.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Heat the oven to 425 F.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Line a 9-inch by 13-inch by 2-inch baking pan with foil; brush the foil lightly with a small amount of olive oil.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Scrub the potatoes. Peel, if desired, and then cut them into bite-sized pieces, about 1/2 inches to 3/4 inches big.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Peel the red onion and cut it into 1/2-inch pieces.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b In a large bowl or in a food storage bag, toss the potatoes and onion chunks with the olive oil, garlic, dill weed, chives, salt, and pepper.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Transfer the potato mixture to the baking pan and bake for 45 to 55 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Stir occasionally so the potatoes will brown evenly.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Let the potatoes cool completely.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, and lemon juice in a small bowl.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Toss the mayonnaise mixture with the potato mixture, adding more mayonnaise if needed.
088788b0-423d-4996-9970-8db5d56d9f2b Serve and enjoy!
ab47f445-38d5-4d93-9e85-fd99ecc4c672 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
ab47f445-38d5-4d93-9e85-fd99ecc4c672 Combine everything in a large bowl.
ab47f445-38d5-4d93-9e85-fd99ecc4c672 Spoon the mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
ab47f445-38d5-4d93-9e85-fd99ecc4c672 Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.
ab47f445-38d5-4d93-9e85-fd99ecc4c672 Serve and enjoy!
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Gather the ingredients.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Place a large skillet over medium heat. When the skillet is hot, add the bacon.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Cook until the bacon is browned and crisp, turning frequently.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Remove the bacon to a paper towel-lined plate to drain. Set aside.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Cook macaroni in boiling salted water following package directions.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Drain the macaroni in a colander, rinse with hot water, and set aside.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Heat oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4).
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Lightly grease a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa In a medium saucepan over medium heat, melt the 3 tablespoons of butter. Add the green onions and garlic powder. Cook, stirring, for about 1 minute.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Add the flour, to create the roux, and stir until well blended and smooth. Continue cooking, stirring, for 2 minutes.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Gradually add the milk and cook, stirring, until thickened. Stir in salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Set 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese aside and stir the remaining 1 1/2 cups of cheese into the sauce. Continue cooking and stirring until the cheese has melted.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Combine the cheese sauce with the drained macaroni and then spoon the mixture into the prepared baking dish.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Crumble the bacon and sprinkle it evenly over the top of the casserole.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Sprinkle the reserved 1/2 cup of shredded cheddar cheese over the bacon.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter. Put the breadcrumbs in a small bowl and drizzle the butter over them. Toss the breadcrumbs lightly to coat with the butter.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Sprinkle the crumbs over the cheese and bacon.
55bb5d5e-c731-4174-912d-eeb33bc128fa Bake the macaroni and cheese casserole for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly.
d3cf49f3-786e-475b-8461-eebaec4c42dc Gather ingredients.
d3cf49f3-786e-475b-8461-eebaec4c42dc Melt the butter in a saucepan over medium-low heat; remove from heat. Stir in the flour, salt, dry mustard, and pepper.
d3cf49f3-786e-475b-8461-eebaec4c42dc Put the saucepan back on the heat and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
d3cf49f3-786e-475b-8461-eebaec4c42dc Gradually add milk or light cream, stirring until well mixed.
d3cf49f3-786e-475b-8461-eebaec4c42dc Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth. Reduce the heat to low and simmer, stirring, for 5 minutes.
d3cf49f3-786e-475b-8461-eebaec4c42dc Add the cheese and cook, stirring, until the cheese has melted and the sauce is smooth and well blended.
d3cf49f3-786e-475b-8461-eebaec4c42dc Serve with pasta or vegetables and enjoy.
5fee7c49-f890-4742-9516-a992b62fdbd0 Gather the ingredients.
5fee7c49-f890-4742-9516-a992b62fdbd0 In a bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, dried dill, salt, pepper, and onion. Stir to blend.
5fee7c49-f890-4742-9516-a992b62fdbd0 Cover and refrigerate the sour cream dressing until serving time.
5fee7c49-f890-4742-9516-a992b62fdbd0 Serve the sour cream and dill dressing with the sliced tomatoes or serve it along with fish, cucumbers, or a tossed salad. It's especially nice with salmon or with a salad with grilled salmon.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Gather the ingredients.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Boil squash whole until just tender; about 6 minutes.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Drain and carefully split the squash lengthwise.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Using a spoon, scoop out pulp, taking care not to break the outer shells.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Set pulp aside. Place squash shells in a baking dish.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook sausage with onion. Add salt and pepper to taste; remove from heat.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Add squash pulp, bread crumbs, and seasoned salt. Add a little water if the mixture is too dry.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Stuff squash shells with the sausage mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
298dd8ca-f15b-46f2-8cdc-2296e1dae4f2 Bake at 375 F for 15 to 20 minutes, or until hot and browned.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d Gather the ingredients.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d Remove liver from giblets and refrigerate.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d Place the remaining giblets into a saucepan and cover with 4 cups cold water; bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low and simmer the giblets for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add the liver to the saucepan and simmer for another 30 minutes.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d Place a mesh strainer or colander over a bowl. Drain the giblets and set the liquids aside to use in the gravy, if needed. Let the giblets cool. Remove the meat from the neck and chop with the rest of the meat.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d Melt the butter in a heavy saucepan and stir in the flour. Cook and stir for 3 to 5 minutes, or until the roux just barely begins to turn golden.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d If you don't have drippings from a roasted turkey or chicken, or if you only have a small amount, add the giblet broth or chicken or turkey stock to make 2 cups. Slowly stir in the drippings and/or broth into the roux. Add the milk or half-and-half. Continue cooking and stirring until thickened.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d Taste and season the gravy with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.
e5a5b01f-b44b-40a0-9e8b-06b828d2bf2d Stir in the chopped hard-cooked eggs and chopped giblets and serve. Enjoy!
67791592-4ce5-4dd5-8721-ffafbfa3ca92 Gather the ingredients.
67791592-4ce5-4dd5-8721-ffafbfa3ca92 Bake or fry the bacon until somewhat crisp.
67791592-4ce5-4dd5-8721-ffafbfa3ca92 Drain on paper towels and then dice or crumble.
67791592-4ce5-4dd5-8721-ffafbfa3ca92 Separate the broccoli crowns into small florets and put in a large bowl.
67791592-4ce5-4dd5-8721-ffafbfa3ca92 Add the chopped red onion, raisins, and bacon to the broccoli and toss to mix.
67791592-4ce5-4dd5-8721-ffafbfa3ca92 Combine the mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar in a small bowl.
67791592-4ce5-4dd5-8721-ffafbfa3ca92 Add to the broccoli mixture. Toss to coat the broccoli with the dressing. For maximum flavor, refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.
927c678e-9667-4ea4-93fe-cd68d87969bd In large bowl, combine squash, onion, carrot, and soup.
927c678e-9667-4ea4-93fe-cd68d87969bd Mix sour cream and flour; stir into vegetables.
927c678e-9667-4ea4-93fe-cd68d87969bd Toss stuffing crumbs with butter and place half in slow cooker.
927c678e-9667-4ea4-93fe-cd68d87969bd Add vegetable mixture and top with remaining stuffing crumbs.
927c678e-9667-4ea4-93fe-cd68d87969bd Cover and cook on LOW for 6 to 8 hours.
1b56dfeb-5ef9-4f23-8922-9c54dfd77bd3 Gather the ingredients.
1b56dfeb-5ef9-4f23-8922-9c54dfd77bd3 In a bowl, combine the cooked shrimp, diced celery, diced cucumber, dill weed, lemon juice, mayonnaise, and sour cream, to taste.
1b56dfeb-5ef9-4f23-8922-9c54dfd77bd3 Add salt and pepper, to taste.
1b56dfeb-5ef9-4f23-8922-9c54dfd77bd3 Stir gently to combine thoroughly. Chill until serving time.
1b56dfeb-5ef9-4f23-8922-9c54dfd77bd3 This shrimp salad is great served as-is on lettuce or serve it as a sandwich filling in soft rolls or buns.
474aa920-1983-436d-a0e9-b3bee5aedb5b Gather the ingredients.
474aa920-1983-436d-a0e9-b3bee5aedb5b Center the roast in the pot of your slow cooker. Line the sides with carrots and new potatoes (or omit the vegetables if you choose).
474aa920-1983-436d-a0e9-b3bee5aedb5b Combine the condensed mushroom soup, water, and onion soup mix.
474aa920-1983-436d-a0e9-b3bee5aedb5b Pour the soup mixture over the pot roast and vegetables.
474aa920-1983-436d-a0e9-b3bee5aedb5b Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or until the meat and vegetables turn tender. Or cook on high for about 3 to 4 hours.
474aa920-1983-436d-a0e9-b3bee5aedb5b Remove the meat and vegetables to a platter and cover to keep warm until serving. If desired, spoon some of the liquid from the bottom of the crock pot onto the meat and vegetables, or use the pan juices to make gravy to serve with the pot roast.
474aa920-1983-436d-a0e9-b3bee5aedb5b Serve and enjoy.
cf20c150-59cf-42ce-af89-8a42ddab0fae Gather the ingredients.
cf20c150-59cf-42ce-af89-8a42ddab0fae Scrub the beets and rinse well. Trim the beets, leaving the rootlets intact and about 1 inch of the tops.
cf20c150-59cf-42ce-af89-8a42ddab0fae Place a beet on a square of foil and drizzle with about 1/2 teaspoon of olive oil; rub the oil over the surface of the beet. Bring the corners of the foil up around the beet and twist to seal. Repeat with the remaining beets.
cf20c150-59cf-42ce-af89-8a42ddab0fae Put the wrapped beets in the slow cooker. Cover, and cook on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours, or until the beets are tender. Remove from the slow cooker with tongs and place on a heatproof platter with a lip to catch any juices.
cf20c150-59cf-42ce-af89-8a42ddab0fae When they're cool enough to handle, remove the foil. Trim top and roots and slip the skins off. Use in a recipe or slice and eat!
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc Gather the ingredients.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc Preheat oven to 400 F. Prepare a 9 x 9-inch baking dish or pan with cooking spray or butter and flour.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc In a large bowl, sift together the flour, cornmeal, baking powder, and salt.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc In a separate bowl or measuring cup, combine the half and half, eggs, melted butter, and honey and sugar if using.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc Add the liquid ingredients to the dry and mix just until the flour is moistened, no more than 10 to 15 seconds. The batter should be visibly lumpy; do not overmix.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc Pour the batter into your prepared pan and bake the cornbread immediately.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean and the edge of the bread starts to pull away from the pan.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc Cool for about 10 minutes, then remove â€‹it from the pan. Let it cool for 5 more minutes on a rack, and serve as soon as possible.
41bed2b8-0be1-47f1-a64d-4e5255d3e4dc Enjoy!
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Rinse the squash well and then pat dry with paper towels. Cut off and discard the ends of the squash. Slice the squash into 1/2-inch rounds.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Peel the onion. Cut off and discard the root end. Cut the onion in half and chop it finely
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Combine the sliced squash and chopped onion in a large saucepan. Cover the vegetables with water and add 1 teaspoon of kosher salt.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Place the saucepan over high heat and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover the pan, and cook for about 15 minutes, or until the squash is very tender.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Preheat the oven to 350 F.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Butter a 2-quart baking dish or casserole.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Drain the squash and onions thoroughly and transfer them to a bowl; mash well. Taste and add seasoned salt and pepper, as desired.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f In a medium bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk, flour, and 3 tablespoons of melted butter. Add the cheese and stir until well blended.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Combine the egg and milk mixture with the mashed squash mixture.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Spoon the mixture into the prepared baking dish.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Bake the squash casserole for about 30 minutes.
b195aa75-dcae-4ccd-a9d1-3df6fb1a6d0f Combine the breadcrumbs with the remaining butter and sprinkle them over the top of the casserole. Return the casserole to the oven and bake for about 10 minutes longer.
f8344432-772a-46ab-98b4-dd0c01b4110c Gather the ingredients.
f8344432-772a-46ab-98b4-dd0c01b4110c Heat oven to 350 F.
f8344432-772a-46ab-98b4-dd0c01b4110c Spray a 2 1/2- to 3-quart casserole dish with cooking spray.
f8344432-772a-46ab-98b4-dd0c01b4110c Combine the noodles, soup, peas, cheese, tuna, and milk. Add salt and freshly ground black pepper. Spoon into the prepared baking dish.
f8344432-772a-46ab-98b4-dd0c01b4110c In a small bowl, toss the breadcrumbs with the melted butter and sprinkle over the top of the casserole.
f8344432-772a-46ab-98b4-dd0c01b4110c Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until hot and bubbly and the breadcrumbs are browned.
f8344432-772a-46ab-98b4-dd0c01b4110c Serve and enjoy.
1ca1fd6c-4889-42d4-af14-26f907731130 Gather the ingredients.
1ca1fd6c-4889-42d4-af14-26f907731130 Combine the flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl.
1ca1fd6c-4889-42d4-af14-26f907731130 Cut in the butter and parsley (if using) until blended using a fork.
1ca1fd6c-4889-42d4-af14-26f907731130 Stir in the milk to form a wet dough. It should be a thick dough but thin enough to drop from a wet spoon.
1ca1fd6c-4889-42d4-af14-26f907731130 Heat the stew until it is simmering. Drop spoonfuls of the soft dough onto the simmering stew. Try to drop the dumplings on top of the vegetables so they won't sink too far into the liquid.
1ca1fd6c-4889-42d4-af14-26f907731130 Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes and then cover the pan tightly and cook for about 10 minutes longer (20 minutes total). Stir a few times to keep the stew from scorching.
1ca1fd6c-4889-42d4-af14-26f907731130 Serve and enjoy.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Gather the ingredients.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Gather your tools.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Dice the bacon strips into 1-inch pieces.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Peel the onion and chop it coarsely; set aside.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 In a large Dutch oven or deep sauté pan that has a cover, cook the diced bacon until it is fully cooked but not crisp.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 With a slotted spoon, remove the bacon pieces to paper towels to drain; set aside. Leave about 2 tablespoons of the bacon drippings in the pot.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Add the chopped onion to the bacon drippings and cook over medium heat until tender and lightly browned, stirring frequently. This step will take about 4 to 5 minutes.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Coarsely chop the cabbage.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Add the chopped cabbage to the browned onions and add 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Cover the pot tightly and reduce the heat to low. Simmer for 15 minutes.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Add more broth or water, as needed, and cook for about 5 to 10 minutes longer, or until the cabbage is tender.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Add the bacon pieces and stir. Heat through and serve.
3a776c18-41d6-4ae7-8836-931f6f0797c3 Enjoy!
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Gather the ingredients.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Preheat the oven to 350 F (180 C / Gas 4).
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Grease an 8-inch or 9-inch square baking pan or 2-quart casserole.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Cook the macaroni in boiling salted water following the package directions.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Drain well.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Return the pasta to the pot and add the butter; stir until melted.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Add 2 cups of the shredded cheese. Taste and add salt and pepper, as needed.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 In a medium bowl, whisk eggs with the milk.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Add the milk mixture to the macaroni; stir until thoroughly combined.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Spoon the pasta and cheese mixture into the prepared casserole or baking pan.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup cheese over the top along with paprika, if using.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Bake the macaroni and cheese (uncovered) for 30 minutes, or until the cheese has melted and browned and casserole is cooked through.
071b04c4-048d-41e4-9aa7-c6279f285377 Serve and enjoy!
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 Gather the ingredients.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 Peel the peaches, remove the stone, and roughly chop the fruits into small chunks. You will need a minimum of two cups for this recipe. Ripe peaches will be easy to peel with a sharp knife. If you are struggling to remove the skin, cut a small cross in the base of the peach, pop the peach into the microwave, and heat on high for 30 seconds.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 Place the chopped peaches into a large glass bowl and press lightly with a potato masher to release some of the juice and squish the peaches pieces a little; be careful not to over press, there should still be some lovely chunks of fruit. Set aside.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 Place the sugar into a microwavable bowl and heat on high for 1 1/2 minute. The sugar will become hot so be careful when handling. Heating the sugar this way helps it to dissolve in the jam more quickly and prevent the jam from being grainy.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 Add the warmed sugar to the peaches and stir through and continue to stir until the sugar dissolves. Taste, and if the jam is still grainy, then pop the jam into the microwave and heat on high for one minute at a time, and taste again. You should not need to do this more than three times if you have heated the sugar beforehand.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 Add the liquid pectin to the jam and stir through, finally add the lemon juice, stir again then cover the bowl with a tea cloth, leave to go completely cold then place into the refrigerator for 24 hours.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 The next day, wash three one-pound glass jars in hot soapy water and dry them carefully if you are canning your jam. Otherwise, use freezer bags.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 Fill the jars leaving a one-inch gap at the top, clean the rim with a damp cloth before covering with a lid. You should fill two comfortably and any leftover can go into the third jar that can be kept in the fridge and used within three weeks. If using freezer bags, portion the jam into the bags, do not overfill, seal and freeze.
74ab41c2-fd33-461a-9101-19936470b5c8 To defrost jars of freezer jam, do not rush this process, remove from the freezer and leave in the refrigerator until defrosted, this will not take more than 24 hours (freezer bag swill defrost much faster). Never put the frozen jars in the microwave to speed up the process.
f45b0405-0161-4b74-8161-2210afd533af Gather the ingredients.
f45b0405-0161-4b74-8161-2210afd533af Combine the sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl, and blend thoroughly.
f45b0405-0161-4b74-8161-2210afd533af Pour it into a small canning jar with a screw top, another small lidded container, or a zip-close food storage bag. Use as desired. Enjoy.
a8d0b0ed-7425-4789-baa1-a38a64ca7a8b Gather the ingredients.
a8d0b0ed-7425-4789-baa1-a38a64ca7a8b Peel the apples, if desired. Core them and then dice them or slice them into thin, uniform wedges. Alternatively, slice the cored apples crosswise to make thin circles.
a8d0b0ed-7425-4789-baa1-a38a64ca7a8b Melt the butter in a heavy skillet or sauté pan over medium heat.
a8d0b0ed-7425-4789-baa1-a38a64ca7a8b When the butter has melted and begins to foam, add the chopped or sliced apples, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and 2 tablespoons of water.
a8d0b0ed-7425-4789-baa1-a38a64ca7a8b Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently, or until the apples are tender and the sugar mixture has become syrupy. Some varieties of apples hold their shape better than others. Add more water to the pan if necessary.
a8d0b0ed-7425-4789-baa1-a38a64ca7a8b Serve over pancakes, ice cream, or inside of crepes, and enjoy!
23d1e60c-29a2-49ee-8ad0-a4a2b4b4eb37 Put potatoes in a medium saucepan and cover with water. Add about 1 teaspoon of kosher salt for each quart of water. Bring the potatoes to a boil, reduce heat to low, and cover the pan. Simmer the potatoes for about 15 minutes, or just until the chunks are fork-tender. Drain and set them aside to cool.
23d1e60c-29a2-49ee-8ad0-a4a2b4b4eb37 Chop the hard-boiled eggs and put them in a large serving bowl.
23d1e60c-29a2-49ee-8ad0-a4a2b4b4eb37 Add the chopped red onion and celery to the eggs.
23d1e60c-29a2-49ee-8ad0-a4a2b4b4eb37 Peel the cucumber and slice it in half lengthwise. Scrape the seeds out with a spoon and then dice the cucumber. Add the diced cucumber to the bowl with the vegetables and eggs.
23d1e60c-29a2-49ee-8ad0-a4a2b4b4eb37 Add the cooled potatoes to the bowl with the vegetables.
23d1e60c-29a2-49ee-8ad0-a4a2b4b4eb37 In another bowl, combine the sour cream, 3/4 cup of mayonnaise, and about 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoons of salt and the pepper; stir to blend.
23d1e60c-29a2-49ee-8ad0-a4a2b4b4eb37 Add the dressing mixture to the potato mixture and toss gently to blend and coat with the dressing. Add more mayonnaise, if needed, to taste.
9202ff9c-188b-4b0f-b4b5-76870ed3c84e Gather the ingredients.
9202ff9c-188b-4b0f-b4b5-76870ed3c84e In a heavy skillet, heat butter over medium-low heat until foamy.
9202ff9c-188b-4b0f-b4b5-76870ed3c84e Add the fresh corn kernels; cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
9202ff9c-188b-4b0f-b4b5-76870ed3c84e Lower the heat if necessary to keep the butter from burning and stir.
9202ff9c-188b-4b0f-b4b5-76870ed3c84e Sprinkle with the salt and pepper. Taste and adjust seasoning, and add about 1 teaspoon of sugar if desired. Enjoy!
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Gather the ingredients.
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4. Butter bottom and sides of 2-quart baking dish.
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Arrange half of the dressing in the bottom of the prepared baking dish.
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Add half of the turkey then top with half of the gravy.
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Repeat the layers.
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Top with cubes of cranberry sauce.
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
4a6c224b-1158-4427-a541-ecf47d314e26 Serve and enjoy!
968fc2c4-a970-476b-9688-caa0f96e59d8 Gather the ingredients.
968fc2c4-a970-476b-9688-caa0f96e59d8 Cut the cucumbers and tomatoes into bite-sized pieces and place in a large bowl.
968fc2c4-a970-476b-9688-caa0f96e59d8 Add remaining ingredients and gently toss to combine the dressing ingredients with the cucumbers and tomatoes.
968fc2c4-a970-476b-9688-caa0f96e59d8 Make several hours or a day ahead, keeping in the refrigerator until shortly before serving time.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Gather the ingredients.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Preheat oven to 425 F.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Grease a 9-inch square baking pan or iron skillet.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt, and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 In another bowl, whisk together the buttermilk and eggs; stir in the cream-style corn and melted butter.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Stir the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients just until blended.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Spoon into the prepared baking pan or iron skillet.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown and the cornbread springs back when lightly touched with a finger.
6a139945-35a3-464a-aadc-190b8d2acf25 Enjoy!
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Gather the ingredients. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and set aside. Preheat oven to 350 F.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d In a large bowl, beat the eggs until thick. Gradually beat in the sugar.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d In another bowl, combine the melted butter with flour, cocoa, vanilla, sweetened flaked coconut, and pecans.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Add the chocolate mixture to egg and sugar mixture. Stir well to combine.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 30 minutes or until a skewer inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Remove the cake from the oven. Immediately spread marshmallow fluff gently on the surface of the warm cake.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Prepare the frosting. In a medium bowl, combine the melted butter, cocoa powder, vanilla extract, and milk. Stir in the powdered sugar.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Spread the frosting gently over the warm marshmallow crème, swirling to give a marbled effect.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Sprinkle the chopped pecans over the top.
79e11588-29b3-4a55-b3b3-e87185e5b10d Cut into squares to serve.
e7a1a4aa-1430-4338-92f9-9acd9d8430ff Gather the ingredients.
e7a1a4aa-1430-4338-92f9-9acd9d8430ff Peel the ripe and sweet peaches and then slice them thinly.
e7a1a4aa-1430-4338-92f9-9acd9d8430ff Place them in a plastic ziplock bag and freeze the peaches for 3 to 4 hours or until completely frozen. Try to place the peaches in an even, flat layer in the bag and place them flat on a freezer shelf so they can be broken up and put in the blender easily.
e7a1a4aa-1430-4338-92f9-9acd9d8430ff Pour the lemonade (water can also be substituted) into a measuring cup. Add the 1 cup of sugar and 1 tablespoon of freshly squeezed lemon juice. Stir the mixture until the sugar dissolves somewhat.
e7a1a4aa-1430-4338-92f9-9acd9d8430ff Pour the lemonade mixture into a blender and then add the frozen peach pieces. If the frozen peaches formed a kind of block, break it up into smaller pieces before adding it to the blender. Blend on high until smooth.
e7a1a4aa-1430-4338-92f9-9acd9d8430ff You can eat it immediately as a a kind of soft serve sorbet or place it in a loaf pan, cover in plastic wrap, and freeze. Freeze the peach sorbet for at least 5 hours or until completely frozen. You can even freeze it overnight if you want to be sure it is completely frozen.
e7a1a4aa-1430-4338-92f9-9acd9d8430ff Scoop and serve the sorbet when you are ready to eat!
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Gather the ingredients.
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. In the bowl of a food processor fitted with the S-shaped (sabatier) blade, combine 3/4 cup of the chilled butter, powdered sugar, and salt. Process until moist clumps begin to form.
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Add the flour and egg, and pulse just until a dough forms
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Press the dough onto bottom and 3/4 inch up the sides of a 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Bake until the crust is golden brown, about 22 minutes. Allow the crust to cool slightly on a wire rack. Maintain the oven temperature as you proceed through the next steps.
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 In a large saucepan, bring the brown sugar, honey, and remaining 3/4 cup of butter to a boil, stirring frequently. Boil for 2 minutes.
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Remove the saucepan from the heat and add the vanilla extract. (The mixture will bubbly slightly when the vanilla is added.)
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Add the pecans and stir to coat completely.
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Pour the pecan filling onto prepared crust, spreading it out evenly. Return the pan to the 375 degree oven. Bake until filling thickens and bubbles all over, about 20 minutes.
d8480177-b831-4afd-a36d-bf039a64b124 Allow to cool completely on a wire rack. Cut into 2-inch squares.
7e677662-bc08-44f6-a83d-c5972dceec94 Heat oven to 325 F.
7e677662-bc08-44f6-a83d-c5972dceec94 Butter an 11 by 7-inch baking dish.
7e677662-bc08-44f6-a83d-c5972dceec94 In a large bowl, combine the sliced apples, raspberries, blueberries, and granulated sugar. Toss to coat. Transfer the apple and berry mixture to the prepared baking dish. Dot with small pieces of cold butter.
7e677662-bc08-44f6-a83d-c5972dceec94 In a medium bowl combine the melted butter with the brown sugar, flour, salt, baking soda, and rolled oats. Sprinkle the crumb mixture evenly over fruit.
7e677662-bc08-44f6-a83d-c5972dceec94 Bake this fruit and berry crisp in the preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes, or until fruit is tender and topping is browned.
7e677662-bc08-44f6-a83d-c5972dceec94 Serve the apple berry crisp warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or drizzle the crisp with heavy cream, or serve it cold or at room temperature with whipped cream or whipped topping. Store leftovers in the refrigerator.
ef65eef9-0ae9-4b65-a183-70f36c167a62 Cut the challah, or other egg bread such as brioche, into 1-inch cubes. This is a great use of stale bread. Although you can use fresh bread as is, stale bread will absorb the liquid better. If your bread is fresh, lightly toast the cubes by spreading them out on a baking sheet and placing them in a 350 F oven for 10 minutes. You can also leave them on the counter overnight.
ef65eef9-0ae9-4b65-a183-70f36c167a62 In a large bowl, whisk together the sugar, unsweetened cocoa powder, ground cinnamon, salt, whole milk, heavy cream, eggs, and vanilla.
ef65eef9-0ae9-4b65-a183-70f36c167a62 Fold in the bread cubes and chocolate chips and allow the mixture to sit for about half an hour for the bread to absorb some of the liquid.
ef65eef9-0ae9-4b65-a183-70f36c167a62 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
ef65eef9-0ae9-4b65-a183-70f36c167a62 Butter a medium sized baking dish (approximately 10" x 7") and pour in the bread mixture and all the unabsorbed liquid. Note that it will puff as it bakes and then slightly deflate when it cools down after baking.
ef65eef9-0ae9-4b65-a183-70f36c167a62 Place on a baking sheet to catch any drips and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until the mixture is set.
ef65eef9-0ae9-4b65-a183-70f36c167a62 Make the topping by melting the chocolate chips in the microwave for a few seconds and stirring in the heavy cream until smooth. Pour over the top of the bread pudding and serve warm or at room temperature.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Gather the ingredients.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Pour the apple cider into a saucepan and bring it to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to medium and boil until it is reduced to 1/4 cup, about 15 minutes. Set the concentrated boiled cider aside to cool.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt. Stir or whisk to blend thoroughly and set aside.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a In another bowl, whisk the buttermilk and eggs together until well blended. Whisk in the melted butter and vanilla extract.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Add the wet mixture to the dry ingredients and mix to form a soft, well-blended dough. You can use a stand mixer with paddle attachment for this step or mix by hand.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper; sprinkle liberally with flour. With floured hands, pat the dough out onto the parchment paper to a thickness of about 3/8-inch to 1/2-inch. Transfer the baking sheet to the freezer for about 15 minutes, until firm and well chilled. Alternatively, refrigerate the dough for about 1 hour.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Meanwhile, pour about 2 to 3 inches of vegetable oil into a Dutch oven or large, heavy saucepan. Attach a deep-fry thermometer to the pan and heat the oil to 350 F.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Remove the dough from the refrigerator or freezer and transfer it to a floured work surface. Cut the donuts out with a 3-inch doughnut cutter. Dip it into flour between cutting out the dough to keep the dough from sticking. Separate the donuts from the doughnut holes. Re-roll the dough as necessary and continue to cut out donuts until all of the dough is used.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a For the cinnamon sugar, combine the 1 cup of granulated sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon in a bowl and set aside.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Place paper towels on a baking sheet and set aside.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Using a metal spatula or skimmer, lower the about 3 to 4 donuts into the hot oil. Fry the donuts on one side for 1 minute and then turn them over and fry for about 1 minute longer, or until golden brown. Carefully remove the donuts to the paper towel-lined baking sheet to drain. Repeat with the remaining donuts; fry the donuts holes last; they will take a bit less time.
33ef33c1-ee71-4a08-a433-95dbcb40af1a Dip the donuts into the cinnamon-sugar mixture while they are still warm, coating them completely or just the tops.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Gather the ingredients.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Line baking sheets with wax paper.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Spread a thick layer of peanut butter on a cracker. Gently press another cracker onto the peanut butter layer to make a sandwich cookie. Repeat with the remaining crackers.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Melt the almond bark or candy melts in a microwave oven or in the top of a double boiler over simmering water as directed on the package.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Dip each sandwich cookie in the melted chocolate or almond bark. With a fork, lift the cookie out and shake gently to let the excess drip off.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Place the cookies on the wax paper-lined pan.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Before the chocolate sets, sprinkle the treats with colorful decorating sugar or candy sprinkles. Refrigerate until firm.
8e24610b-a497-4021-a27a-de4c736ada39 Serve and enjoy!
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Gather the ingredients.
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Peel the banana and slice lengthwise.
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Melt brown sugar and butter in a small saucepan.
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Add the banana and sauté until tender.
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Sprinkle with the ground cinnamon. Add the banana liqueur and rum. Gently warm the alcohol and coat the bananas in the sauce.
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Ignite the sauce with a flame.
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Baste the bananas in the liquid until the flame burns out.
1233e95a-8941-4288-b82a-516667aafd03 Serve the bananas foster immediately with a scoop of ice cream, and enjoy.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Grease your bundt pan with cooking spray. Pour the 1/2 cup of melted butter into the bottom of the pan and sprinkle the 1/2 cup of brown sugar evenly over the butter.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Prepare the pineapple by cutting the peeled fruit into rings and coring each ring. Cut each ring in half. Lay the curved edge of each half ring into the indentations of the bundt pan. Place the maraschino cherries in between each piece of pineapple. You may need more or fewer maraschino cherries and pineapple rings depending on the shape of your bundt pan.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Preheat the oven to 350 F. Place the oven rack on the lower middle part of the oven. Cream together the 1/2 cup of butter and 1 1/2 cups of sugar in the bowl of a stand mixer with the whisk attachment until creamy, about 10 minutes on medium-high speed.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Beat in the 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla until fluffy.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Sift together the dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Add the dry ingredients alternately with the 1 1/4 cup of milk to the creamed mixture in your stand mixer. Beat after each addition and scrape down the sides of the bowl as needed.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Pour the cake batter over the prepared bundt pan.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Place the pan in the preheated oven and bake for about 40 minutes, or until edges are bubbly and a toothpick comes out of the cake cleanly.
24878912-f7fe-41df-add7-5d6990c5e92d Remove the cake from the oven and allow it to cool for 15 minutes in the cake pan. Then flip the cake onto your chosen serving platter and serve while it is still warm.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 Gather the ingredients.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 Spray doughnut pans with nonstick cooking or baking spray.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 In a medium bowl, combine the flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt. Blend thoroughly with a whisk or spoon.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 In a large mixing bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk, melted butter, 2 teaspoons of orange zest and 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla extract.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 Add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture along with the finely chopped cranberries. Mix just until the ingredients are moistened.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 Spoon the batter into the cavities of the doughnut pans, filling about half full. Alternatively, spoon the batter into a plastic food storage bag, cut off a small piece of the corner and pipe the batter into the pan.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 Bake the doughnuts for about 10 to 12 minutes (about 7 to 9 minutes for mini doughnuts), or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into a doughnut.
f619bd23-6d2a-4739-a44a-37de91f9be48 Let the doughnuts cool for about 5 minutes and then carefully remove them to a rack to cool completely.
071bdcb4-c8d9-45da-8e1d-91f55dd75337 Heat the oven to 350° F.
071bdcb4-c8d9-45da-8e1d-91f55dd75337 Combine flour and confectioners' sugar in mixing bowl. Add melted butter and mix to blend well. Pat the dough out into a 12-inch or 14-inch pizza pan. Bake the crust for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
071bdcb4-c8d9-45da-8e1d-91f55dd75337 In a medium bowl with an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, and vanilla. Spread over the cooled pizza crust.
071bdcb4-c8d9-45da-8e1d-91f55dd75337 In a large saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; stir in water. Cook, constantly stirring, over medium heat until thickened. Add blueberries and cool completely.
071bdcb4-c8d9-45da-8e1d-91f55dd75337 Spread cooled blueberry mixture over cream cheese layer. Chill thoroughly.
071bdcb4-c8d9-45da-8e1d-91f55dd75337 Cut wedge-shaped portions for serving. Top each wedge with a generous dollop of whipped cream or whipped topping and fresh blueberries or strawberry slices, if desired.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Gather the ingredients.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4).
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Butter an 8-inch square baking dish.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 In a mixing bowl, combine the brown sugar, flour, oats, melted butter, and cinnamon.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Mix the ingredients until crumbly.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Press half of the brown sugar and oat mixture into the prepared baking dish.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Top with the sliced or diced rhubarb pieces.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 In a saucepan, combine 1 cup of granulated sugar, cornstarch, and the 1 cup of water and vanilla.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Cook together, stirring, until the mixture is thickened and clear.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Pour the thickened syrup mixture over the rhubarb in the baking dish.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Top the rhubarb filling evenly with the remaining crumb mixture.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Bake the rhubarb crisp in the preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes, or until the topping is browned and the filling is bubbling.
d23f3c93-b5e8-4db3-b507-36f31c1113d9 Enjoy your dessert drizzled with cream or top it with a big scoop of ice cream.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 Gather the ingredients. Heat the oven to 350 F.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking pan.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 In a small bowl, lightly beat one large egg.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, combine the cake mix, butter, and the beaten egg. Beat on low speed until the butter is blended into the dry cake mix and the egg mixture and the crumbs begin to clump together. Stop mixing and pat the crumbs firmly into the bottom of the prepared baking pan.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the softened cream cheese until smooth. Add the confectioners' sugar and beat until the mixture is light and well blended. Beat in the remaining 3 large eggs. Continue beating until very smooth. Beat in the vanilla, if using.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 Pour the cream cheese batter over the first layer and spread to cover evenly.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 Bake the chess squares for 35 to 40 minutes, or until set and lightly browned.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 Cook on a rack and then cover the pan with foil or plastic wrap. Transfer the pan to the refrigerator to chill thoroughly before cutting. They are a little gooier if you cut them while they are still warm.
ce45dcb9-dd73-4c94-94f8-afed0aa359a2 This recipe makes about 24 (2-inch) bars. Store the bars in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
33de97a8-d974-40ce-8108-d45388fb5cc7 Gather the ingredients.
33de97a8-d974-40ce-8108-d45388fb5cc7 Place the granulated sugar, cocoa powder, flour, and salt in a medium-sized saucepan, along with 1/2 cup of the milk and whisk to combine into a thick paste.
33de97a8-d974-40ce-8108-d45388fb5cc7 Whisk in the remaining milk and bring the mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. This can take up to 10 minutes.
33de97a8-d974-40ce-8108-d45388fb5cc7 When the sauce comes to a boil, reduce the heat to low and simmer very gently for 5 minutes, whisking often. Remove from heat, add the vanilla extract, and let the sauce cool.
33de97a8-d974-40ce-8108-d45388fb5cc7 Store the sauce in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks, covered.
33de97a8-d974-40ce-8108-d45388fb5cc7 Warm the sauce in the microwave or on the stovetop, if desired, and enjoy!
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa Cut the butternut squash in half lengthwise; remove stem and scoop out the seeds.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa Place the squash, cut side down, on a foil-lined oiled baking pan; add about 1/2 cup of water to the pan. Cover loosely with foil and bake at 400 F for 45 to 55 minutes, or until the squash is tender and can be easily pierced with a fork.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa Let the squash cool completely; scoop out the flesh and then peel and mash or puree the squash or put it through a food mill. Measure 1 1/2 cups of the squash and set aside.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa Reduce oven temperature to 350 F and position an oven rack in the center of the oven.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the squash with the brown sugar. Add the eggs, evaporated milk, spices salt, flour, butter, and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa Pour the filling into the chilled pie crust and place on the center oven rack.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa Bake for 45 to 55 minutes, or until set. Check after about 35 minutes and loosely set a ring of foil or a pie crust protector over the browned crust, so it won't get too dark.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa When the filling is set, transfer the pie to a rack to cool.
c802df52-194b-4e7d-a066-c0e93f674aaa Serve just warm or at room temperature with a dollop of whipped topping or whipped cream.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 Gather the ingredients.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish or 9-inch pie plate. Heat the oven to 425 F.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 In a saucepan, combine 2/3 cup of granulated sugar and cornstarch, stir in water. Bring to a boil; stirring constantly, boil for 1 minute. Add blueberries and blend well.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 Pour blueberry mixture into the prepared baking dish or 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cinnamon and drizzle with 1 teaspoon melted butter.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, 2 tablespoons of sugar (if using), baking powder, and salt.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 Pour the milk and 3 tablespoons melted butter into a measuring cup; add to flour mixture all at once. Stir just until mixture is moistened and forms a soft dough.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 Drop spoonfuls of the dough onto the blueberries.
3cec1a2b-0bab-4a1f-af4e-ac3b3d75ea96 Bake the cobbler for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Gather the ingredients.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Heat the oven to 300 F.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Butter and flour a 10-inch tube cake pan.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed with an electric hand-held mixer.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Gradually add oil, beating until well-blended.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Gradually add sugar, beating well. Continue beating for about 5 minutes, or until very light and fluffy.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Mix just until blended after each addition.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Stir in lemon extract.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Spoon the batter into the prepared pan and spread evenly.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Bake in the preheated oven for 1 hour and 35 minutes to 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center of the cake comes out clean. The cake will pull away from the sides of the pan slightly.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Cool in pan on a wire rack for 15 minutes.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Remove from pan and place directly on â€‹a wire rack or invert onto a rack if using a 1-piece pan.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Combine glaze ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Brush lemon glaze on sides of cake and spoon glaze over top, a little at a time.
96627ccb-c177-44bd-ba3b-9caec169aaa6 Let cake cool completely before serving.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 Heat the oven to 325 F.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 Butter and flour an 8-inch or 9-inch square or round layer cake pan.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 In a small mixing bowl, combine 1/2 cup of brown sugar with 1/4 cup of all-purpose flour and the cinnamon. Stir to blend, then work in the 1/4 cup of softened butter with a fork or your fingers until the mixture feels crumbly. Set the streusel aside.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 In a medium bowl, combine the 1 1/2 cups of all-purpose flour with the baking powder and salt; blend thoroughly with a whisk or spoon, then set it aside.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the egg lightly and then beat in the sugar and the 1/3 cup of melted butter. Add the milk and vanilla and blend well. Stir in the flour and mix the batter on low speed until well-blended.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 Sprinkle the brown sugar streusel topping evenly over the batter.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 Bake the cake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 Partially cool it in the pan on a wire rack.
7a82e150-447e-49e5-ab69-5077fa6478f7 Cut the coffee cake into squares while it's still warm.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Gather the ingredients.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Peel and thinly slice the peaches and put them on paper towels to remove excess moisture. Set aside.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Grease a 9-inch springform pan. Heat oven to 350 F.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Combine the 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, soda, and salt; set aside.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the 4 ounces of softened butter with the granulated sugar and 1/4 cup of brown sugar. Beat for about 3 to 4 minutes.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Beat in the eggs until smooth.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Beat in sour cream and vanilla and almond extracts.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f With a mixer, on low speed, beat in the flour mixture just until blended.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan. Arrange the thinly sliced peaches evenly over the batter, overlapping where needed.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f In another bowl combine the brown sugar, 3/4 cup flour, cinnamon, and nutmeg, stirring with a fork until smooth.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Add the 5 tablespoons of melted butter and blend well with the fork.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Sprinkle the crumb mixture evenly over the peach slices.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until the cake is firm and top is browned.
503fa630-0e35-4c69-b3a5-842d2b24868f Let cool for about 10 minutes on a rack; remove the side of the pan and cool completely before slicing.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 Gather the ingredients.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 Lay a sheet of waxed paper or parchment paper on the countertop.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 Put the butterscotch chips in a medium microwave-safe bowl or container. Microwave at 50% power for about 3 to 5 minutes, or just until the butterscotch chips are melted.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 In a large bowl, mix the peanut butter, peanuts, melted butterscotch chips, and chow mein noodles, stirring gently to coat the noodles thoroughly.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 Drop teaspoons of the mixture onto the parchment paper. Let them stand at room temperature until set.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 Transfer candies to a container, separated by sheets of waxed paper.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 Cover and store in the refrigerator.
2c0a9220-5281-4e3f-88e5-fa59ea4475f5 Enjoy!
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Gather the ingredients.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Combine the graham cracker crumbs and melted butter and press into an 8 x 8-inch pan or glass dish and chill.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Add the powdered sugar and vanilla, then beat until smooth.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Whip the cream and fold into the cream cheese mixture.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Spoon the cream cheese mixture onto the chilled crust and spread it evenly.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Spoon the cherry pie filling evenly over the cream cheese layer.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Cover the dessert with wax paper or plastic and put it in the freezer.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Before it's entirely frozen, cut the dessert into squares and then return it to the freezer.
ae0381ae-4c4c-4d84-8533-bf61e994f96b Remove the dessert from the freezer about 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Gather the ingredients.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Heat the oven to 375 F. Butter a 9-inch square baking pan.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Combine the sliced apples, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon salt, water, and vanilla in a mixing bowl and toss.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Add the mixture to the prepared baking pan.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Dot apples with the pieces of butter.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac In a medium mixing bowl, combine the 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, and salt. Add the softened butter and beaten egg and beat until blended.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Using a tablespoon, drop the batter evenly over the apple filling mixture. If desired, sprinkle the batter with a cinnamon-sugar mixture.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until the apples are tender and crust is golden brown.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Serve the apple cobbler warm with a drizzling of heavy cream or a scoop of ice cream.
141802fa-5552-4155-9b42-2d70874a35ac Enjoy!
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Gather the ingredients.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Heat oven to 375 F.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Butter an 8-inch square baking dish.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Arrange diced rhubarb in the prepared baking dish.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Mix together the orange juice and cornstarch, then toss the rhubarb in it.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Then sprinkle with the 1 cup sugar and the cinnamon, and dot with the 1 tablespoon of cut up butter.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Combine melted butter with brown sugar.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Sift together the flour, salt, and baking soda; mix with oats.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Combine the flour-oat mixture with the brown sugar and melted butter mixture until well blended. With hands, spread the crumb mixture over rhubarb.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Bake for 40 minutes.
2d4a0891-fbbc-4896-a427-037778377cbd Serve warm, with ice cream or whipped topping.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Gather the ingredients.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Preheat oven to 350 F. Lightly grease a baking sheet or line it with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Cream the butter, peanut butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar until light.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Add the egg and mix until the batter is smooth and fluffy.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 In a separate bowl, blend the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt together well.
