2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Add the dry ingredients to the butter mixture. Stir until well blended
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Fold in the chocolate chips.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Drop the cookie dough by teaspoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheet.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set and lightly browned on the bottoms.
2482d4f6-c7bc-4f23-bca3-9bde534a9209 Serve and enjoy!
5b997753-147b-479f-a50a-f2ef82545a3a Heat the oven to 325 F. Lightly grease baking sheets or line with parchment paper or silicone baking mats.
5b997753-147b-479f-a50a-f2ef82545a3a In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter until creamy. Add the brown sugar and beat on high speed until light and fluffy. Stir in the vanilla.
5b997753-147b-479f-a50a-f2ef82545a3a With the mixer on low speed, gradually add the flour.
5b997753-147b-479f-a50a-f2ef82545a3a Fold in the chopped pecans.
5b997753-147b-479f-a50a-f2ef82545a3a Scoop portions of cookie dough with a tablespoon or small cookie scoop and shape each into a ball. Arrange the cookie dough balls on the prepared baking sheets about 2 1/2 inches apart.
5b997753-147b-479f-a50a-f2ef82545a3a Lightly grease the bottom of a glass or other small container with a flat bottom and dip it in granulated sugar, pourable brown sugar, or raw sugar. Press the bottom of the glass lightly on a cookie ball to flatten slightly. Redip the glass in sugar and repeat with the remaining balls of cookie dough.
5b997753-147b-479f-a50a-f2ef82545a3a Bake the cookies in the preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until they are firm and lightly browned on the bottoms.
ac8f97dc-491d-40ec-a86e-fcf6b95d7fa2 Gather the ingredients.
ac8f97dc-491d-40ec-a86e-fcf6b95d7fa2 In a large mixing bowl, combine the oats, chocolate chips, vanilla, and peanut butter, if using; stir to blend the ingredients. Set aside.
ac8f97dc-491d-40ec-a86e-fcf6b95d7fa2 In a saucepan, combine the butter with the milk and granulated sugar. Place the pan over medium-high heat and bring to a full rolling boil. Boil the mixture for 1 full minute.
ac8f97dc-491d-40ec-a86e-fcf6b95d7fa2 Combine the hot butter and sugar mixture with the oatmeal and chocolate chip mixture. Stir until the chocolate has melted and the mixture is well blended.
ac8f97dc-491d-40ec-a86e-fcf6b95d7fa2 Working quickly, drop by spoonfuls or cookie scoop onto waxed paper or parchment paper.
ac8f97dc-491d-40ec-a86e-fcf6b95d7fa2 Allow to cool and firm up.
ac8f97dc-491d-40ec-a86e-fcf6b95d7fa2 Serve and enjoy!
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Gather the cake ingredients.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Pre heat the oven to 325 F (165 C/Gas 3). Generously grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan. Make sure you get all the nooks and crannies of the Bundt cake pan.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 In a large bowl or the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, combine the flour, 2 cups of sugar, salt, baking powder and soda, the buttermilk, 1 cup of butter, 2 teaspoons of vanilla, and the eggs; beat on low speed until moistened. Increase the mixer speed to medium and beat for about 3 minutes longer.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Spoon the batter into the prepared cake pan and spread evenly.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Bake the cake in the preheated oven for 55 to 65 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Meanwhile, gather the glaze ingredients.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 In a small saucepan over low heat, combine the 3/4 cup of sugar, 1/3 cup of butter, 3 tablespoons of water, and 2 teaspoons of vanilla; cook, stirring, just until butter melts. Do not bring the mixture to a boil.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Remove the cake to a rack and (while it is still in the pan) pierce it all over with a fork or skewer.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Pour the hot butter glaze over the warm cake.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Let the cake stand 5 to 10 minutes, or until glaze is absorbed.
b21ae152-66a4-4ce2-acb2-2c8d3e2c7be3 Then carefully turn it out onto a cake plate and sprinkle with some confectioners' sugar, if you'd like.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Gather the ingredients.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Thoroughly combine the vanilla wafer crumbs, chopped pecans, 1 cup confectioners' sugar, and the cocoa powder.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 In a separate bowl, blend the bourbon and corn syrup.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Stir the bourbon mixture into the dry mixture. Stir and mix well with the help of a wooden or stainless steel spoon.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Cover the mixture and chill in the refrigerator for at least 2 to 3 hours.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Once the mixture is chilled and ready to be shaped, sift about 1/2 to 1 cup of confectioners' sugar into a wide, shallow bowl.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Place a bowl of cold water next to your working area. Wet your hands with cold water and shape small bits of the dough into balls. Roll them in the confectioners' sugar.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Serve right away, or store in the refrigerator in tightly covered containers for up to 2 weeks.
2f149ac1-f353-4a57-bb05-a12294ecc6e3 Enjoy!
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Gather the ingredients.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Preheat the oven to 300 F.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Combine the butter and sugar in the bowl of a stand mixer. Alternatively, use a hand mixer in a sturdy bowl.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Gradually stir flour into the creamed mixture until well blended. Use a paddle attachment for the stand mixer, or mix by hand with the help of a wooden spoon.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Once the mixture is well incorporated, use a small offset spatula to spread or pat it into the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. If you'd like a thicker shortbread, use a 9-inch square pan. Prick the dough all over with a fork. Alternatively, roll the dough out on a lightly floured surface and cut out with round or square cookie cutters.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Bake in the preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes until just lightly browned.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Remove from the oven and immediately cut into squares or rectangles. Cool completely before removing from pan. If using, dust with powdered sugar.
e0b1d400-eaa2-43af-933b-e718a50895ea Enjoy!
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Gather the ingredients.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Preheat the oven to 325 F/165 C/Gas Mark 3. Mix the pears with 1/2 cup of the sugar and let stand.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Put butter in a 2-quart baking dish and place in the oven until melted.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Combine the remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt in a mixing bowl. Mix well.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Whisk together the milk and egg in a separate small mixing bowl.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Slowly combine the milk and egg mixture with the dry ingredients to make a batter.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Pour the batter over the melted butter. Do not stir.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Spoon the sliced pears over the batter. Do not stir.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Bake in the preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until nicely browned and the pears are tender. If the topping appears to be over-browning, cover the dish with foil and continue baking until the pears are tender.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Remove the cobbler from the oven and set it on a rack to cool slightly.
c25669ed-3344-4f45-99ad-f5accce600fe Enjoy the cobbler hot or cold with a scoop of ice cream or whipped cream.
1bcd81e4-d90c-41c5-8290-7e19d5d4b792 With a wire whisk, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
1bcd81e4-d90c-41c5-8290-7e19d5d4b792 Whisk in eggs, milk and butter.
1bcd81e4-d90c-41c5-8290-7e19d5d4b792 Fold in peaches.
1bcd81e4-d90c-41c5-8290-7e19d5d4b792 Heat oil in fryer or pan to 375 degrees F.
1bcd81e4-d90c-41c5-8290-7e19d5d4b792 With a long-handled ladle, ladle about 1/4 -1/2 cup batter into hot oil. The batter will sink at first and then rise. Cook for about 2 - 3 minutes, depending on the size of fritters.
1bcd81e4-d90c-41c5-8290-7e19d5d4b792 Remove fritters from oil with long-handled tongs. Quickly drain on paper towels or newspaper.
1bcd81e4-d90c-41c5-8290-7e19d5d4b792 One by one, place each fritter in â€‹a bowl of sugar. Coat both sides. Place on serving plate. Serve warm.
a265ec8d-b5df-445f-818e-6199e67eaf5f Gather the ingredients.
a265ec8d-b5df-445f-818e-6199e67eaf5f Peel the apples, if desired. Core them and then dice them or slice them into thin, uniform wedges. Alternatively, slice the cored apples crosswise to make thin circles.
a265ec8d-b5df-445f-818e-6199e67eaf5f Melt the butter in a heavy skillet or sauté pan over medium heat.
a265ec8d-b5df-445f-818e-6199e67eaf5f When the butter has melted and begins to foam, add the chopped or sliced apples, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and 2 tablespoons of water.
a265ec8d-b5df-445f-818e-6199e67eaf5f Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently, or until the apples are tender and the sugar mixture has become syrupy. Some varieties of apples hold their shape better than others. Add more water to the pan if necessary.
a265ec8d-b5df-445f-818e-6199e67eaf5f Serve over pancakes, ice cream, or inside of crepes, and enjoy!
407d6d54-05de-4fc0-b695-7cf949000e7c Gather the ingredients.
407d6d54-05de-4fc0-b695-7cf949000e7c Place a mesh sieve over a bowl and, from the canned pineapple, strain the pineapple juice into the bowl. Set the juice aside.
407d6d54-05de-4fc0-b695-7cf949000e7c Measure 6 tablespoons (about 1/3 cup) of crushed pineapple into a small bowl and set aside. Refrigerate or freeze any remaining crushed pineapple and juice for another use, if desired.
407d6d54-05de-4fc0-b695-7cf949000e7c Add butter to a large bowl. Using an electric mixer, cream the butter until smooth and pale. Gradually beat in the confectioners' sugar. Continue beating until light and fluffy.
407d6d54-05de-4fc0-b695-7cf949000e7c Stir in the 6 tablespoons of crushed pineapple and just enough of the reserved pineapple juice to make it spreadable. Beat to blend thoroughly.
407d6d54-05de-4fc0-b695-7cf949000e7c Spread over cake layers or cupcakes. If desired, add more crushed pineapple and spoon the mixture over a Bundt cake.
bd25fc0c-743e-463e-9bc6-0cc5a727baf7 Lightly butter the slow cooker and then add bread cubes.
bd25fc0c-743e-463e-9bc6-0cc5a727baf7 In a small bowl, whisk together the scalded milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, vanilla, and melted butter.
bd25fc0c-743e-463e-9bc6-0cc5a727baf7 Pour milk mixture over the bread cubes then add raisins, if desired.
bd25fc0c-743e-463e-9bc6-0cc5a727baf7 Using a large spoon or spatula, gently press bread cubes down into the mixture so all of the bread pieces are soaked with the milk and egg mixture. Do not stir.
bd25fc0c-743e-463e-9bc6-0cc5a727baf7 Cover and cook on the low setting for 5 to 6 hours or until the bread pudding is set.
bd25fc0c-743e-463e-9bc6-0cc5a727baf7 Serve with a dessert sauce or whipped cream.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Heat the oven to 300 F/150 C/Gas 2.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Lightly butter a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Trim the crusts from the bread; butter them lightly with about 2 teaspoons of softened butter and arrange them in the baking dish. If the slices are smaller than a standard loaf size, trim extra slices so they will make a full layer in the bottom of the baking dish. Set aside.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Heat the milk in a saucepan over low heat until hot, but not boiling.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 In a bowl, combine eggs, sugar, and salt; stir well.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 While whisking briskly, gradually stir about one-quarter of the hot milk into the egg mixture. Add the remaining hot milk, stirring constantly.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Whisk the cinnamon and vanilla extract into the egg and milk mixture.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Sprinkle the raisins over bread, if you are using them.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Pour the milk mixture over bread.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Sprinkle ground nutmeg lightly over the pudding mixture.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Bake the bread pudding uncovered in the preheated oven for about 50 minutes, or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 To brown the top slightly, turn the broiler on and continue to cook for a minute or two, or just until the top has browned.
8230188c-ccf9-407b-8458-968c7527b944 Serve warm with vanilla sauce, a caramel sauce, or purchased dessert sauce, as desired.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Generously grease and flour a 10-inch, one-piece tube cake pan or Bundt pan.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Put 3/4 cup of undrained pineapple with its juice in a small bowl; set aside.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Drain remaining pineapple and measure 1 cup of drained crushed pineapple; set aside.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the shortening and 1 cup of butter until smooth, about 2 minutes.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Gradually beat in the sugar and continue beating until the mixture is light and fluffy, or about 3 to 4 minutes.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Do not overbeat.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d In a separate bowl, combine the flour and baking powder and blend thoroughly.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Add one-third of the dry mixture to the creamed mixture and about half of the milk; blend well. Repeat with another third of the flour mixture and the remaining milk; blend well. Beat in the remaining flour mixture just until well blended.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Add the vanilla extract and the reserved 3/4 cup of undrained pineapple with juice; stir to blend.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Pour the batter into the prepared tube cake pan.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Place the cake in the unheated oven. Turn on the oven to 325 F and bake for 1 1/2 hours (do not preheat), or until a long wooden pick comes out clean when inserted into the center.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Let the cake stand for about 5 minutes in the pan on a rack.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Run a knife around the edge of the pan to loosen and then carefully remove the cake to a rack.
add51c06-0871-4cd3-92a7-06902e0d142d Combine 1/4 cup of butter, the confectioners' sugar, and the remaining 1 cup drained pineapple. Pour the pineapple sauce over the cake while it is still hot.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Gather the ingredients.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Combine the 2 1/2 cups of flour, 2 teaspoons of sugar, and 3/4 teaspoon of salt in a food processor. Pulse to blend thoroughly. Add half of the butter pieces and pulse 6 times. Add the remaining butter and pulse 6 to 8 more times. The mixture should look crumbly with larger pea-size pieces of butter visible.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Add about 7 tablespoons of ice water and pulse a few times. Add more water, about 1 teaspoon at a time, until the dough is moist enough to hold together when squeezed.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Turn the dough out onto a floured surface. Press the dough together and shape it into 2 flattened discs. Do not knead more than necessary to bring it together into a dough. Wrap the discs in plastic wrap and refrigerate for about 30 to 45 minutes.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Take one disc of dough out of the refrigerator. On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough into a circle about 2 inches larger than the upside-down pie plate. Fit the dough into the pie plate and leave the overhang.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Peel the pears and cut them in half lengthwise. Remove the cores and fibers and slice them thinly. Toss them in a bowl with the lemon zest and juice.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Turn the sliced pears into the pie crust. Combine 1 cup of sugar, 1/4 cup of flour, cinnamon, and 1/8 teaspoon of salt; sprinkle over the pears. Dot with the cut-up 2 tablespoons of butter.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Remove the remaining disc of dough from the refrigerator. On the lightly floured surface, roll it out and cut it into strips about 3/4-inch in width. Arrange five dough strips across the top of the filling. Weave the strips in a criss-cross pattern over the top of the pie. Fold every other strip back and place a new strip at a right angle to the first set.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b To create the latticework, unfold the strips you folded and fold the alternate strips. Place another new strip over the strips and unfold the folded strips again. Repeat until you have covered the pie with "woven" strips of dough. Cut any long ends and wrap the overhang over the ends of the strips. Flute as desired.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Combine the egg and 1 tablespoon of milk and whisk until well blended. Brush the egg wash lightly over the lattice strips. Avoid the edge for now. Set the egg wash aside.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Cover the fluted edge of pie with a strip of foil or pie shield.
62aa7a26-3933-4dfe-90e1-1a2c581ae96b Bake the pie at 425 F for 15 minutes. Remove pie shield and brush the egg wash over the crust edge. Reduce the oven temperature to 375 and bake the pie for about 20 to 25 minutes longer, or until the pears are tender and the crust is golden brown.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Gather the ingredients.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, and salt. Whisk or stir to blend thoroughly.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Make three wells in the flour mixture.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 In one put the vanilla; in another the vinegar, and in the third the vegetable oil.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Pour the cold water over the mixture and stir until moistened.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until it springs back when touched lightly.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Frost with chocolate frosting or your favorite icing or glaze. Or sift powdered sugar over the cake.
652dd182-bd24-451f-a4a8-1d2fb4328c23 Enjoy!
72dea114-9324-46de-96f1-375b6e6cbec8 Gather the ingredients.
72dea114-9324-46de-96f1-375b6e6cbec8 Line a baking pan or tray with wax paper or parchment paper.
72dea114-9324-46de-96f1-375b6e6cbec8 Sift the confectioners' sugar into a large bowl and add the sweetened condensed milk, coconut, melted butter, and pecans. Mix well with the help of a wooden spoon. Refrigerate for 30 minutes, covered.
72dea114-9324-46de-96f1-375b6e6cbec8 With your hands, shape the mixture into balls and place them on the pan or tray. Refrigerate the balls until the balls are very firm, or about 1 hour.
72dea114-9324-46de-96f1-375b6e6cbec8 Once the candy is hard, melt the wax and milk chocolate chips together in a double boiler. Make sure the water at the bottom is simmering and not boiling.
72dea114-9324-46de-96f1-375b6e6cbec8 Dip the chilled balls in the melted chocolate and let cool on top of wax paper.
72dea114-9324-46de-96f1-375b6e6cbec8 Enjoy!
